  version: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 255596ce6b91ac640b392e20dd4f8a9e, type: 2}
  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Creation'
      title: The Creation
      number: 1
      content: '  In the beginning God (Elohim)  created [by forming from nothing]
        the heavens and the earth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'The earth was formless and void or a waste and emptiness, and darkness
        was upon the face of the deep [primeval ocean that covered the unformed earth].
        The Spirit of God was moving (hovering, brooding) over the face of the waters. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And God said, \u201CLet there be light\u201D; and there was light. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'God saw that the light was good (pleasing, useful) and  He affirmed
        and sustained it; and God separated the light [distinguishing it] from the
        darkness. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And God called the light day, and the darkness He called night. And
        there was evening and there was morning, one day.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And God said, \u201CLet there be an expanse [of the sky] in the midst
        of the waters, and let it separate the waters [below the expanse] from the
        waters [above the expanse].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And God made the expanse [of sky] and separated the waters which
        were under the expanse from the waters which were above the expanse; and
        it was so [just as He commanded]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'God called the expanse [of sky] heaven. And there was evening and
        there was morning, a second day.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Then God said, \u201CLet the waters below the heavens be gathered
        into one place [of standing, pooling together], and let the dry land appear\u201D;
        and it was so. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'God called the dry land earth, and the gathering of the waters He
        called seas; and God saw that this was good (pleasing, useful) and He affirmed
        and sustained it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "So God said, \u201CLet the earth sprout [tender] vegetation, plants
        yielding seed, and fruit trees bearing fruit according to (limited to, consistent
        with) their kind, whose seed is in them upon the earth\u201D; and it was
        so. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'The earth sprouted and abundantly produced vegetation, plants yielding
        seed according to their kind, and trees bearing fruit with seed in them,
        according to their kind; and God saw that it was good and He affirmed and
        sustained it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And there was evening and there was morning, a third day.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Then God said, \u201CLet there be light-bearers (sun, moon, stars)
        in the expanse of the heavens to separate the day from the night, and let
        them be useful for signs (tokens) [of God\u2019s provident care], and for
        marking seasons, days, and years; "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "and let them be useful as lights in the expanse of the heavens to
        provide light on the earth\u201D; and it was so, [just as He commanded]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "God made the two great lights\u2014the greater light (the sun) to
        rule the day, and the lesser light (the moon) to rule the night; He made
        the [galaxies of] stars also [that is, all the amazing wonders in the heavens]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'God placed them in the expanse of the heavens to provide light upon
        the earth, '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'to rule over the day and the night, and to separate the light from
        the darkness; and God saw that it was good and He affirmed and sustained
        it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And there was evening and there was morning, a fourth day.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Then God said, \u201CLet the waters swarm and abundantly produce
        living creatures, and let birds soar above the earth in the open expanse
        of the heavens.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'God created the great sea monsters and every living creature that
        moves, with which the waters swarmed according to their kind, and every winged
        bird according to its kind; and God saw that it was good and He affirmed
        and sustained it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "And God blessed them, saying, \u201CBe fruitful, multiply, and fill
        the waters in the seas, and let birds multiply on the earth.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'And there was evening and there was morning, a fifth day.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Then God said, \u201CLet the earth bring forth living creatures according
        to (limited to, consistent with) their kind: livestock, crawling things,
        and wild animals of the earth according to their kinds\u201D; and it was
        so [because He had spoken them into creation]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'So God made the wild animals of the earth according to their kind,
        and the cattle according to their kind, and everything that creeps and crawls
        on the earth according to its kind; and God saw that it was good (pleasing,
        useful) and He affirmed and sustained it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Then God said, \u201CLet Us (Father, Son, Holy Spirit) make man in
        Our image, according to Our likeness [not physical, but a spiritual personality
        and moral likeness]; and let them have complete authority over the fish of
        the sea, the birds of the air, the cattle, and over the entire earth, and
        over everything that creeps and crawls on the earth.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'So God created man in His own image, in the image and likeness of
        God He created him; male and female He created them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "And God blessed them [granting them certain authority] and said to
        them, \u201CBe fruitful, multiply, and fill the earth, and subjugate it [putting
        it under your power]; and rule over (dominate) the fish of the sea, the birds
        of the air, and every living thing that moves upon the earth.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "So God said, \u201CBehold, I have given you every plant yielding
        seed that is on the surface of the entire earth, and every tree which has
        fruit yielding seed; it shall be food for you; "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "and to all the animals on the earth and to every bird of the air
        and to everything that moves on the ground\u2014to everything in which there
        is the breath of life\u2014I have given every green plant for food\u201D;
        and it was so [because He commanded it]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: God saw everything that He had made, and behold, it was very good
        and He validated it completely. And there was evening and there was morning,
        a sixth day.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Creation of Man and Woman'
      title: The Creation of Man and Woman
      number: 1
      content: '  So the heavens and the earth were completed, and all their hosts
        (inhabitants). '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And by the seventh day God completed His work which He had done,
        and He rested (ceased) on the seventh day from all His work which He had
        done. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'So God blessed the seventh day and sanctified it [as His own, that
        is, set it apart as holy from other days], because in it He rested from all
        His work which He had created and done.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "This is the history of [the origin of] the heavens and of the earth
        when they were created, in the day [that is, days of creation] that the Lord
        God made the earth and the heavens\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'no shrub or plant of the field was yet in the earth, and no herb
        of the field had yet sprouted, for the Lord God had not caused it to rain
        on the earth, and there was no man to cultivate the ground, '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "but a mist (fog, dew, vapor) used to rise from the land and water
        the entire surface of the ground\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'then the Lord God formed [that is, created the body of] man from
        the dust of the ground, and breathed into his nostrils the breath of life;
        and the man became a living being [an individual complete in body and spirit]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And the Lord God planted a garden (oasis) in the east, in Eden (delight,
        land of happiness); and He put the man whom He had formed (created) there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And [in that garden] the Lord God caused to grow from the ground
        every tree that is desirable and pleasing to the sight and good (suitable,
        pleasant) for food; the tree of life was also in the midst of the garden,
        and the tree of the [experiential] knowledge (recognition) of [the difference
        between] good and evil.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Now a river flowed out of Eden to water the garden; and from there
        it divided and became four [branching] rivers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'The first [river] is named Pishon; it flows around the entire land
        of Havilah, where there is gold. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'The gold of that land is good; bdellium (a fragrant, valuable resin)
        and the onyx stone are found there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'The name of the second river is Gihon; it flows around the entire
        land of Cush [in Mesopotamia]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'The third river is named Hiddekel (Tigris); it flows east of Assyria.
        And the fourth river is the Euphrates.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'So the Lord God took the man [He had made] and settled him in the
        Garden of Eden to cultivate and keep it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And the Lord God commanded the man, saying, \u201CYou may freely
        (unconditionally) eat [the fruit] from every tree of the garden; "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "but [only] from the tree of the knowledge (recognition) of good and
        evil you shall not eat, otherwise on the day that you eat from it, you shall
        most certainly die [because of your disobedience].\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Now the Lord God said, \u201CIt is not good (beneficial) for the
        man to be alone; I will make him a helper [one who balances him\u2014a counterpart
        who is] suitable and complementary for him.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'So the Lord God formed out of the ground every animal of the field
        and every bird of the air, and brought them to Adam to see what he would
        call them; and whatever the man called a living creature, that was its name. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And the man gave names to all the livestock, and to the birds of
        the air, and to every animal of the field; but for Adam there was not found
        a helper [that was] suitable (a companion) for him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'So the Lord God caused a deep sleep to fall upon Adam; and while
        he slept, He took one of his ribs and closed up the flesh at that place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'And the rib which the Lord God had taken from the man He made (fashioned,
        formed) into a woman, and He brought her and presented her to the man. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Then Adam said,\u201CThis is now bone of my bones,And flesh of my
        flesh;She shall be called Woman,Because she was taken out of Man.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'For this reason a man shall leave his father and his mother, and
        shall be joined to his wife; and they shall become one flesh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: And the man and his wife were both naked and were not ashamed or embarrassed.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Fall of Man'
      title: The Fall of Man
      number: 1
      content: "  Now the serpent was more crafty (subtle, skilled in deceit) than
        any living creature of the field which the Lord God had made. And the serpent
        (Satan) said to the woman, \u201CCan it really be that God has said, \u2018You
        shall not eat from any tree of the garden\u2019?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And the woman said to the serpent, \u201CWe may eat fruit from the
        trees of the garden, "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "except the fruit from the tree which is in the middle of the garden.
        God said, \u2018You shall not eat from it nor touch it, otherwise you will
        die.\u2019\u2009\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "But the serpent said to the woman, \u201CYou certainly will not die! "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "For God knows that on the day you eat from it your eyes will be opened
        [that is, you will have greater awareness], and you will be like God, knowing
        [the difference between] good and evil.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And when the woman saw that the tree was good for food, and that
        it was delightful to look at, and a tree to be desired in order to make one
        wise and insightful, she took some of its fruit and ate it; and she also
        gave some to her husband with her, and he ate. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Then the eyes of the two of them were opened [that is, their awareness
        increased], and they knew that they were naked; and they fastened fig leaves
        together and made themselves coverings.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And they heard the sound of the Lord God walking in the garden in
        the cool [afternoon breeze] of the day, so the man and his wife hid and kept
        themselves hidden from the presence of the Lord God among the trees of the
        garden. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "But the Lord God called to Adam, and said to him, \u201CWhere are
        you?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "He said, \u201CI heard the sound of You [walking] in the garden,
        and I was afraid because I was naked; so I hid myself.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "God said, \u201CWho told you that you were naked? Have you eaten
        [fruit] from the tree of which I commanded you not to eat?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And the man said, \u201CThe woman whom You gave to be with me\u2014she
        gave me [fruit] from the tree, and I ate it.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Then the Lord God said to the woman, \u201CWhat is this that you
        have done?\u201D And the woman said, \u201CThe serpent beguiled and deceived
        me, and I ate [from the forbidden tree].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "The Lord God said to the serpent,\u201CBecause you have done this,You
        are cursed more than all the cattle,And more than any animal of the field;On
        your belly you shall go,And dust you shall eatAll the days of your life.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And I will put enmity (open hostility)Between you and the woman,And
        between your seed (offspring) and her Seed;He shall [fatally] bruise your
        head,And you shall [only] bruise His heel.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "To the woman He said,\u201CI will greatly multiplyYour pain in childbirth;In
        pain you will give birth to children;Yet your desire and longing will be
        for your husband,And he will rule [with authority] over you and be responsible
        for you.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Then to Adam the Lord God said, \u201CBecause you have listened [attentively]
        to the voice of your wife, and have eaten [fruit] from the tree about which
        I commanded you, saying, \u2018You shall not eat of it\u2019;The ground is
        [now] under a curse because of you;In sorrow and toil you shall eat [the
        fruit] of itAll the days of your life.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Both thorns and thistles it shall grow for you;And you shall eat
        the plants of the field.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "By the sweat of your faceYou will eat breadUntil you return to the
        ground,For from it you were taken;For you are dust,And to dust you shall
        return.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'The man named his wife Eve (life spring, life giver), because she
        was the mother of all the living. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'The Lord God made tunics of [animal] skins for Adam and his wife
        and clothed them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "And the Lord God said, \u201CBehold, the man has become like one
        of Us (Father, Son, Holy Spirit), knowing [how to distinguish between] good
        and evil; and now, he might stretch out his hand, and take from the tree
        of life as well, and eat [its fruit], and live [in this fallen, sinful condition]
        forever\u201D\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'therefore the Lord God sent Adam away from the Garden of Eden, to
        till and cultivate the ground from which he was taken. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: So God drove the man out; and at the east of the Garden of Eden He
        [permanently] stationed the cherubim and the sword with the flashing blade
        which turned round and round [in every direction] to protect and guard the
        way (entrance, access) to the tree of life.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Cain and Abel'
      title: Cain and Abel
      number: 1
      content: "  Now the man Adam knew Eve as his wife, and she conceived and gave
        birth to Cain, and she said, \u201CI have obtained a man (baby boy, son)
        with the help of the Lord.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And [later] she gave birth to his brother Abel. Now Abel kept the
        flocks [of sheep and goats], but Cain cultivated the ground. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And in the course of time Cain brought to the Lord an offering of
        the fruit of the ground. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'But Abel brought [an offering of] the [finest] firstborn of his flock
        and the fat portions. And the Lord had respect (regard) for Abel and for
        his offering; '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'but for Cain and his offering He had no respect. So Cain became extremely
        angry (indignant), and he looked annoyed and hostile. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And the Lord said to Cain, \u201CWhy are you so angry? And why do
        you look annoyed? "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "If you do well [believing Me and doing what is acceptable and pleasing
        to Me], will you not be accepted? And if you do not do well [but ignore My
        instruction], sin crouches at your door; its desire is for you [to overpower
        you], but you must master it.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Cain talked with Abel his brother [about what God had said]. And
        when they were [alone, working] in the field, Cain attacked Abel his brother
        and killed him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Then the Lord said to Cain, \u201CWhere is Abel your brother?\u201D
        And he [lied and] said, \u201CI do not know. Am I my brother\u2019s keeper?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "The Lord said, \u201CWhat have you done? The voice of your brother\u2019s
        [innocent] blood is crying out to Me from the ground [for justice]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And now you are cursed from the ground, which has opened its mouth
        to receive your brother\u2019s [shed] blood from your hand. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "When you cultivate the ground, it shall no longer yield its strength
        [it will resist producing good crops] for you; you shall be a fugitive and
        a vagabond [roaming aimlessly] on the earth [in perpetual exile without a
        home, a degraded outcast].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Cain said to the Lord, \u201CMy punishment is greater than I can
        bear. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Behold, You have driven me out this day from the face of the land;
        and from Your face (presence) I will be hidden, and I will be a fugitive
        and an [aimless] vagabond on the earth, and whoever finds me will kill me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And the Lord said to him, \u201CTherefore, whoever kills Cain, a
        sevenfold vengeance [that is, punishment seven times worse] shall be taken
        on him [by Me].\u201D And the Lord set a [protective] mark (sign) on Cain,
        so that no one who found (met) him would kill him.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'So Cain went away from the [manifested] presence of the Lord, and
        lived in the land of Nod [wandering in exile], east of Eden.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Cain knew his wife [one of Adam\u2019s descendants] and she conceived
        and gave birth to Enoch; and Cain built a city and named it Enoch, after
        the name of his son. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Now to Enoch was born Irad, and Irad became the father of Mehujael,
        and Mehujael became the father of Methushael, and Methushael became the father
        of Lamech. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And Lamech took for himself two wives; the name of the one was Adah,
        and the name of the other, Zillah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Adah gave birth to Jabal; he became the father of those [nomadic
        herdsmen] who live in tents and have cattle and raise livestock. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "His brother\u2019s name was Jubal; he became the father of all those
        [musicians] who play the lyre and flute. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Zillah gave birth to Tubal-cain, the smith (craftsman) and teacher
        of every artisan in instruments of bronze and iron. The sister of Tubal-cain
        was Naamah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Lamech said to his wives,\u201CAdah and Zillah,Hear my voice;You
        wives of Lamech,Listen to what I say;For I have killed a man [merely] for
        wounding me,And a boy [only] for striking (bruising) me.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "If Cain is avenged sevenfold [as the Lord said he would be],Then
        Lamech [will be avenged] seventy-sevenfold.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Adam knew [Eve as] his wife again; and she gave birth to a son, and
        named him Seth, for [she said], \u201CGod has granted another child for me
        in place of Abel, because Cain killed him.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: To Seth, also, a son was born, whom he named Enosh (mortal man, mankind).
        At that [same] time men began to call on the name of the Lord [in worship
        through prayer, praise, and thanksgiving].
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Descendants of Adam'
      title: Descendants of Adam
      number: 1
      content: '  This is the book (the written record, the history) of the generations
        of [the descendants of] Adam. When God created man, He made him in the likeness
        of God [not physical, but a spiritual personality and moral likeness]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'He created them male and female, and blessed them and named them
        Mankind at the time they were created.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'When Adam had lived a hundred and thirty years, he became the father
        of a son in his own likeness, according to his image, and named him Seth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'After he became the father of Seth, Adam lived eight hundred years
        and had other sons and daughters. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'So Adam lived nine hundred and thirty years in all, and he died.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'When Seth was a hundred and five years old, he became the father
        of Enosh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Seth lived eight hundred and seven years after the birth of Enosh,
        and he had other sons and daughters. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'So Seth lived nine hundred and twelve years, and he died.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'When Enosh was ninety years old, he became the father of Kenan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Enosh lived eight hundred and fifteen years after the birth of Kenan
        and had other sons and daughters. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'So Enosh lived nine hundred and five years, and he died.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'When Kenan was seventy years old, he became the father of Mahalalel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Kenan lived eight hundred and forty years after the birth of Mahalalel
        and had other sons and daughters. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'So Kenan lived nine hundred and ten years, and he died.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'When Mahalalel was sixty-five years old, he became the father of
        Jared. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Mahalalel lived eight hundred and thirty years after the birth of
        Jared and had other sons and daughters. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'So Mahalalel lived eight hundred and ninety-five years, and he died.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'When Jared was a hundred and sixty-two years old, he became the father
        of Enoch. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Jared lived eight hundred years after the birth of Enoch and had
        other sons and daughters. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'So Jared lived nine hundred and sixty-two years, and he died.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'When Enoch was sixty-five years old, he became the father of Methuselah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Enoch walked [in habitual fellowship] with God three hundred years
        after the birth of Methuselah and had other sons and daughters. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'So all the days of Enoch were three hundred and sixty-five years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'And [in reverent fear and obedience] Enoch walked with God; and he
        was not [found among men], because God took him [away to be home with Him].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'When Methuselah was a hundred and eighty-seven years old, he became
        the father of Lamech. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Methuselah lived seven hundred and eighty-two years after the birth
        of Lamech and had other sons and daughters. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'So Methuselah lived nine hundred and sixty-nine years, and he died.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'When Lamech was a hundred and eighty-two years old, he became the
        father of a son. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "He named him Noah, saying, \u201CThis one shall bring us rest and
        comfort from our work and from the [dreadful] toil of our hands because of
        the ground which the Lord cursed.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Lamech lived five hundred and ninety-five years after the birth of
        Noah and had other sons and daughters. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'So all the days of Lamech were seven hundred and seventy-seven years,
        and he died.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: After Noah was five hundred years old, he became the father of Shem,
        Ham, and Japheth.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Corruption of Mankind'
      title: The Corruption of Mankind
      number: 1
      content: '  Now it happened, when men began to multiply on the face of the
        land, and daughters were born to them, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'that the sons of God saw that the daughters of men were beautiful
        and desirable; and they took wives for themselves, whomever they chose and
        desired. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Then the Lord said, \u201CMy Spirit shall not strive and remain with
        man forever, because he is indeed flesh [sinful, corrupt\u2014given over
        to sensual appetites]; nevertheless his days shall yet be a hundred and twenty
        years.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "There were Nephilim (men of stature, notorious men) on the earth
        in those days\u2014and also afterward\u2014when the sons of God lived with
        the daughters of men, and they gave birth to their children. These were the
        mighty men who were of old, men of renown (great reputation, fame).  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'The Lord saw that the wickedness (depravity) of man was great on
        the earth, and that every imagination or intent of the thoughts of his heart
        were only evil continually. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'The Lord  regretted that He had made mankind on the earth, and He
        was [deeply] grieved in His heart. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "So the Lord said, \u201CI will destroy (annihilate) mankind whom
        I have created from the surface of the earth\u2014not only man, but the animals
        and the crawling things and the birds of the air\u2014because it [deeply]
        grieves Me [to see mankind\u2019s sin] and I regret that I have made them.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'But Noah found favor and grace in the eyes of the Lord.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'These are the records of the generations (family history) of Noah.
        Noah was a righteous man [one who was just and had right standing with God],
        blameless in his [evil] generation; Noah walked (lived) [in habitual fellowship]
        with God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Now Noah became the father of three sons: Shem, Ham, and Japheth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "The [population of the] earth was corrupt [absolutely depraved\u2014spiritually
        and morally putrid] in God\u2019s sight, and the land was filled with violence
        [desecration, infringement, outrage, assault, and lust for power]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'God looked on the earth and saw how debased and degenerate it was,
        for all humanity had corrupted their way on the earth and lost their true
        direction.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "God said to Noah, \u201CI intend to make an end of all that lives,
        for through men the land is filled with violence; and behold, I am about
        to destroy them together with the land. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Make yourself an ark of gopher wood; make in it rooms (stalls, pens,
        coops, nests, cages, compartments) and coat it inside and out with pitch
        (bitumen). '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "This is the way you are to make it: the length of the ark shall be
        three hundred cubits, its width fifty cubits, and its height thirty cubits
        (450\u2019 x 75\u2019 x 45\u2019). "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "You shall make a window [for light and ventilation] for the ark,
        and finish it to at least a cubit (eighteen inches) from the top\u2014and
        set the [entry] door of the ark in its side; and you shall make it with lower,
        second and third decks. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'For behold, I, even I, will bring a flood of waters on the earth,
        to destroy all life under the heavens in which there is the breath and spirit
        of life; everything that is on the land shall die. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "But I will establish My covenant (solemn promise, formal agreement)
        with you; and you shall come into the ark\u2014you and your [three] sons
        and your wife, and your sons\u2019 wives with you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And of every living thing [found on land], you shall bring two of
        every kind into the ark, to keep them alive with you; they shall be male
        and female. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Of fowls and birds according to their kind, of animals according
        to their kind, of every crawling thing of the ground according to its kind\u2014two
        of every kind shall come to you to keep them alive. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Also take with you every kind of food that is edible, and you shall
        collect and store it; and it shall be food for you and for them.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: So Noah did this; according to all that God commanded him, that is
        what he did.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Flood'
      title: The Flood
      number: 1
      content: "  Then the Lord said to Noah, \u201CCome into the ark, you with all
        your household, for you [alone] I have seen as righteous (doing what is right)
        before Me in this generation. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Of every clean animal you shall take with you seven pair, the male
        and his female, and of animals that are not clean, two each the male and
        his female; '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'also of the birds of the air, seven pair, the male and the female,
        to keep the offspring alive on the surface of the earth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "For in seven days I am going to cause it to rain on the earth for
        forty days and forty nights; and I will destroy (blot out, wipe away) every
        living thing that I have made from the surface of the earth.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'So Noah did all that the Lord commanded him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Noah was six hundred years old when the flood (deluge) of water came
        on the earth [covering all of the land]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Then Noah and his sons and his wife and his sons\u2019 wives with
        him entered the ark to escape the flood waters. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Of clean animals and animals that are not clean and birds and fowls
        and everything that crawls on the ground, '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'they came [motivated by God] into the ark with Noah two by two, the
        male and the female, just as God had commanded Noah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And after the seven days [God released the rain and] the floodwaters
        came on the earth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "In the six hundredth year of Noah\u2019s life, on the seventeenth
        day of the second month, on that same day all the fountains of the great
        deep [subterranean waters] burst open, and the windows and floodgates of
        the heavens were opened. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'It rained on the earth for forty days and forty nights.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "On the very same day Noah and Shem and Ham and Japheth, the sons
        of Noah, and Noah\u2019s wife and the three wives of his sons with them,
        entered the ark, "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'they and every animal according to its kind, all the livestock according
        to their kinds, every moving thing that crawls on the earth according to
        its kind, and every bird according to its kind, every winged thing of every
        sort. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'So they went into the ark with Noah, two by two of all living beings
        in which there was the breath and spirit of life. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Those which entered, male and female of all flesh (creatures), entered
        as God had commanded Noah; and the Lord closed the door behind him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'The flood [the great downpour of rain] was forty days and nights
        on the earth; and the waters increased and lifted up the ark, and it floated
        [high] above the land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'The waters became mighty and increased greatly on the earth, and
        the ark floated on the surface of the waters. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'The waters prevailed so greatly and were so mighty and overwhelming
        on the earth, so that all the high mountains everywhere under the heavens
        were covered. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: '[In fact] the waters became fifteen cubits higher [than the highest
        ground], and the mountains were covered. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "All living beings that moved on the earth perished\u2014birds and
        cattle (domestic animals), [wild] animals, all things that swarm and crawl
        on the earth, and all mankind. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Everything on the dry land, all in whose nostrils was the breath
        and spirit of life, died. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'God destroyed (blotted out, wiped away) every living thing that was
        on the surface of the earth; man and animals and the crawling things and
        the birds of the heavens were destroyed from the land. Only Noah and those
        who were with him in the ark remained alive. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: The waters covered [all of] the earth for a hundred and fifty days
        (five months).
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Flood Abates'
      title: The Flood Abates
      number: 1
      content: '  And God remembered and thought kindly of Noah and every living
        thing and all the animals that were with him in the ark; and God made a wind
        blow over the land, and the waters receded. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Also the fountains of the deep [subterranean waters] and the windows
        of the heavens were closed, the [pouring] rain from the sky was restrained, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'and the waters receded steadily from the earth. At the end of a hundred
        and fifty days the waters had diminished. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'On the seventeenth day of the seventh month [five months after the
        rain began], the ark came to rest on the mountains of Ararat [in Turkey]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'The waters continued to decrease until the tenth month; on the first
        day of the tenth month the tops of the mountains were seen.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'At the end of [another] forty days Noah opened the window of the
        ark which he had made; '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'and he sent out a raven, which flew here and there until the waters
        were dried up from the earth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Then Noah sent out a dove to see if the water level had fallen below
        the surface of the land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'But the dove found no place on which to rest the sole of her foot,
        and she returned to him to the ark, for the waters were [still] on the face
        of the entire earth. So he reached out his hand and took the dove, and brought
        her into the ark. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'He waited another seven days and again sent the dove out from the
        ark. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'The dove came back to him in the evening, and there, in her beak,
        was a fresh olive leaf. So Noah knew that the water level had subsided from
        the earth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Then he waited another seven days and sent out the dove, but she
        did not return to him again.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Now in the six hundred and first year [of Noah\u2019s life], on the
        first day of the first month, the waters were drying up from the earth. Then
        Noah removed the covering of the ark and looked, and the surface of the ground
        was drying. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'On the twenty-seventh day of the second month the land was [entirely]
        dry. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And God spoke to Noah, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CGo out of the ark, you and your wife and your sons and their
        wives with you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Bring out with you every living thing from all flesh\u2014birds and
        animals and every crawling thing that crawls on the earth\u2014that they
        may breed abundantly on the earth, and be fruitful and multiply on the earth.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'So Noah went out, and his wife and his sons and their wives with
        him [after being in the ark one year and ten days]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Every animal, every crawling thing, every bird\u2014and whatever
        moves on the land\u2014went out by families (types, groupings) from the ark.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And Noah built an altar to the Lord, and took of every [ceremonially]
        clean animal and of every clean bird and offered burnt offerings on the altar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "The Lord smelled the pleasing aroma [a soothing, satisfying scent]
        and the Lord said to Himself, \u201CI will never again curse the ground because
        of man, for the intent (strong inclination, desire) of man\u2019s heart is
        wicked from his youth; and I will never again destroy every living thing,
        as I have done.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "While the earth remains,Seedtime and harvest,Cold and heat,Winter
        and summer,And day and nightShall not cease.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Covenant of the Rainbow'
      title: Covenant of the Rainbow
      number: 1
      content: "  And God blessed Noah and his sons and said to them, \u201CBe fruitful
        and multiply, and fill the earth. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'The fear and the terror of you shall be [instinctive] in every animal
        of the land and in every bird of the air; and together with everything that
        moves on the ground, and with all the fish of the sea; they are given into
        your hand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Every moving thing that lives shall be food for you; I give you everything,
        as I gave you the green plants and vegetables. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'But you shall not eat meat along with its life, that is, its blood. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "For your lifeblood I will most certainly require an accounting; from
        every animal [that kills a person] I will require it. And from man, from
        every man\u2019s brother [that is, anyone who murders] I will require the
        life of man.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Whoever sheds man\u2019s blood [unlawfully],By man (judicial government)
        shall his blood be shed,For in the image of GodHe made man.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "As for you, be fruitful and multiply;Populate the earth abundantly
        and multiply in it.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Then God spoke to Noah and to his sons with him, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CNow behold, I am establishing My covenant (binding agreement,
        solemn promise) with you and with your descendants after you "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "and with every living creature that is with you\u2014the birds, the
        livestock, and the wild animals of the earth along with you, of everything
        that comes out of the ark\u2014every living creature of the earth. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "I will establish My covenant with you: Never again shall all flesh
        be cut off by the water of a flood, nor shall there ever again be a flood
        to destroy and ruin the earth.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And God said, \u201CThis is the token (visible symbol, memorial)
        of the [solemn] covenant which I am making between Me and you and every living
        creature that is with you, for all future generations; "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'I set My rainbow in the clouds, and it shall be a sign of a covenant
        between Me and the earth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'It shall come about, when I bring clouds over the earth, that the
        rainbow shall be seen in the clouds, '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'and I will [compassionately] remember My covenant, which is between
        Me and you and every living creature of all flesh; and never again will the
        water become a flood to destroy all flesh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "When the rainbow is in the clouds and I look at it, I will [solemnly]
        remember the everlasting covenant between God and every living creature of
        all flesh that is on the earth.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "And God said to Noah, \u201CThis [rainbow] is the sign of the covenant
        (solemn pledge, binding agreement) which I have established between Me and
        all living things on the earth.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'The sons of Noah who came out of the ark were Shem and Ham and Japheth.
        Ham would become the father of Canaan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'These are the three sons of Noah, and from these [men] the whole
        earth was populated and scattered with inhabitants.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And Noah began to farm and cultivate the ground and he planted a
        vineyard. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'He drank some of the wine and became drunk, and he was uncovered
        and lay exposed inside his tent. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Ham, the father of Canaan, saw [by accident] the nakedness of his
        father, and [to his father\u2019s shame] told his two brothers outside. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "So Shem and Japheth took a robe and put it on both their shoulders,
        and walked backwards and covered the nakedness of their father; their faces
        were turned away so that they did not see their father\u2019s nakedness. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'When Noah awoke from his wine [induced stupor], he knew what his
        younger son [Ham] had done to him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "So he said,\u201CCursed be Canaan [the son of Ham];  A servant of
        servantsHe shall be to his brothers.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "He also said,\u201CBlessed be the Lord,The God of Shem;And let Canaan
        be his servant.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "May God enlarge [the land of] Japheth,And let him dwell in the tents
        of Shem;And let Canaan be his servant.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Noah lived three hundred and fifty years after the flood. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: So all the days of Noah were nine hundred and fifty years, and he
        died.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Descendants of Noah'
      title: Descendants of Noah
      number: 1
      content: '  These are the records of the generations (descendants) of Shem,
        Ham, and Japheth, the sons of Noah; and the sons born to them after the flood:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'the sons of Japheth: Gomer, Magog, Madai, Javan, Tubal, Meshech,
        and Tiras; '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'the sons of Gomer: Ashkenaz, Riphath, and Togarmah; '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'the sons of Javan: Elishah, Tarshish, Kittim, and Dodanim. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'From these, [the people of] the coastlands of the nations were separated
        and spread into their lands, every one according to his own language, according
        to their constituent groups (families), and into their nations:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'the sons of Ham: Cush, Mizraim [from whom descended the Egyptians],
        Put, and Canaan; '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'the sons of Cush: Seba, Havilah, Sabtah, Raamah, and Sabteca; and
        the sons of Raamah; Sheba and Dedan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Cush became the father of Nimrod; he became a mighty one on the earth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "He was a mighty hunter before the Lord; therefore it is said, \u201CLike
        Nimrod a mighty hunter before the Lord.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'The beginning of his kingdom was Babel and Erech and Accad and Calneh,
        in the land of Shinar [in Babylonia]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'From that land Nimrod went to Assyria, and built Nineveh, and Rehoboth-Ir,
        and Calah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'and [Nimrod built] Resen, which is between Nineveh and Calah; all
        these [combined to form] the great city [Nineveh]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Mizraim [the ancestor of the Egyptians] became the father of Ludim,
        Anamim, Lehabim, Naphtuhim '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "and Pathrusim and Casluhim\u2014from whom came the Philistines\u2014and
        Caphtorim.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Canaan became the father of Sidon, his firstborn, and Heth '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'and the Jebusite and the Amorite and the Girgashite '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'and the Hivite and the Arkite and the Sinite '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'and the Arvadite and the Zemarite and the Hamathite. Afterward the
        families of the Canaanite were spread abroad. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'The territory of the Canaanite extended from Sidon as one goes to
        Gerar, as far as Gaza; and as one goes to Sodom and Gomorrah and Admah and
        Zeboiim, as far as Lasha. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'These are the descendants of Ham according to their constituent groups,
        according to their languages, by their lands, and by their nations.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Also to Shem, the father of all the children of Eber [including the
        Hebrews], the older brother of Japheth, children were born. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'The sons of Shem: Elam, Asshur, Arpachshad, Lud and Aram; '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'the sons of Aram [ancestor of the Syrians]: Uz, Hul, Gether and Mash. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Arpachshad became the father of Shelah; and Shelah became the father
        of Eber. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Two sons were born to Eber; the name of one was Peleg (division),
        for [the inhabitants of] the earth were divided in his days; and his brother\u2019s
        name was Joktan. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Joktan became the father of Almodad, Sheleph, Hazarmaveth, Jerah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'and Hadoram, Uzal, Diklah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'and Obal, Abimael, Sheba, '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'and Ophir, Havilah, and Jobab; all these were the sons of Joktan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Now their territory extended from Mesha as one goes toward Sephar,
        to the hill country of the east. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "These are Shem\u2019s descendants according to their constituent
        groups (families), according to their languages, by their lands, according
        to their nations.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: These are the families of the sons of Noah, according to their descendants,
        by their nations; and from these [people] the nations were separated and
        spread abroad on the earth after the flood.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Universal Language, Babel, Confusion'
      title: Universal Language, Babel, Confusion
      number: 1
      content: '  Now the whole earth spoke one language and used the same words
        (vocabulary). '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And as people journeyed eastward, they found a plain in the land
        of Shinar and they settled there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "They said one to another, \u201CCome, let us make bricks and fire
        them thoroughly [in a kiln, to harden and strengthen them].\u201D So they
        used brick for stone [as building material], and they used tar (bitumen,
        asphalt) for mortar. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "They said, \u201CCome, let us build a city for ourselves, and a tower
        whose top will reach into the heavens, and let us make a [famous] name for
        ourselves, so that we will not be scattered [into separate groups] and be
        dispersed over the surface of the entire earth [as the Lord instructed].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Now the Lord came down to see the city and the tower which the sons
        of men had built. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And the Lord said, \u201CBehold, they are one [unified] people, and
        they all have the same language. This is only the beginning of what they
        will do [in rebellion against Me], and now no evil thing they imagine they
        can do will be impossible for them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Come, let Us (Father, Son, Holy Spirit) go down and there confuse
        and mix up their language, so that they will not understand one another\u2019s
        speech.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'So the Lord scattered them abroad from there over the surface of
        the entire earth; and they stopped building the city. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: Descendants of Shem'
      title: Descendants of Shem
      number: 9
      content: "Therefore the name of the city was Babel\u2014because there the Lord
        confused the language of the entire earth; and from that place the Lord scattered
        and dispersed them over the surface of all the earth.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'These are the records of the generations of Shem [from whom Abraham
        descended]. Shem was a hundred years old when he became the father of Arpachshad,
        two years after the flood. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And Shem lived five hundred years after Arpachshad was born, and
        he had other sons and daughters.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'When Arpachshad had lived thirty-five years, he became the father
        of Shelah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Arpachshad lived four hundred and three years after Shelah was born,
        and he had other sons and daughters.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'When Shelah had lived thirty years, he became the father of Eber. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Shelah lived four hundred and three years after Eber was born, and
        he had other sons and daughters.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'When Eber had lived thirty-four years, he became the father of Peleg. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And Eber lived four hundred and thirty years after Peleg was born,
        and he had other sons and daughters.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'When Peleg had lived thirty years, he became the father of Reu. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And Peleg lived two hundred and nine years after Reu was born, and
        he had other sons and daughters.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'When Reu had lived thirty-two years, he became the father of Serug. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And Reu lived two hundred and seven years after Serug was born, and
        he had other sons and daughters.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'When Serug had lived thirty years, he became the father of Nahor. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'And Serug lived two hundred years after Nahor was born, and he had
        other sons and daughters.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'When Nahor had lived twenty-nine years, he became the father of Terah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'And Nahor lived a hundred and nineteen years after Terah was born,
        and he had other sons and daughters.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'After Terah had lived seventy years, he became the father of Abram
        and Nahor and Haran [his firstborn].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Now these are the records of the descendants of Terah. Terah was
        the father of Abram (Abraham), Nahor, and Haran; and Haran was the father
        of Lot. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Haran died before his father Terah in the land of his birth, in Ur
        of the Chaldeans. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Abram and Nahor took wives for themselves. The name of Abram\u2019s
        wife was Sarai (later called Sarah), and the name of Nahor\u2019s wife was
        Milcah, the daughter of Haran, the father of Milcah and Iscah. "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'But Sarai was barren; she did not have a child.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "Terah took Abram his son, and Lot the son of Haran, his grandson,
        and Sarai his daughter-in-law, his son Abram\u2019s wife; and they went out
        together to go from Ur of the Chaldeans into the land of Canaan; but when
        they came to Haran [about five hundred and fifty miles northwest of Ur],
        they settled there. "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: Terah lived two hundred and five years; and Terah died in Haran.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Abram Journeys to Egypt'
      title: Abram Journeys to Egypt
      number: 1
      content: "  Now [in Haran] the Lord had said to Abram,\u201CGo away from your
        country,And from your relativesAnd from your father\u2019s house,To the land
        which I will show you;  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And I will make you a great nation,And I will bless you [abundantly],And
        make your name great (exalted, distinguished);And you shall be a blessing
        [a source of great good to others];  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And I will bless (do good for, benefit) those who bless you,And I
        will curse [that is, subject to My wrath and judgment] the one who curses
        (despises, dishonors, has contempt for) you.And in you all the families (nations)
        of the earth will be blessed.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'So Abram departed [in faithful obedience] as the Lord had directed
        him; and Lot [his nephew] left with him. Abram was seventy-five years old
        when he left Haran. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Abram took Sarai his wife and Lot his nephew, and all their possessions
        which they had acquired, and the people (servants) which they had acquired
        in Haran, and they set out to go to the land of Canaan. When they came to
        the land of Canaan, '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Abram passed through the land as far as the site of Shechem, to the
        [great] terebinth (oak) tree of Moreh. Now the Canaanites were in the land
        at that time. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Then the Lord appeared to Abram and said, \u201CI will give this
        land to your descendants.\u201D So Abram built an altar there to [honor]
        the Lord who had appeared to him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Then he moved on from there to the mountain on the east of Bethel,
        and pitched his tent, with Bethel on the west and Ai on the east; and there
        he built an altar to the Lord and called on the name of the Lord [in worship
        through prayer, praise, and thanksgiving]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Then Abram journeyed on, continuing toward the Negev (the South country
        of Judah).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Now there was a famine in the land; and Abram went down into Egypt
        to live temporarily, for the famine in the land was oppressive and severe. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And when he was about to enter Egypt, he said to Sarai his wife,
        \u201CListen: I know that you are a beautiful woman; "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "so when the Egyptians see you, they will say, \u2018This is his wife\u2019;
        and they will kill me [to acquire you], but they will let you live. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Please tell them that you are my sister so that things will go well
        for me for your sake, and my life will be spared because of you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And when Abram entered Egypt, the Egyptians saw that Sarai was very
        beautiful. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Pharaoh\u2019s princes (officials) also saw her and praised her to
        Pharaoh; and the woman was taken [for the purpose of marriage] into Pharaoh\u2019s
        house (harem). "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Therefore Pharaoh treated Abram well for her sake; he acquired sheep,
        oxen, male and female donkeys, male and female servants, and camels.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "But the Lord punished Pharaoh and his household with severe plagues
        because of Sarai, Abram\u2019s wife. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Then Pharaoh called Abram and said, \u201CWhat is this that you have
        done to me? Why did you not tell me that she was your wife? "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Why did you say, \u2018She is my sister,\u2019 so that I took her
        as my wife? Now then, here is your wife; take her and go!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: So Pharaoh commanded his men concerning him; and they escorted him
        on his way, with his wife and all that he had.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Abram and Lot'
      title: Abram and Lot
      number: 1
      content: '  So Abram went up out of Egypt, he and his wife and all that he
        had, and Lot [his nephew] with him, into the Negev (the South country of
        Judah).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Now Abram was extremely rich in livestock and in silver and in gold. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'He journeyed on from the Negev as far as Bethel, to the place where
        his tent had been at the beginning, between Bethel and Ai, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'where he had first built an altar; and there Abram called on the
        name of the Lord [in prayer]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'But Lot, who went with Abram, also had flocks and herds and tents. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Now the land was not able to support them [that is, sustain all their
        grazing and water needs] while they lived near one another, for their possessions
        were too great for them to stay together. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And there was strife and quarreling between the herdsmen of Abram\u2019s
        cattle and the herdsmen of Lot\u2019s cattle. Now the Canaanite and the Perizzite
        were living in the land at that same time [making grazing of the livestock
        difficult].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "So Abram said to Lot, \u201CPlease let there be no strife and disagreement
        between you and me, nor between your herdsmen and my herdsmen, because we
        are relatives. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Is not the entire land before you? Please separate [yourself] from
        me. If you take the left, then I will go to the right; or if you choose the
        right, then I will go to the left.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "So Lot looked and saw that the valley of the Jordan was well watered
        everywhere\u2014this was before the Lord destroyed Sodom and Gomorrah; [it
        was all] like the garden of the Lord, like the land of Egypt, as you go to
        Zoar [at the south end of the Dead Sea]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Then Lot chose for himself all the valley of the Jordan, and he traveled
        east. So they separated from each other. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Abram settled in the land of Canaan, and Lot settled in the cities
        of the valley and camped as far as Sodom and lived there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'But the men of Sodom were extremely wicked and sinful against the
        Lord [unashamed in their open sin before Him].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "The Lord said to Abram, after Lot had left him, \u201CNow lift up
        your eyes and look from the place where you are standing, northward and southward
        and eastward and westward; "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'for all the land which you see I will give to you and to your descendants
        forever. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'I will make your descendants [as numerous] as the dust of the earth,
        so that if a man could count the [grains of] dust of the earth, then your
        descendants could also be counted. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Arise, walk (make a thorough reconnaissance) around in the land,
        through its length and its width, for I will give it to you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: Then Abram broke camp and moved his tent, and came and settled by
        the [grove of the great] terebinths (oak trees) of Mamre [the Amorite], which
        are in Hebron, and there he built an altar to [honor] the Lord.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: War of the Kings'
      title: War of the Kings
      number: 1
      content: '  In the days of the [Eastern] kings Amraphel of Shinar, Arioch of
        Ellasar, Chedorlaomer of Elam, and Tidal of Goiim, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'they [invaded the Jordan Valley near the Dead Sea, and] made war
        with Bera king of Sodom, Birsha king of Gomorrah, Shinab king of Admah, Shemeber
        king of Zeboiim, and the king of Bela (that is, Zoar). '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'All of these [kings] joined together [as allies] in the Valley of
        Siddim (that is, the Sea of Salt). '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Twelve years they had served Chedorlaomer [the most powerful king
        in the invading confederacy], but in the thirteenth year they rebelled. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'In the fourteenth year Chedorlaomer and the [three] kings who were
        with him attacked and subdued the Rephaim in Ashteroth-karnaim, the Zuzim
        in Ham, and the Emim in Shaveh-kiriathaim, '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'and the Horites in their mountainous country of Seir, as far as El-paran,
        which is on the border of the wilderness. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Then they turned back and came to En-mishpat (that is, Kadesh), and
        subdued all the country of the Amalekites, and also the Amorites who lived
        in Hazazon-tamar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Then the kings of Sodom, Gomorrah, Admah, Zeboiim, and Bela (that
        is, Zoar) came out; and they joined together for battle with the invading
        kings in the Valley of Siddim, '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "against Chedorlaomer king of Elam and Tidal king of Goiim and Amraphel
        king of Shinar and Arioch king of Ellasar\u2014four kings against five. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Now the Valley of Siddim was full of tar (bitumen) pits; and as the
        kings of Sodom and Gomorrah fled, they fell into them. But the remainder
        [of the kings] who survived fled to the hill country. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Then the victors took all the possessions of Sodom and Gomorrah and
        all their food supply and provisions and left. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And they also took [captive] Lot, Abram\u2019s nephew, and his possessions
        and left, for he was living in Sodom.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Then a survivor who had escaped [from the invading forces on the
        other side of the Jordan] came and told Abram the Hebrew. Now he was living
        by the terebinths (oaks) of Mamre the Amorite, brother of Eshcol and brother
        of Aner\u2014they were allies of Abram. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'When Abram heard that his nephew [Lot] had been captured, he armed
        and led out his trained men, born in his own house, [numbering] three hundred
        and eighteen, and went in pursuit as far [north] as Dan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'He divided his forces against them by night, he and his servants,
        and attacked and defeated them, and pursued them as far as Hobah, which is
        north of Damascus. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: Abram and Melchizedek'
      title: Abram and Melchizedek
      number: 16
      content: 'And he brought back all the goods, and also brought back his nephew
        Lot and his possessions, and also the women, and the people.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Then after Abram\u2019s return from the defeat (slaughter) of Chedorlaomer
        and the kings who were with him, the king of Sodom went out to meet him at
        the Valley of Shaveh (that is, the King\u2019s Valley). "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Melchizedek king of Salem (ancient Jerusalem) brought out bread and
        wine [for them]; he was the priest of God Most High. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "And Melchizedek blessed Abram and said,\u201CBlessed (joyful, favored)
        be Abram by God Most High,Creator and Possessor of heaven and earth;  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "And blessed, praised, and glorified be God Most High,Who has given
        your enemies into your hand.\u201DAnd Abram gave him a tenth of all [the
        treasure he had taken in battle]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "The king of Sodom said to Abram, \u201CGive me the people and keep
        the goods (spoils of battle) for yourself.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "But Abram said to the king of Sodom, \u201CI have raised my hand
        and sworn an oath to the Lord God Most High, the Creator and Possessor of
        heaven and earth, "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "that I would not take anything that is yours, from a thread to a
        sandal strap, so you could not say, \u2018I [the King of Sodom] have made
        Abram rich.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "I will take nothing except what my young men have eaten, and the
        share of the spoils belonging to the men [my allies] who went with me\u2014Aner,
        Eshcol, and Mamre; let them take their share of the spoils.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Abram Promised a Son'
      title: Abram Promised a Son
      number: 1
      content: "  After these things the word of the Lord came to Abram in a vision,
        saying,\u201CDo not be afraid, Abram,I am your shield;Your reward [for obedience]
        shall be very great.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Abram said, \u201CLord God, what reward will You give me, since I
        am [leaving this world] childless, and he who will be the owner and heir
        of my house is this [servant] Eliezer from Damascus?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And Abram continued, \u201CSince You have given no child to me, one
        (a servant) born in my house is my heir.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Then behold, the word of the Lord came to him, saying, \u201CThis
        man [Eliezer] will not be your heir but he who shall come from your own body
        shall be your heir.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And the Lord brought Abram outside [his tent into the night] and
        said, \u201CLook now toward the heavens and count the stars\u2014if you are
        able to count them.\u201D Then He said to him, \u201CSo [numerous] shall
        your descendants be.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Then Abram believed in (affirmed, trusted in, relied on, remained
        steadfast to) the Lord; and He counted (credited) it to him as righteousness
        (doing right in regard to God and man). '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And He said to him, \u201CI am the [same] Lord who brought you out
        of Ur of the Chaldeans, to give you this land as an inheritance.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "But Abram said, \u201CLord God, by what [proof] will I know that
        I will inherit it?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "So God said to him, \u201CBring Me a three-year-old heifer, a three-year-old
        female goat, a three-year-old ram, a turtledove, and a young pigeon.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'So Abram brought all these to Him and cut them down the middle, and
        laid each half opposite the other; but he did not cut the birds. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'The birds of prey swooped down on the carcasses, but Abram drove
        them away.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'When the sun was setting, a deep sleep overcame Abram; and a horror
        (terror, shuddering fear, nightmare) of great darkness overcame him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "God said to Abram, \u201CKnow for sure that your descendants will
        be strangers [living temporarily] in a land (Egypt) that is not theirs, where
        they will be enslaved and oppressed for four hundred years. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'But on that nation whom your descendants will serve I will bring
        judgment, and afterward they will come out [of that land] with great possessions. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'As for you, you shall [die and] go to your fathers in peace; you
        shall be buried at a good old age. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Then in the fourth generation your descendants shall return here
        [to Canaan, the land of promise], for the wickedness and guilt of the Amorites
        is not yet complete (finished).\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'When the sun had gone down and a [deep] darkness had come, there
        appeared a smoking brazier and a flaming torch which passed between the [divided]
        pieces [of the animals]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "On the same day the Lord made a covenant (promise, pledge) with Abram,
        saying,\u201CTo your descendants I have given this land,From the river of
        Egypt to the great river Euphrates\u2014  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: '[the land of] the Kenites and the Kenizzites and the Kadmonites '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'and the Hittites and the Perizzites and the Rephaim, '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "the Amorites and the Canaanites and the Girgashites and the Jebusites.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Sarai and Hagar'
      title: Sarai and Hagar
      number: 1
      content: "  Now Sarai, Abram\u2019s wife, had not borne him any children, and
        she had an Egyptian maid whose name was Hagar. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "So Sarai said to Abram, \u201CSee here, the Lord has prevented me
        from bearing children. I am asking you to go in to [the bed of] my maid [so
        that she may bear you a child]; perhaps I will obtain children by her.\u201D
        And Abram listened to Sarai and did as she said. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "After Abram had lived in the land of Canaan ten years, Abram\u2019s
        wife Sarai took Hagar the Egyptian [maid], and gave her to her husband Abram
        to be his [secondary] wife. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'He went in to [the bed of] Hagar, and she conceived; and when she
        realized that she had conceived, she looked with contempt on her mistress
        [regarding Sarai as insignificant because of her infertility]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then Sarai said to Abram, \u201CMay [the responsibility for] the
        wrong done to me [by the arrogant behavior of Hagar] be upon you. I gave
        my maid into your arms, and when she realized that she had conceived, I was
        despised and looked on with disrespect. May the Lord judge [who has done
        right] between you and me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "But Abram said to Sarai, \u201CLook, your maid is entirely in your
        hands and subject to your authority; do as you please with her.\u201D So
        Sarai treated her harshly and humiliated her, and Hagar fled from her.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'But the Angel of the Lord found her by a spring of water in the wilderness,
        on the road to [Egypt by way of] Shur. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And He said, \u201CHagar, Sarai\u2019s maid, where did you come from
        and where are you going?\u201D And she said, \u201CI am running away from
        my mistress Sarai.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "The Angel of the Lord said to her, \u201CGo back to your mistress,
        and submit humbly to her authority.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Then the Angel of the Lord said to her, \u201CI will greatly multiply
        your descendants so that they will be too many to count.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "The Angel of the Lord continued,\u201CBehold, you are with child,And
        you will bear a son;And you shall name him Ishmael (God hears),Because the
        Lord has heard and paid attention to your persecution (suffering).  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "He (Ishmael) will be a wild donkey of a man;His hand will be against
        every man [continually fighting]And every man\u2019s hand against him;And
        he will dwell in defiance of all his brothers.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Then she called the name of the Lord who spoke to her, \u201CYou
        are God Who Sees\u201D; for she said, \u201CHave I not even here [in the
        wilderness] remained alive after seeing Him [who sees me with understanding
        and compassion]?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Therefore the well was called Beer-lahai-roi (Well of the Living
        One Who Sees Me); it is between Kadesh and Bered.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "So Hagar gave birth to Abram\u2019s son; and Abram named his son,
        to whom Hagar gave birth, Ishmael (God hears). "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: Abram was eighty-six years old when Hagar gave birth to Ishmael.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Abraham and the Covenant of Circumcision'
      title: Abraham and the Covenant of Circumcision
      number: 1
      content: "  When Abram was ninety-nine years old, the Lord appeared to him
        and said,\u201CI am God Almighty;Walk [habitually] before Me [with integrity,
        knowing that you are always in My presence], and be blameless and complete
        [in obedience to Me].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "I will establish My covenant (everlasting promise) between Me and
        you,And I will multiply you exceedingly [through your descendants].\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Then Abram fell on his face [in worship], and God spoke with him,
        saying,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CAs for Me, behold, My covenant is with you,And [as a result]
        you shall be the father of many nations.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'No longer shall your name be Abram (exalted father),But your name
        shall be Abraham (father of a multitude);For I will make you the father of
        many nations.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'I will make you exceedingly fruitful, and I will make nations of
        you, and kings will come from you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'I will establish My covenant between Me and you and your descendants
        after you throughout their generations for an everlasting covenant, to be
        God to you and to your descendants after you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "I will give to you and to your descendants after you the land in
        which you are a stranger [moving from place to place], all the land of Canaan,
        as an everlasting possession [of property]; and I will be their God.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Further, God said to Abraham, \u201CAs for you [your part of the
        agreement], you shall keep and faithfully obey [the terms of] My covenant,
        you and your descendants after you throughout their generations. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'This is [the sign of] My covenant, which you shall keep and faithfully
        obey, between Me and you and your descendants after you: Every male among
        you shall be circumcised. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And you shall be circumcised in the flesh of your foreskins, and
        it shall be the sign (symbol, memorial) of the covenant between Me and you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Every male among you who is eight days old shall be circumcised throughout
        your generations, [including] a servant whether born in the house or one
        who is purchased with [your] money from any foreigner, who is not of your
        descendants. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'A servant who is born in your house or one who is purchased with
        your money must be circumcised; and [the sign of] My covenant shall be in
        your flesh for an everlasting covenant. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "And the male who is not circumcised in the flesh of his foreskin,
        that person shall be cut off from his people; he has broken My covenant.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Then God said to Abraham, \u201CAs for Sarai your wife, you shall
        not call her name Sarai (my princess), but her name will be Sarah (Princess). "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "I will bless her, and indeed I will also give you a son by her. Yes,
        I will bless her, and she shall be a mother of nations; kings of peoples
        will come from her.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Then Abraham fell on his face and laughed, and said in his heart,
        \u201CShall a child be born to a man who is a hundred years old? And shall
        Sarah, who is ninety years old, bear a child?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "And Abraham said to God, \u201COh, that Ishmael [my firstborn] might
        live before You!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "But God said, \u201CNo, Sarah your wife shall bear you a son indeed,
        and you shall name him Isaac (laughter); and I will establish My covenant
        with him for an everlasting covenant and with his descendants after him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'As for Ishmael, I have heard and listened to you; behold, I will
        bless him, and will make him fruitful and will greatly multiply him [through
        his descendants]. He will be the father of twelve princes (chieftains, sheiks),
        and I will make him a great nation. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "But My covenant [My promise, My solemn pledge], I will establish
        with Isaac, whom Sarah will bear to you at this time next year.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'And God finished speaking with him and went up from Abraham.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Then Abraham took Ishmael his son, and all the servants who were
        born in his house and all who were purchased with his money, every male among
        the men of Abraham\u2019s household, and circumcised the flesh of their foreskin
        the very same day, as God had said to him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'So Abraham was ninety-nine years old when he was circumcised. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'And Ishmael his son was thirteen years old when he was circumcised. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'On the very same day Abraham was circumcised, as well as Ishmael
        his son. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "All the men [servants] of his household, both those born in the house
        and those purchased with money from a foreigner, were circumcised along with
        him [as the sign of God\u2019s covenant with Abraham]."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Birth of Isaac Promised'
      title: Birth of Isaac Promised
      number: 1
      content: '  Now the Lord appeared to Abraham by the terebinth trees of Mamre
        [in Hebron], while he was sitting at the tent door in the heat of the day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'When he raised his eyes and looked up, behold, three men were standing
        [a little distance] from him. When he saw them, he ran from the tent door
        to meet them and bowed down [with his face] to the ground, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "and Abraham said, \u201CMy lord, if now I have found favor in your
        sight, please do not pass by your servant [without stopping to visit]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Please let a little water be brought [by one of my servants] and
        [you may] wash your feet, and recline and rest comfortably under the tree. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And I will bring a piece of bread to refresh and sustain you; after
        that you may go on, since you have come to your servant.\u201D And they replied,
        \u201CDo as you have said.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "So Abraham hurried into the tent to Sarah, and said, \u201CQuickly,
        get ready three measures of fine meal, knead it and bake cakes.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Abraham also ran to the herd and brought a calf, tender and choice,
        and he gave it to the servant [to butcher], and he hurried to prepare it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Then he took curds and milk and the calf which he had prepared, and
        set it before the men; and he stood beside them under the tree while they
        ate.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Then they said to him, \u201CWhere is Sarah your wife?\u201D And
        he said, \u201CThere, in the tent.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "He said, \u201CI will surely return to you at this time next year;
        and behold, Sarah your wife will have a son.\u201D And Sarah was listening
        at the tent door, which was behind him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Now Abraham and Sarah were old, well advanced in years; she was past
        [the age of] childbearing. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "So Sarah laughed to herself [when she heard the Lord\u2019s words],
        saying, \u201CAfter I have become old, shall I have pleasure and delight,
        my lord (husband) being also old?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And the Lord asked Abraham, \u201CWhy did Sarah laugh [to herself],
        saying, \u2018Shall I really give birth [to a child] when I am so old?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Is anything too difficult or too wonderful for the Lord? At the appointed
        time, when the season [for her delivery] comes, I will return to you and
        Sarah will have a son.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Then Sarah denied it, saying, \u201CI did not laugh\u201D; because
        she was afraid. And He (the Lord) said, \u201CNo, but you did laugh.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Then the men got up from there, and looked toward Sodom; and Abraham
        walked with them to send them on the way. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "The Lord said, \u201CShall I keep secret from Abraham [My friend
        and servant] what I am going to do, "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'since Abraham is destined to become a great and mighty nation, and
        all the nations of the earth will be blessed through him? '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "For I have known (chosen, acknowledged) him [as My own], so that
        he may teach and command his children and [the sons of] his household after
        him to keep the way of the Lord by doing what is righteous and just, so that
        the Lord may bring upon Abraham what He has promised him.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "And the Lord said, \u201CThe outcry [of the sin] of Sodom and Gomorrah
        is indeed great, and their sin is exceedingly grave. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "I will go down now, and see whether they have acted [as vilely and
        wickedly] as the outcry which has come to Me [indicates]; and if not, I will
        know.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Now the [two] men (angelic beings) turned away from there and went
        toward Sodom, but Abraham remained standing before the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Abraham approached [the Lord] and said, \u201CWill You really sweep
        away the righteous (those who do right) with the wicked (those who do evil)? "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Suppose there are fifty righteous [people] within the city; will
        You really sweep it away and not spare it for the sake of the fifty righteous
        who are in it? '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Far be it from You to do such a thing\u2014to strike the righteous
        with the wicked, so that the righteous and the wicked are treated alike.
        Far be it from You! Shall not the Judge of all the earth do right [by executing
        just and righteous judgment]?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "So the Lord said, \u201CIf I find within the city of Sodom fifty
        righteous [people], then I will spare the entire place for their sake.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Abraham answered, \u201CNow behold, I who am but dust [in origin]
        and ashes have decided to speak to the Lord. "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "If five of the fifty righteous are lacking, will You destroy the
        entire city for lack of five?\u201D And He said, \u201CIf I find [at least]
        forty-five [righteous people] there, I will not destroy it.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Abraham spoke to Him yet again and said, \u201CSuppose [only] forty
        are found there.\u201D And He said, \u201CI will not do it for the sake of
        the forty [who are righteous].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "Then Abraham said [to Him], \u201COh, may the Lord not be angry,
        and I will speak; suppose thirty [righteous people] are found there?\u201D
        And He said, \u201CI will not do it if I find thirty there.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "And he said, \u201CNow behold, I have decided to speak to the Lord
        [again]. Suppose [only] twenty [righteous people] are found there?\u201D
        And the Lord said, \u201CI will not destroy it for the sake of the twenty.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "Then Abraham said, \u201COh may the Lord not be angry [with me],
        and I will speak only this once; suppose ten [righteous people] are found
        there?\u201D And He said, \u201CI will not destroy it for the sake of the
        ten.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: As soon as He had finished speaking with Abraham the Lord departed,
        and Abraham returned to his own place.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Doom of Sodom'
      title: The Doom of Sodom
      number: 1
      content: "  It was evening when the two angels came to Sodom. Lot was sitting
        at Sodom\u2019s [city] gate. Seeing them, Lot got up to meet them and bowed
        down with his face to the ground. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And he said, \u201CSee here, my lords, please turn aside and come
        into your servant\u2019s house, and spend the night, and wash your feet;
        then you may get up early and go on your way.\u201D But they said, \u201CNo,
        we shall spend the night in the open plaza [of the city].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'However, Lot strongly urged them, so they turned aside and entered
        his house; and he prepared a feast for them [with wine], and baked unleavened
        bread, and they ate. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'But before they lay down [to sleep], the men of the city, the men
        of Sodom, both young and old, surrounded the house, all the men from every
        quarter; '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "and they called out to Lot and said to him, \u201CWhere are the men
        who came to you tonight? Bring them out to us so that we may know them [intimately].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'But Lot went out of the doorway to the men, and shut the door after
        him, '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "and said, \u201CPlease, my brothers, do not do something so wicked. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "See here, I have two daughters who have not known a man [intimately];
        please let me bring them out to you [instead], and you can do as you please
        with them; only do nothing to these men, because they have in fact come under
        the shelter of my roof [for protection].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "But they said, \u201CGet out of the way!\u201D And they said, \u201CThis
        man (Lot) came [as an outsider] to live here temporarily, and now he is acting
        like a judge. Now we will treat you worse than your visitors!\u201D So they
        rushed forward and pressed violently against Lot and came close to breaking
        down the door [of his house]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'But the men (angels) reached out with their hands and pulled Lot
        into the house with them, and shut the door [after him]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'They struck (punished) the men who were at the doorway of the house
        with blindness, from the young men to the old men, so that they exhausted
        themselves trying to find the doorway.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And the [two] men (angels) asked Lot, \u201CHave you any others here
        [in Sodom]\u2014a son-in-law, and your sons, and your daughters? Whomever
        you have in the city, take them out of here; "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "for we are destroying this place, because the outcry [for judgment]
        against them has grown so great before the Lord that the Lord has sent us
        to destroy and ruin it.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "So Lot went out and spoke to his sons-in-law, who were [betrothed,
        and legally promised] to marry his daughters, and said, \u201CGet up, get
        out of this place, for the Lord is about to destroy this city!\u201D But
        to his sons-in-law he appeared to be joking.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "When morning dawned, the angels urged Lot [to hurry], saying, \u201CGet
        up! Take your wife and two daughters who are here [and go], or you will be
        swept away in the punishment of the city.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "But Lot hesitated and lingered. The men took hold of his hand and
        the hand of his wife and the hands of his two daughters, because the Lord
        was merciful to him [for Abraham\u2019s sake]; and they brought him out,
        and left him outside the city [with his family]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "When they had brought them outside, one [of the angels] said, \u201CEscape
        for your life! Do not look behind you, or stop anywhere in the entire valley;
        escape to the mountains [of Moab], or you will be consumed and swept away.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "But Lot said to them, \u201COh no, [not that place] my lords! "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Please listen, your servant has found favor in your sight, and you
        have magnified your lovingkindness (mercy) to me by saving my life; but I
        cannot escape to the mountains, because the disaster will overtake me and
        I will be killed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Now look, this town [in the distance] is near enough for us to flee
        to, and it is small [with only a few people]. Please, let me escape there
        (is it not small?) so that my life will be saved.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "And the angel said to him, \u201CBehold, I grant you this request
        also; I will not destroy this town of which you have spoken. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Hurry and take refuge there, for I cannot do anything [to punish
        Sodom] until you arrive there.\u201D For this reason the town was named Zoar
        (few, small).  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'The sun had risen over the earth when Lot came to Zoar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Then the Lord rained down brimstone (flaming sulfur) and fire on
        Sodom and on Gomorrah from the Lord out of heaven, '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'and He overthrew (demolished, ended) those cities, and the entire
        valley, and all the inhabitants of the cities, and whatever grew on the ground. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "But Lot\u2019s wife, from behind him, [foolishly, longingly] looked
        [back toward Sodom in an act of disobedience], and she became a pillar of
        salt.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Abraham started out early the next morning to the place where he
        [only the day before] had stood before the Lord; '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'and he looked down toward Sodom and Gomorrah, and toward all the
        land of the valley [of the Dead Sea]; and he saw, and behold, the smoke of
        the land went up like the smoke of a kiln (pottery furnace).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: Lot Is Debased'
      title: Lot Is Debased
      number: 29
      content: "Now when God ravaged and destroyed the cities of the plain [of Siddim],
        He remembered Abraham [and for that reason], and He sent [Abraham\u2019s
        nephew] Lot out of the midst of the destruction, when He destroyed the cities
        in which Lot had lived.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Now Lot went up from Zoar, and lived in the mountain together with
        his two daughters, for he was afraid to stay [any longer] in Zoar; and he
        lived in a cave with his two daughters. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "The firstborn said to the younger, \u201COur father is aging, and
        there is not a man on earth [available] to be intimate with us in the customary
        way [so that we may have children]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "Come, let us make our father drunk with wine, and we will lie with
        him so that we may preserve our family through our father.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'So they gave their father wine that night, and the firstborn went
        in and lay with her father; and he did not know when she lay down or when
        she got up [because he was completely intoxicated]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "Then the next day, the firstborn said to the younger, \u201CBehold,
        I lay with my father last night; let us make him drunk with wine tonight
        also, and then you go in and lie with him, so that we may preserve our family
        through our father.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'So they gave their father wine that night also, and the younger got
        up and lay with him; and again he did not know when she lay down or when
        she got up. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'Thus both the daughters of Lot conceived by their father. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'The firstborn gave birth to a son, and named him Moab (from father);
        he is the father of the Moabites to this day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: The younger also gave birth to a son and named him Ben-ammi (son of
        my people); he is the father of the Ammonites to this day.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Abraham\u2019s Deception"
      title: "Abraham\u2019s Deception"
      number: 1
      content: '  Now Abraham journeyed from there toward the Negev (the South country),
        and settled between Kadesh and Shur; then he lived temporarily in Gerar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Abraham said [again] of Sarah his wife, \u201CShe is my sister.\u201D
        So Abimelech king of Gerar sent and took Sarah [into his harem]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "But God came to Abimelech in a dream during the night, and said,
        \u201CBehold, you are a dead man because of the woman whom you have taken
        [as your wife], for she is another man\u2019s wife.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Now Abimelech had not yet come near her; so he said, \u201CLord,
        will you kill a people who are righteous and innocent and blameless [regarding
        Sarah]? "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Did Abraham not tell me, \u2018She is my sister?\u2019 And she herself
        said, \u2018He is my brother.\u2019 In the integrity of my heart and innocence
        of my hands I have done this.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Then God said to him in the dream, \u201CYes, I know you did this
        in the integrity of your heart, for it was I who kept you back and spared
        you from sinning against Me; therefore I did not give you an opportunity
        to touch her. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "So now return the man\u2019s wife, for he is a prophet, and he will
        pray for you and you will live. But if you do not return her [to him], know
        that you shall die, you and all who are yours (your household).\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'So Abimelech got up early in the morning and called all his servants
        and told them all these things; and the men were terrified. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Then Abimelech called Abraham and said to him, \u201CWhat have you
        done to us? And how have I offended you that you have brought on me and my
        kingdom a great sin? You have done to me what ought not to be done [to anyone].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And Abimelech said to Abraham, \u201CWhat have you encountered or
        seen [in us or our customs], that you have done this [unjust] thing?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Abraham said, \u201CBecause I thought, \u2018Surely there is no fear
        or reverence of God in this place, and they will kill me because of my wife.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Besides, she actually is my [half] sister; she is the daughter of
        my father [Terah], but not of my mother; and she became my wife. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "When God caused me to wander from my father\u2019s house, I said
        to her, \u2018This kindness and loyalty you can show me: at every place we
        stop, say of me, \u201CHe is my brother.\u201D\u2009\u2019\u2009\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Then Abimelech took sheep and oxen and male and female slaves, and
        gave them to Abraham, and returned Sarah his wife to him [as God commanded]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "So Abimelech said, \u201CBehold, my land is before you; settle wherever
        you please.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Then to Sarah he said, \u201CLook, I have given this brother of yours
        a thousand pieces of silver; it is to compensate you [for all that has happened]
        and to vindicate your honor before all who are with you; before all men you
        are cleared and compensated.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'So Abraham prayed to God, and God healed Abimelech and his wife and
        his maids, and they again gave birth to children,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "for the Lord had securely closed the wombs of all [the women] in
        Abimelech\u2019s household because of Sarah, Abraham\u2019s wife."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Isaac Is Born'
      title: Isaac Is Born
      number: 1
      content: '  The Lord graciously remembered and visited Sarah as He had said,
        and the Lord did for her as He had promised. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'So Sarah conceived and gave birth to a son for Abraham in his old
        age, at the appointed time of which God had spoken to him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Abraham named his son Isaac (laughter), the son to whom Sarah gave
        birth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'So Abraham circumcised his son Isaac when he was eight days old,
        just as God had commanded him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Abraham was a hundred years old when his son Isaac was born. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Sarah said, \u201CGod has made me laugh; all who hear [about our
        good news] will laugh with me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And she said, \u201CWho would have said to Abraham that Sarah would
        nurse children? For I have given birth to a son by him in his old age.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: Sarah Turns against Hagar'
      title: Sarah Turns against Hagar
      number: 8
      content: 'The child [Isaac] grew and was weaned, and Abraham held a great feast
        on the day that Isaac was weaned.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Now [as time went on] Sarah saw [Ishmael] the son of Hagar the Egyptian,
        whom she had borne to Abraham, mocking [Isaac]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Therefore she said to Abraham, \u201CDrive out this maid and her
        son, for the son of this maid shall not be an heir with my son Isaac.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'The situation distressed Abraham greatly because of his son [Ishmael]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "God said to Abraham, \u201CDo not let it distress you because of
        Ishmael and your maid; whatever Sarah tells you, listen to her and do what
        she asks, for your descendants will be named through Isaac. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And I will also make a nation of [Ishmael] the son of the maid, because
        he is your descendant.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'So Abraham got up early in the morning and took bread and a skin
        of water and gave them to Hagar, putting them on her shoulder, and gave her
        the boy, and sent her away. And she left [but lost her way] and wandered
        [aimlessly] in the Wilderness of Beersheba.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'When the water in the skin was all gone, Hagar abandoned the boy
        under one of the bushes. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Then she went and sat down opposite him, about a bowshot away, for
        she said, \u201CDo not let me see the boy die.\u201D And as she sat down
        opposite him, she raised her voice and wept. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "God heard the voice of the boy, and the angel of God called to Hagar
        from heaven and said to her, \u201CWhat troubles you, Hagar? Do not be afraid,
        for God has heard the voice of the boy from where he is [resting]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Get up, help the boy up, and hold him by the hand, for I will make
        him a great nation.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Then God opened her eyes and she saw a well of water; and she went
        and filled the [empty] skin with water and gave the boy a drink.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'God was with Ishmael, and he grew and developed; and he lived in
        the wilderness and became an [expert] archer. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: Covenant with Abimelech'
      title: Covenant with Abimelech
      number: 21
      content: 'He lived in the wilderness of Paran; and his mother took a wife for
        him from the land of Egypt.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Now at that time Abimelech and Phicol, the commander of his army,
        said to Abraham, \u201CGod is with you in everything you do; "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "so now, swear to me here by God that you will not deal unfairly with
        me [by breaking any agreements we have] or with my son or with my descendants,
        but as I have treated you with kindness, you shall do the same to me and
        to the land in which you have sojourned (temporarily lived).\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "And Abraham said, \u201CI will swear.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Then Abraham complained to Abimelech about a well of water which
        the servants of Abimelech had [violently] seized [from him], '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Abimelech said, \u201CI do not know who did this thing. Indeed, you
        did not tell me, and I did not hear of it until today.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'So Abraham took sheep and oxen and gave them to Abimelech, and the
        two men made a covenant (binding agreement). '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Then Abraham set apart seven ewe lambs of the flock, '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "and Abimelech said to Abraham, \u201CWhat is the meaning of these
        seven ewe lambs which you have set apart?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "Abraham said, \u201CYou are to accept these seven ewe lambs from
        me as a witness for me, that I dug this well.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Therefore that place was called Beersheba (Well of the Oath or Well
        of the Seven), because there the two of them swore an oath. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'So they made a covenant at Beersheba; then Abimelech and Phicol,
        the commander of his army, got up and returned to the land of the Philistines. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'Abraham planted a tamarisk tree at Beersheba, and there he called
        on the name of the Lord [in prayer], the Eternal God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: And Abraham lived [as a resident alien] in the land of the Philistines
        for many days.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Offering of Isaac'
      title: The Offering of Isaac
      number: 1
      content: "  Now after these things, God tested [the faith and commitment of]
        Abraham and said to him, \u201CAbraham!\u201D And he answered, \u201CHere
        I am.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "God said, \u201CTake now your son, your only son [of promise], whom
        you love, Isaac, and go to the region of Moriah, and offer him there as a
        burnt offering on one of the mountains of which I shall tell you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'So Abraham got up early in the morning, saddled his donkey, and took
        two of his young men with him and his son Isaac; and he split the wood for
        the burnt offering, and then he got up and went to the place of which God
        had told him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'On the third day [of travel] Abraham looked up and saw the place
        in the distance. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Abraham said to his servants, \u201CSettle down and stay here with
        the donkey; the young man and I will go over there and worship [God], and
        we will come back to you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Then Abraham took the wood for the burnt offering and laid it on
        [the shoulders of] Isaac his son, and he took the fire (firepot) in his own
        hand and the [sacrificial] knife; and the two of them walked on together. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And Isaac said to Abraham, \u201CMy father!\u201D And he said, \u201CHere
        I am, my son.\u201D Isaac said, \u201CLook, the fire and the wood, but where
        is the lamb for the burnt offering?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Abraham said, \u201CMy son, God will provide for Himself a lamb for
        the burnt offering.\u201D So the two walked on together.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'When they came to the place of which God had told him, Abraham built
        an altar there and arranged the wood, and bound Isaac his son and placed
        him on the altar, on top of the wood. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Abraham reached out his hand and took the knife to kill his son. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "But the Angel of the Lord called to him from heaven and said, \u201CAbraham,
        Abraham!\u201D He answered, \u201CHere I am.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "The Lord said, \u201CDo not reach out [with the knife in] your hand
        against the boy, and do nothing to [harm] him; for now I know that you fear
        God [with reverence and profound respect], since you have not withheld from
        Me your son, your only son [of promise].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Then Abraham looked up and glanced around, and behold, behind him
        was a ram caught in a thicket by his horns. And Abraham went and took the
        ram and offered it up for a burnt offering (ascending sacrifice) instead
        of his son. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "So Abraham named that place The Lord Will Provide. And it is said
        to this day, \u201COn the mountain of the Lord it will be seen and provided.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'The Angel of the Lord called to Abraham from heaven a second time '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "and said, \u201CBy Myself (on the basis of Who I Am) I have sworn
        [an oath], declares the Lord, that since you have done this thing and have
        not withheld [from Me] your son, your only son [of promise], "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'indeed I will greatly bless you, and I will greatly multiply your
        seed like the stars of the heavens and like the sand on the seashore; and
        your seed shall possess the gate of their enemies [by conquering them]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Through your seed all the nations of the earth shall be blessed,
        because you have heard and obeyed My voice.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'So Abraham returned to his servants, and they got up and went with
        him to Beersheba; and Abraham settled in Beersheba.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Now after these things Abraham was told, \u201CMilcah has borne children
        to your brother Nahor: "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Uz the firstborn and Buz his brother and Kemuel the father of Aram, '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Chesed and Hazo and Pildash and Jidlaph and Bethuel.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Bethuel became the father of Rebekah. These eight [children] Milcah
        bore to Nahor, Abraham\u2019s brother. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Nahor\u2019s concubine, whose name was Reumah, gave birth to Tebah
        and Gaham and Tahash and Maacah."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Death and Burial of Sarah'
      title: Death and Burial of Sarah
      number: 1
      content: '  Sarah lived a hundred and twenty-seven years; this was the length
        of the life of Sarah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Sarah died in Kiriath-arba (that is, Hebron) in the land of Canaan,
        and Abraham went to mourn for Sarah and to weep for her. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Then Abraham stood up before his dead [wife\u2019s body], and spoke
        to the sons of Heth (Hittites), saying, "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CI am a stranger and a sojourner (resident alien) among you;
        give (sell) me property for a burial place among you so that I may bury my
        dead [in the proper manner].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'The Hittites replied to Abraham, '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CListen to us, my lord; you are a prince of God [a mighty prince]
        among us; bury your dead in the choicest of our graves; none of us will refuse
        you his grave or hinder you from burying your dead [wife].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'So Abraham stood up and bowed to the people of the land, the Hittites. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And Abraham said to them, \u201CIf you are willing to grant my dead
        a [proper] burial, listen to me, and plead with Ephron the son of Zohar for
        me, "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "so that he may give (sell) me the cave of Machpelah which he owns\u2014it
        is at the end of his field; let him give it to me here in your presence for
        the full price as a burial site [which I may keep forever among you].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Now Ephron was present there among the sons of Heth; so within the
        hearing of all the sons of Heth and all who were entering the gate of his
        city, Ephron the Hittite answered Abraham, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CNo, my lord, hear me; I give you the [entire] field, and I
        also give you the cave that is in it. In the presence of the men of my people
        I give (sell) it to you; bury your dead [there].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Then Abraham bowed down before the people of the land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "He said to Ephron in the presence of the people of the land, \u201CIf
        you will only please listen to me and accept my offer. I will give you the
        price of the field; accept it from me and I will bury my dead there.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Ephron replied to Abraham, '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u201CMy lord, listen to me. The land [you seek] is worth four hundred
        shekels of silver; what is that between you and me? So bury your dead.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'So Abraham listened to Ephron [and agreed to his terms]; and he weighed
        out for Ephron the [amount of] silver which he had named in the hearing of
        the Hittites: four hundred shekels of silver, according to the weights current
        among the merchants.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "So the field of Ephron in Machpelah, which was to the east of Mamre
        (Hebron)\u2014the field and the cave which was in it, and all the trees that
        were in the field and in all its borders around it\u2014were deeded over
        [legally] "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'to Abraham as his possession in the presence of the Hittites, before
        all who were entering at the gate of his city. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'After this, Abraham buried Sarah his wife in the cave of the field
        of Machpelah to the east of Mamre (that is, Hebron) in the land of Canaan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: The field and the cave in it were deeded over to Abraham by the Hittites
        as a [permanent] possession and burial place.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: A Bride for Isaac'
      title: A Bride for Isaac
      number: 1
      content: '  Now Abraham was old, [well] advanced in age; and the Lord had blessed
        Abraham in all things. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Abraham said to his servant [Eliezer of Damascus], the oldest of
        his household, who had charge over all that Abraham owned, \u201CPlease,
        put your hand under my thigh [as is customary for affirming a solemn oath], "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'and I will make you swear by the Lord, the God of heaven and the
        God of earth, that you will not take a wife for my son from the daughters
        of the Canaanites, among whom I live, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "but you will [instead] go to my [former] country (Mesopotamia) and
        to my relatives, and take a wife for my son Isaac [the heir of the covenant
        promise].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "The servant said to him, \u201CSuppose the woman will not be willing
        to follow me back to this country; should I take your son back to the country
        from which you came?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Abraham said to him, \u201CSee to it that you do not take my son
        back there! "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "The Lord, the God of heaven, who took me from my father\u2019s house,
        from the land of my family and my birth, who spoke to me and swore to me,
        saying, \u2018To your descendants I will give this land\u2019\u2014He will
        send His angel before you [to guide you], and you will take a wife from there
        for my son [and bring her here]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "If the woman is not willing to follow you [to this land], then you
        will be free from this my oath and blameless; only you must never take my
        son back there.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'So the servant put his hand under the thigh of Abraham his master,
        and swore to him concerning this matter.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Then the servant took ten of his master\u2019s camels, and set out,
        taking some of his master\u2019s good things with him; so he got up and journeyed
        to Mesopotamia [between the Tigris and the Euphrates Rivers], to the city
        of Nahor [the home of Abraham\u2019s brother]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'He made the camels kneel down outside the city by the well of water
        at the time of the evening when women go out to draw water. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And he said, \u201CO Lord, God of my master Abraham, please grant
        me success today, and show lovingkindness (faithfulness) to my master Abraham. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Behold, I stand here at the spring of water, and the daughters of
        the men of the city are coming out to draw water; '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: Rebekah Is Chosen'
      title: Rebekah Is Chosen
      number: 14
      content: "now let it be that the girl to whom I say, \u2018Please, let down
        your jar so that I may [have a] drink,\u2019 and she replies, \u2018Drink,
        and I will also give your camels water to drink\u2019\u2014may she be the
        one whom You have selected [as a wife] for Your servant Isaac; and by this
        I will know that You have shown lovingkindness (faithfulness) to my master.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Before Eliezer had finished speaking (praying), Rebekah came out
        with her [water] jar on her shoulder. Rebekah was the daughter of Bethuel
        the son of Milcah, who was the wife of Abraham\u2019s brother Nahor. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'The girl was very beautiful, a virgin and unmarried; and she went
        down to the spring and filled her jar and came up. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Then the servant ran to meet her, and said, \u201CPlease let me drink
        a little water from your jar.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "And she said, \u201CDrink, my lord\u201D; and she quickly lowered
        her jar to her hand, and gave him a drink. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "When she had given Eliezer a drink, she said, \u201CI will also draw
        water for your camels until they have finished drinking.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'So she quickly emptied her jar into the trough, and ran again to
        the well and drew water for all his camels. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Meanwhile, the man stood gazing at Rebekah in [reverent] silence,
        [waiting] to know if the Lord had made his trip successful or not.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'When the camels had finished drinking, Eliezer took a gold ring weighing
        a half-shekel and two bracelets for her hands weighing ten shekels in gold, '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "and said, \u201CWhose daughter are you? Please tell me, is there
        room in your father\u2019s house for us to lodge?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "And she said to him, \u201CI am the daughter of Bethuel, Milcah\u2019s
        son, whom she bore to [her husband] Nahor.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Again she said to him, \u201CWe have plenty of both straw and feed,
        and also room to lodge.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'The man bowed his head and worshiped the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "He said, \u201CBlessed be the Lord, the God of my master Abraham,
        who has not denied His lovingkindness and His truth to my master. As for
        me, the Lord led me to the house of my master\u2019s brothers.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Then the girl ran and told her mother\u2019s household what had happened. "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Now Rebekah had a brother whose name was Laban; and Laban ran out
        to the man at the well. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "When he saw the ring and the bracelets on his sister\u2019s arms,
        and when he heard Rebekah his sister, saying, \u201CThe man said this to
        me,\u201D he went to Eliezer and found him standing by the camels at the
        spring. "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "And Laban said, \u201CCome in, blessed of the Lord! Why do you stand
        outside since I have made the house ready and have prepared a place for the
        camels?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'So the man came into the house, and Laban unloaded his camels and
        gave them straw and feed, and [he gave] water to [Eliezer to] wash his feet
        and the feet of the men who were with him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "But when food was set before him, he said, \u201CI will not eat until
        I have stated my business.\u201D And Laban said, \u201CSpeak on.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "So he said, \u201CI am Abraham\u2019s servant. "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'The Lord has greatly blessed my master, and he has become great (wealthy,
        powerful); He has given him flocks and herds, and silver and gold, and servants
        and maids, and camels and donkeys. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "Now Sarah my master\u2019s wife bore a son to my master when she
        was in her old age, and he has given everything that he has to him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "My master made me swear [an oath], saying, \u2018You must not take
        a wife for my son from the daughters of the Canaanites, in whose land I live; "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "but you shall [instead] go to my father\u2019s house and to my family
        and take a wife for my son [Isaac].\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "Then I said to my master, \u2018But suppose the woman will not follow
        me [back to this land].\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "He said to me, \u2018The Lord, before whom I walk [habitually and
        obediently], will send His angel with you to make your journey successful,
        and you will take a wife for my son from my relatives and from my father\u2019s
        house; "
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: "then you will be free of my oath, when you come to my relatives;
        and if they do not give her to you, you will [also] be free of my oath.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: "\u201CI came today to the spring, and said, \u2018O Lord, God of
        my master Abraham, if now You will make my journey on which I go successful; "
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: "please look, I am standing by the spring of water; now let it be
        that when the maiden [whom You have chosen for Isaac] comes out to draw [water],
        and to whom I say, \u201CPlease, give me a little water to drink from your
        jar\u201D; "
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: "and if she says to me, \u201CYou drink, and I will also draw [water]
        for your camels\u201D; let that woman be the one whom the Lord has selected
        and chosen [as a wife] for my master\u2019s son.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: "\u201CBefore I had finished praying in my heart, behold, Rebekah
        came out with her [water] jar on her shoulder, and she went down to the spring
        and drew water. And I said to her, \u2018Please, let me have a drink.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: "And she quickly let down her jar from her shoulder, and said, \u2018Drink,
        and I will also water your camels\u2019; so I drank, and she also watered
        the camels. "
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: "Then I asked her, \u2018Whose daughter are you?\u2019 She said, \u2018The
        daughter of Bethuel, Nahor\u2019s son, whom Milcah bore to him\u2019; and
        I put the ring in her nose, and the bracelets on her arms. "
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: "And I bowed down my head and worshiped the Lord, and blessed the
        Lord, the God of my master Abraham, who had led me in the right way to take
        the daughter of my master\u2019s brother to his son [as a wife]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: "So now if you are going to show kindness and truth to my master [being
        faithful to him], tell me; and if not, tell me, that I may turn to the right
        or to the left [and go on my way].\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: "Then Laban and Bethuel answered, \u201CThe matter has come from the
        Lord; so we dare not speak bad or good [to you about it\u2014we cannot interfere]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: "Rebekah is before you; take her and go, and let her be the wife of
        your master\u2019s son, as the Lord has spoken.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '52: '
      title: 
      number: 52
      content: "When Abraham\u2019s servant heard their words, he bowed himself to
        the ground [in worship] before the Lord. "
      comments: []
    - name: '53: '
      title: 
      number: 53
      content: 'Then the servant brought out jewelry of silver, jewelry of gold,
        and articles of clothing, and gave them to Rebekah; he also gave precious
        things to her brother and her mother. '
      comments: []
    - name: '54: '
      title: 
      number: 54
      content: "Then he and the men who were with him ate and drank and spent the
        night [there]. In the morning when they got up, he said, \u201CNow send me
        back to my master.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '55: '
      title: 
      number: 55
      content: "But Rebekah\u2019s brother and mother said, \u201CLet the girl stay
        with us a few days\u2014at least ten; then she may go.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '56: '
      title: 
      number: 56
      content: "But Eliezer said to them, \u201CDo not delay me, since the Lord has
        prospered my way. Send me away, so that I may go back to my master.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '57: '
      title: 
      number: 57
      content: "And they said, \u201CWe will call the girl and ask her what she prefers.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '58: '
      title: 
      number: 58
      content: "So they called Rebekah and said, \u201CWill you go with this man?\u201D
        And she answered, \u201CI will go.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '59: '
      title: 
      number: 59
      content: "So they sent off their sister Rebekah and her nurse [Deborah, as
        her attendant] and Abraham\u2019s servant [Eliezer] and his men. "
      comments: []
    - name: '60: '
      title: 
      number: 60
      content: "They blessed Rebekah and said to her,\u201CMay you, our sister,Become
        [the mother of] thousands of ten thousands,And may your descendants possess
        (conquer)The [city] gate of those who hate them.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '61: Isaac Marries Rebekah'
      title: Isaac Marries Rebekah
      number: 61
      content: 'Then Rebekah and her attendants stood, and they mounted camels and
        followed the man. So the servant took Rebekah and went on his way.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '62: '
      title: 
      number: 62
      content: 'Now Isaac had returned from going to Beer-lahai-roi (Well of the
        Living One Who Sees Me), for he was living in the Negev. '
      comments: []
    - name: '63: '
      title: 
      number: 63
      content: 'Isaac went out to bow down [in prayer] in the field in the [early]
        evening; he raised his eyes and looked, and camels were coming. '
      comments: []
    - name: '64: '
      title: 
      number: 64
      content: 'Rebekah also raised her eyes and looked, and when she saw Isaac,
        she dismounted from her camel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '65: '
      title: 
      number: 65
      content: "She said to the servant, \u201CWho is that man there walking across
        the field to meet us?\u201D And the servant said, \u201CHe is my master [Isaac].\u201D
        So she took a veil and covered herself [as was customary]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '66: '
      title: 
      number: 66
      content: 'The servant told Isaac everything that he had done. '
      comments: []
    - name: '67: '
      title: 
      number: 67
      content: "Then Isaac brought her into his mother Sarah\u2019s tent, and he
        took Rebekah [in marriage], and she became his wife, and he loved her; therefore
        Isaac was comforted after his mother\u2019s death."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Abraham\u2019s Death"
      title: "Abraham\u2019s Death"
      number: 1
      content: '  Abraham took another wife, whose name was Keturah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'She gave birth to Zimran, Jokshan, Medan, Midian, Ishbak, and Shuah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Jokshan was the father of Sheba and Dedan. The sons of Dedan were
        Asshurim, Letushim, and Leummim. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'The sons of Midian were Ephah, Epher, Hanoch, Abida, and Eldaah.
        All these were the sons of Keturah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Now Abraham gave everything that he had to Isaac; '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'but to the sons of his concubines [Hagar and Keturah], Abraham gave
        gifts while he was still living and he sent them to the east country, away
        from Isaac his son [of promise].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "The days of Abraham\u2019s life were a hundred and seventy-five years. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Then Abraham breathed his last and he died at a good old age, an
        old man who was satisfied [with life]; and he was gathered to his people
        [who had preceded him in death]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'So his sons Isaac and Ishmael buried him in the cave of Machpelah,
        in the field of Ephron the son of Zohar the Hittite, which is east of Mamre, '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'the field which Abraham purchased from the sons of Heth; there Abraham
        was buried with Sarah his wife. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: Descendants of Ishmael'
      title: Descendants of Ishmael
      number: 11
      content: 'Now after the death of Abraham, God blessed his son Isaac; and Isaac
        lived at Beer-lahai-roi.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Now these are the records of the descendants of Ishmael, Abraham\u2019s
        son, whom Hagar the Egyptian, Sarah\u2019s maid, bore to Abraham; "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'and these are the names of the [twelve] sons of Ishmael, named in
        the order of their births: Nebaioth, the firstborn of Ishmael, and Kedar,
        Adbeel, Mibsam, '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Mishma, Dumah, Massa, '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Hadad, Tema, Jetur, Naphish, and Kedemah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'These are the sons of Ishmael and these are their names, by their
        settlements, and by their encampments (sheepfolds); twelve princes (sheiks)
        according to their tribes. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Ishmael lived a hundred and thirty-seven years; then he breathed
        his last and died, and was gathered to his people [who had preceded him in
        death]. '
      comments: []
    - name: "18: Isaac\u2019s Sons"
      title: "Isaac\u2019s Sons"
      number: 18
      content: "Ishmael\u2019s sons (descendants) settled from Havilah to Shur which
        is east of Egypt as one goes toward Assyria; he settled opposite (east) of
        all his relatives.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Now these are the records of the descendants of Isaac, Abraham\u2019s
        son: Abraham was the father of Isaac. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Isaac was forty years old when he married Rebekah, the daughter of
        Bethuel the Aramean (Syrian) of Paddan-aram, the sister of Laban the Aramean. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Isaac prayed to the Lord for his wife, because she was unable to
        conceive children; and the Lord granted his prayer and Rebekah his wife conceived
        [twins]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "But the children struggled together within her [kicking and shoving
        one another]; and she said, \u201CIf it is so [that the Lord has heard our
        prayer], why then am I this way?\u201D So she went to inquire of the Lord
        [praying for an answer]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "The Lord said to her,\u201C[The founders of] two nations are in your
        womb;And the separation of two nations has begun in your body;The one people
        shall be stronger than the other;And the older shall serve the younger.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'When her days to be delivered were fulfilled, behold, there were
        twins in her womb. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'The first came out reddish all over like a hairy garment; and they
        named him Esau (hairy). '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Afterward his brother came out, and his hand grasped Esau\u2019s
        heel, so he was named Jacob (one who grabs by the heel, supplanter). Isaac
        was sixty years old when Rebekah gave birth to them.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'When the boys grew up, Esau was an able and skilled hunter, a man
        of the outdoors, but Jacob was a quiet and peaceful man, living in tents. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Now Isaac loved [and favored] Esau, because he enjoyed eating his
        game, but Rebekah loved [and favored] Jacob. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Jacob had cooked [reddish-brown lentil] stew [one day], when Esau
        came from the field and was famished; '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "and Esau said to Jacob, \u201CPlease, let me have a quick swallow
        of that red stuff there, because I am exhausted and famished.\u201D For that
        reason Esau was [also] called Edom (Red). "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "Jacob answered, \u201CFirst sell me your birthright (the rights of
        a firstborn).\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "Esau said, \u201CLook, I am about to die [if I do not eat soon];
        so of what use is this birthright to me?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "Jacob said, \u201CSwear [an oath] to me today [that you are selling
        it to me for this food]\u201D; so he swore [an oath] to him, and sold him
        his birthright. "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: Then Jacob gave Esau bread and lentil stew; and he ate and drank,
        and got up and went on his way. In this way Esau scorned his birthright.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Isaac Settles in Gerar'
      title: Isaac Settles in Gerar
      number: 1
      content: '  Now there was a famine in the land [of Canaan], besides the previous
        famine that had occurred in the days of Abraham. So Isaac went to Gerar,
        to Abimelech king of the Philistines. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "The Lord appeared to him and said, \u201CDo not go down to Egypt;
        stay in the land of which I will tell you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Live temporarily [as a resident] in this land and I will be with
        you and will bless and favor you, for I will give all these lands to you
        and to your descendants, and I will establish and carry out the oath which
        I swore to Abraham your father. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'I will make your descendants multiply as the stars of the heavens,
        and will give to your descendants all these lands; and by your descendants
        shall all the nations of the earth be blessed, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "because Abraham listened to and obeyed My voice and [consistently]
        kept My charge, My commandments, My statutes, and My laws.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'So Isaac stayed in Gerar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "The men of the place asked him about his wife, and he said, \u201CShe
        is my sister,\u201D for he was afraid to say, \u201Cmy wife\u201D\u2014thinking,
        \u201Cthe men of the place might kill me on account of Rebekah, since she
        is very beautiful.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'It happened when he had been there a long time, that Abimelech king
        of the Philistines looked out of a window and saw Isaac caressing Rebekah
        his wife. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Then Abimelech called Isaac and said, \u201CSee here, Rebekah is
        in fact your wife! How did you [dare to] say to me, \u2018She is my sister\u2019?\u201D
        And Isaac said to him, \u201CBecause I thought I might be killed because
        of her [desirability].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Abimelech said, \u201CWhat is this that you have done to us? One
        of the men [among our people] might easily have been intimate with your wife,
        and you would have brought guilt on us [before God].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Then Abimelech commanded all his people, \u201CWhoever touches this
        man [Isaac] or his wife [Rebekah] shall without exception be put to death.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Then Isaac planted [seed] in that land [as a farmer] and reaped in
        the same year a hundred times [as much as he had planted], and the Lord blessed
        and favored him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And the man [Isaac] became great and gained more and more until he
        became very wealthy and extremely distinguished; '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'he owned flocks and herds and a great household [with a number of
        servants], and the Philistines envied him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Now all the wells which his father\u2019s servants had dug in the
        days of Abraham his father, the Philistines stopped up by filling them with
        dirt. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Then Abimelech said to Isaac, \u201CGo away from here, because you
        are far too powerful for us.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: Quarrel over the Wells'
      title: Quarrel over the Wells
      number: 17
      content: 'So Isaac left that region and camped in the Valley of Gerar, and
        settled there.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Now Isaac again dug [and reopened] the wells of water which had been
        dug in the days of Abraham his father, because the Philistines had filled
        them up [with dirt] after the death of Abraham; and he gave the wells the
        same names that his father had given them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "But when Isaac\u2019s servants dug in the valley and found there
        a well of flowing [spring] water, "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "the herdsmen of Gerar quarreled with Isaac\u2019s herdsmen, saying,
        \u201CThe water is ours!\u201D So Isaac named the well Esek (quarreling),
        because they quarreled with him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Then his servants dug another well, and they quarreled over that
        also, so Isaac named it Sitnah (enmity). '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "He moved away from there and dug another well, and they did not quarrel
        over that one; so he named it Rehoboth (broad places), saying, \u201CFor
        now the Lord has made room for us, and we shall be prosperous in the land.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Then he went up from there to Beersheba. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "The Lord appeared to him the same night and said,\u201CI am the God
        of Abraham your father;Do not be afraid, for I am with you.I will bless and
        favor you, and multiply your descendants,For the sake of My servant Abraham.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: Covenant with Abimelech'
      title: Covenant with Abimelech
      number: 25
      content: "So Isaac built an altar there and called on the name of the Lord
        [in prayer]. He pitched his tent there; and there Isaac\u2019s servants dug
        a well.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Then Abimelech came to him from Gerar with Ahuzzath, his [close friend
        and confidential] adviser, and Phicol, the commander of his army. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Isaac said to them, \u201CWhy have you [people] come to me, since
        you hate me and have sent me away from you?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "They said, \u201CWe see clearly that the Lord has been with you;
        so we said, \u2018There should now be an oath between us [with a curse for
        the one who breaks it], that is, between you and us, and let us make a covenant
        (binding agreement, solemn promise) with you, "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "that you will not harm us, just as we have not touched you and have
        done nothing but good to you and have sent you away in peace. You are now
        the blessed and favored of the Lord!\u2019\u2009\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Then Isaac held a [formal] banquet (covenant feast) for them, and
        they ate and drank. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'They got up early in the morning and swore oaths [pledging to do
        nothing but good to each other]; and Isaac sent them on their way and they
        left him in peace. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "Now on the same day, Isaac\u2019s servants came and told him about
        the well they had dug, saying, \u201CWe have found water.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'So he named the well Shibah; therefore the name of the city is Beersheba
        to this day.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'When Esau was forty years old he married Judith the daughter of Beeri
        the Hittite, and Basemath the daughter of Elon the Hittite as his wives; '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "and they were a source of grief to [Esau\u2019s parents] Isaac and
        Rebekah."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Jacob\u2019s Deception"
      title: "Jacob\u2019s Deception"
      number: 1
      content: "  Now when Isaac was old and his eyes were too dim to see, he called
        his elder [and favorite] son Esau and said to him, \u201CMy son.\u201D And
        Esau answered him, \u201CHere I am.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Isaac said, \u201CSee here, I am old; I do not know when I may die. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'So now, please take your [hunting] gear, your quiver [of arrows]
        and your bow, and go out into the open country and hunt game for me; '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "and make me a savory and delicious dish [of meat], the kind I love,
        and bring it to me to eat, so that my soul may bless you [as my firstborn
        son] before I die.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'But Rebekah overheard what Isaac said to Esau his son; and when Esau
        had gone to the open country to hunt for game that he might bring back, '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Rebekah said to Jacob her [younger and favorite] son, \u201CListen
        carefully: I heard your father saying to Esau your brother, "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u2018Bring me some game and make me a savory and delicious dish
        [of meat], so that I may eat it, and declare my blessing on you in the presence
        of the Lord before my death.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'So now, my son, listen [carefully] to me [and do exactly] as I command
        you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Go now to the flock and bring me two good and suitable young goats,
        and I will make them into a savory dish [of meat] for your father, the kind
        he loves [to eat]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Then you shall bring it to your father to eat, so that he may bless
        you before his death.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Jacob said to Rebekah his mother, \u201CListen, Esau my brother is
        a hairy man and I am a smooth [skinned] man. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Suppose my father touches me and feels my skin; then I will be seen
        by him as a cheat (imposter), and I will bring his curse on me and not a
        blessing.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "But his mother said to him, \u201CMay your curse be on me, my son;
        only listen and obey me, and go, bring the young goats to me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'So Jacob went and got the two young goats, and brought them to his
        mother; and his mother prepared a delicious dish of food [with a delightful
        aroma], the kind his father loved [to eat]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Then Rebekah took her elder son Esau\u2019s best clothes, which were
        with her in her house, and put them on Jacob her younger son. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And she put the skins of the young goats on his hands and on the
        smooth part of his neck. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Then she gave her son Jacob the delicious meat and the bread which
        she had prepared.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "So he went to his father and said, \u201CMy father.\u201D And Isaac
        said, \u201CHere I am. Who are you, my son?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Jacob said to his father, \u201CI am Esau your firstborn; I have
        done what you told me to do. Now please, sit up and eat some of my game,
        so that you may bless me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Isaac said to his son, \u201CHow is it that you have found the game
        so quickly, my son?\u201D And he said, \u201CBecause the Lord your God caused
        it to come to me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "But Isaac [wondered and] said to Jacob, \u201CPlease come close [to
        me] so that I may touch you, my son, and determine if you are really my son
        Esau or not.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "So Jacob approached Isaac, and his father touched him and said, \u201CThe
        voice is Jacob\u2019s voice, but the hands are the hands of Esau.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "He could not recognize him [as Jacob], because his hands were hairy
        like his brother Esau\u2019s hands; so he blessed him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "But he said, \u201CAre you really my son Esau?\u201D Jacob answered,
        \u201CI am.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Then Isaac said, \u201CBring the food to me, and I will eat some
        of my son\u2019s game, so that I may bless you.\u201D He brought it to him,
        and he ate; and he brought him wine and he drank. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Then his father Isaac said to him, \u201CPlease come, my son, and
        kiss me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "So he came and kissed him; and Isaac smelled his clothing and blessed
        him and said,\u201CThe scent of my son [Esau]Is like the aroma of a field
        which the Lord has blessed;  "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Now may God give you of the dew of heaven [to water your land],And
        of the fatness (fertility) of the earth,And an abundance of grain and new
        wine;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: The Stolen Blessing'
      title: The Stolen Blessing
      number: 29
      content: "May peoples serve you,And nations bow down to you;Be lord and master
        over your brothers,And may your mother\u2019s sons bow down to you.May those
        who curse you be cursed,And may those who bless you be blessed.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Now as soon as Isaac had finished blessing Jacob, and Jacob had scarcely
        left the presence of Isaac his father, Esau his brother came in from his
        hunting. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "Esau also made a delicious dish [of meat] and brought it to his father
        and said to him, \u201CLet my father get up and eat some of his son\u2019s
        game, so that you may bless me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "Isaac his father said to him, \u201CWho are you?\u201D And he replied,
        \u201CI am your son, your firstborn, Esau.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "Then Isaac trembled violently, and he said, \u201CThen who was the
        one [who was just here] who hunted game and brought it to me? I ate all of
        it before you came, and I blessed him. Yes, and he [in fact] shall be (shall
        remain) blessed.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "When Esau heard the words of his father, he cried out with a great
        and extremely bitter cry and said to his father, \u201CBless me, even me
        also, O my father!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "Isaac said, \u201CYour brother came deceitfully and has [fraudulently]
        taken away your blessing [for himself].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "Esau replied, \u201CIs he not rightly named Jacob (the supplanter)?
        For he has supplanted me these two times: he took away my birthright, and
        now he has taken away my blessing. Have you not reserved a blessing for me?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "But Isaac replied to Esau, \u201CListen carefully: I have made Jacob
        your lord and master; I have given him all his brothers and relatives as
        servants; and I have sustained him with grain and new wine. What then, can
        I do for you, my son?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "Esau said to his father, \u201CHave you only one blessing, my father?
        Bless me, even me also, O my father.\u201D Then Esau [no longer able to restrain
        himself] raised his voice and wept [loudly].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "Then Isaac his father answered and [prophesied and] said to him,\u201CYour
        dwelling shall be away from the fertility of the earthAnd away from the dew
        of heaven above;  "
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "But you shall live by your sword,And serve your brother;However it
        shall come to pass when you break loose [from your anger and hatred],That
        you will tear his yoke off your neck [and you will be free of him].\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: "So Esau hated Jacob because of the blessing with which his father
        blessed him; and Esau said in his heart, \u201CThe days of mourning for my
        father are very near; then I will kill my brother Jacob.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: "When these words of her elder son Esau were repeated to Rebekah,
        she sent for Jacob her younger son, and said to him, \u201CListen carefully,
        your brother Esau is comforting himself concerning you by planning to kill
        you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'So now, my son, listen and do what I say; go, escape to my brother
        Laban in Haran! '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: "Stay with him for a while, until your brother\u2019s anger subsides. "
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: "When your brother\u2019s anger toward you subsides and he forgets
        what you did to him, then I will send and bring you back from there. Why
        should I be deprived of you both in a single day?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: "Then Rebekah said to Isaac, \u201CI am tired of living because of
        the daughters of Heth [these insolent wives of Esau]. If Jacob takes a wife
        from the daughters of Heth, like these daughters of the land, what good will
        my life be to me?\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jacob Is Sent Away'
      title: Jacob Is Sent Away
      number: 1
      content: "  So Isaac called Jacob and blessed him and charged him, and said
        to him, \u201CYou shall not marry one of the women of Canaan. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Arise, go to Paddan-aram, to the house of Bethuel your mother\u2019s
        father; and take from there as a wife for yourself one of the daughters of
        Laban your mother\u2019s brother. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'May God Almighty bless you and make you fruitful and multiply you,
        so that you may become a [great] company of peoples. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "May He also give the blessing of Abraham to you and your descendants
        with you, that you may inherit the [promised] land of your sojournings, which
        He gave to Abraham.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Then Isaac sent Jacob away, and he went to Paddan-aram, to Laban,
        son of Bethuel the Aramean, the brother of Rebekah, the mother of Jacob and
        Esau.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Now Esau noticed that Isaac had blessed Jacob and sent him to Paddan-aram
        to take a wife for himself from there, and that as he blessed him he gave
        him a prohibition, saying, \u201CYou shall not take a wife from the daughters
        of Canaan,\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'and that Jacob obeyed his father and his mother and had gone to Paddan-aram. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'So Esau realized that [his two wives] the daughters of Canaan displeased
        Isaac his father; '
      comments: []
    - name: "9: Jacob\u2019s Dream"
      title: "Jacob\u2019s Dream"
      number: 9
      content: "and [to appease his parents] Esau went to [the family of] Ishmael
        and took as his wife, in addition to the wives he [already] had, Mahalath
        the daughter of Ishmael, Abraham\u2019s son, the sister of Nebaioth [Ishmael\u2019s
        firstborn son].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Now Jacob left Beersheba [never to see his mother again] and traveled
        toward Haran. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And he came to a certain place and stayed overnight there because
        the sun had set. Taking one of the stones of the place, he put it under his
        head and lay down there [to sleep]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'He dreamed that there was a ladder (stairway) placed on the earth,
        and the top of it reached [out of sight] toward heaven; and [he saw] the
        angels of God ascending and descending on it [going to and from heaven]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And behold, the Lord stood above and around him and said, \u201CI
        am the Lord, the God of Abraham your [father\u2019s] father and the God of
        Isaac; I will give to you and to your descendants the land [of promise] on
        which you are lying. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Your descendants shall be as [countless as] the dust of the earth,
        and you shall spread abroad to the west and the east and the north and the
        south; and all the families (nations) of the earth shall be blessed through
        you and your descendants. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Behold, I am with you and will keep [careful watch over you and guard]
        you wherever you may go, and I will bring you back to this [promised] land;
        for I will not leave you until I have done what I have promised you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Then Jacob awoke from his sleep and he said, \u201CWithout any doubt
        the Lord is in this place, and I did not realize it.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "So he was afraid and said, \u201CHow fearful and awesome is this
        place! This is none other than the house of God, and this is the gateway
        to heaven.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'So Jacob got up early in the morning, and took the stone he had put
        under his head and he set it up as a pillar [that is, a monument to the vision
        in his dream], and he poured [olive] oil on the top of it [to consecrate
        it]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'He named that place Bethel (the house of God); the previous name
        of that city was Luz (Almond Tree). '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Then Jacob made a vow (promise), saying, \u201CIf God will be with
        me and will keep me on this journey that I take, and will give me food to
        eat and clothing to wear, "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "and if [He grants that] I return to my father\u2019s house in safety,
        then the Lord will be my God. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "This stone which I have set up as a pillar (monument, memorial) will
        be God\u2019s house [a sacred place to me], and of everything that You give
        me I will give the tenth to You [as an offering to signify my gratitude and
        dependence on You].\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jacob Meets Rachel'
      title: Jacob Meets Rachel
      number: 1
      content: '  Then Jacob went on his way and came to the land of the people of
        the East [near Haran]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'As he looked, he saw a well in the field, and three flocks of sheep
        lying there [resting] beside it because the flocks were watered from that
        well. Now the stone on the mouth of the well [that covered and protected
        it] was large, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'and when all the flocks were gathered there, the shepherds would
        roll the stone from the mouth of the well, water the sheep, and [afterward]
        replace the stone on the mouth of the well.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Jacob said to them, \u201CMy brothers, where are you from?\u201D
        And they said, \u201CWe are from Haran.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "So he said to them, \u201CDo you know Laban the grandson of Nahor
        [Abraham\u2019s brother]?\u201D And they replied, \u201CWe know him.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And he asked them, \u201CIs it well with him?\u201D And they said,
        \u201CHe is doing well; look, here comes his daughter Rachel with the sheep!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Jacob said, \u201CLook, the sun is still high [overhead]; it is a
        long time before the flocks need to be gathered [in their folds for the night].
        Water the sheep, and go, and return them to their pasture.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "But they said, \u201CWe cannot [leave] until all the flocks are gathered
        together, and the shepherds roll the stone from the mouth of the well; then
        we will water the sheep.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "While he was still speaking with them, Rachel came with her father\u2019s
        sheep, for she was a shepherdess. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "When Jacob saw [his cousin] Rachel, the daughter of Laban, his mother\u2019s
        brother, and Laban\u2019s sheep, he came up and rolled the stone away from
        the mouth of the well and watered the flock of Laban, his uncle. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Then Jacob kissed Rachel [in greeting], and he raised his voice and
        wept. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Jacob told Rachel he was her father\u2019s relative, Rebekah\u2019s
        son; and she ran and told her father.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "When Laban heard of the arrival of Jacob, his sister\u2019s son,
        he ran to meet him, and embraced and kissed him and brought him to his house.
        Then he told Laban all these things. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Then Laban said to him, \u201CYou are my bone and my flesh.\u201D
        And Jacob stayed with him a month.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Then Laban said to Jacob, \u201CJust because you are my relative,
        should you work for me for nothing? Tell me, what should your wages be?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Now Laban had two daughters; the name of the older was Leah, and
        the name of the younger was Rachel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Leah\u2019s eyes were weak, but Rachel was beautiful in form and
        appearance. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Jacob loved Rachel, so he said, \u201CI will serve you [as a hired
        workman] for seven years [in return] for [the privilege of marrying] Rachel
        your younger daughter.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Laban said, \u201CIt is better that I give her [in marriage] to you
        than give her to another man. Stay and work with me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: "20: Laban\u2019s Treachery"
      title: "Laban\u2019s Treachery"
      number: 20
      content: 'So Jacob served [Laban] for seven years for [the right to marry]
        Rachel, but they seemed like only a few days to him because of his love for
        her.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Finally, Jacob said to Laban, \u201CGive me my wife, for my time
        [of service] is completed, so that I may take her to me [as my wife].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'So Laban gathered together all the men of the place and prepared
        a [wedding] feast [with wine]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'But in the evening he took Leah his daughter and brought her to Jacob,
        and Jacob went in to [consummate the marriage with] her. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Laban also gave Zilpah his maid to his daughter Leah as a maid. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "But in the morning [when Jacob awoke], it was Leah [who was with
        him]! And he said to Laban, \u201CWhat is this that you have done to me?
        Did I not work for you [for seven years] for Rachel? Why have you deceived
        and betrayed me [like this]?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "But Laban only said, \u201CIt is not the tradition here to give the
        younger [daughter in marriage] before the older. "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Finish the week [of the wedding feast] for Leah; then we will give
        you Rachel also, and in return you shall work for me for seven more years.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "So Jacob complied and fulfilled Leah\u2019s week [of celebration];
        then Laban gave him his daughter Rachel as his [second] wife. "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Laban also gave Bilhah his maid to his daughter Rachel as a maid. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'So Jacob consummated his marriage and lived with Rachel [as his wife],
        and he loved Rachel more than Leah, and he served with Laban for another
        seven years.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Now when the Lord saw that Leah was unloved, He made her able to
        bear children, but Rachel was barren. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "Leah conceived and gave birth to a son and named him Reuben (See,
        a son!), for she said, \u201CBecause the Lord has seen my humiliation and
        suffering; now my husband will love me [since I have given him a son].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "Then she conceived again and gave birth to a son and said, \u201CBecause
        the Lord heard that I am unloved, He has given me this son also.\u201D So
        she named him Simeon (God hears). "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "She conceived again and gave birth to a son and said, \u201CNow this
        time my husband will become attached to me [as a companion], for I have given
        him three sons.\u201D Therefore he was named Levi. "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "Again she conceived and gave birth to a [fourth] son, and she said,
        \u201CNow I will praise the Lord.\u201D So she named him Judah; then [for
        a time] she stopped bearing [children]."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Sons of Jacob'
      title: The Sons of Jacob
      number: 1
      content: "  When Rachel saw that she conceived no children for Jacob, she envied
        her sister, and said to Jacob, \u201CGive me children, or else I will die.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Then Jacob became furious with Rachel, and he said, \u201CAm I in
        the place of God, who has denied you children?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "She said, \u201CHere, take my maid Bilhah and go in to her; and [when
        the baby comes] she shall deliver it [while sitting] on my knees, so that
        by her I may also have children [to count as my own].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'So she gave him Bilhah her maid as a [secondary] wife, and Jacob
        went in to her. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Bilhah conceived and gave birth to a son for Jacob. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Then Rachel said, \u201CGod has judged and vindicated me, and has
        heard my plea and has given me a son [through my maid].\u201D So she named
        him Dan (He judged). "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Bilhah, Rachel\u2019s maid, conceived again and gave birth to a second
        son for Jacob. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "So Rachel said, \u201CWith mighty wrestlings [in prayer to God] I
        have struggled with my sister and have prevailed.\u201D So she named him
        Naphtali (my wrestlings).  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'When Leah saw that she had stopped bearing [children], she took Zilpah
        her maid and gave her to Jacob as a [secondary] wife. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Zilpah, Leah\u2019s maid, gave birth to a son for Jacob. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Then Leah said, \u201CHow fortunate!\u201D So she named him Gad (good
        fortune). "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Zilpah, Leah\u2019s maid, gave birth to a second son for Jacob. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Then Leah said, \u201CI am happy! For women will call me happy.\u201D
        So she named him Asher (happy).  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Now at the time of wheat harvest Reuben [the eldest child] went and
        found some mandrakes in the field, and brought them to his mother Leah. Then
        Rachel said to Leah, \u201CPlease give me some of your son\u2019s mandrakes.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "But Leah answered, \u201CIs it a small thing that you have taken
        my husband? Would you take away my son\u2019s mandrakes also?\u201D So Rachel
        said, \u201CJacob shall sleep with you tonight in exchange for your son\u2019s
        mandrakes.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "When Jacob came in from the field in the evening, Leah went out to
        meet him and said, \u201CYou must sleep with me [tonight], for I have in
        fact hired you with my son\u2019s mandrakes.\u201D So he slept with her that
        night. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'God listened and answered [the prayer of] Leah, and she conceived
        and gave birth to a fifth son for Jacob. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Then Leah said, \u201CGod has given me my reward because I have given
        my maid to my husband.\u201D So she named him Issachar. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Leah conceived again and gave birth to a sixth son for Jacob. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Then Leah said, \u201CGod has endowed me with a good [marriage] gift
        [for my husband]; now he will live with me [regarding me with honor as his
        wife], because I have given birth to six sons.\u201D So she named him Zebulun. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Afterward she gave birth to a daughter and named her Dinah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Then God remembered [the prayers of] Rachel, and God thought of her
        and opened her womb [so that she would conceive]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "So she conceived and gave birth to a son; and she said, \u201CGod
        has taken away my disgrace and humiliation.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: Jacob Prospers'
      title: Jacob Prospers
      number: 24
      content: "She named him Joseph (may He add) and said, \u201CMay the Lord add
        to me another son.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Now when Rachel had given birth to Joseph, Jacob said to Laban, \u201CSend
        me away, that I may go back to my own place and to my own country. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Give me my wives and my children for whom I have served you, and
        let me go; for you know the work which I have done for you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "But Laban said to him, \u201CIf I have found favor in your sight,
        stay with me; for I have learned [from the omens in divination and by experience]
        that the Lord has blessed me because of you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "He said, \u201CName your wages, and I will give it [to you].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Jacob answered him, \u201CYou know how I have served you and how
        your possessions, your cattle and sheep and goats, have fared with me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "For you had little before I came and it has increased and multiplied
        abundantly, and the Lord has favored you with blessings wherever I turned.
        But now, when shall I provide for my own household?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "Laban asked, \u201CWhat shall I give you?\u201D Jacob replied, \u201CYou
        shall not give me anything. But if you will do this one thing for me [which
        I now propose], I will again pasture and keep your flock: "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'Let me pass through your entire flock today, removing from it every
        speckled and spotted sheep and every dark or black one among the lambs and
        the spotted and speckled among the goats; and those shall be my wages. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "So my honesty will be evident for me later, when you come [for an
        accounting] concerning my wages. Every one that is not speckled and spotted
        among the goats and dark among the young lambs, if found with me, shall be
        considered stolen.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "And Laban said, \u201CGood! Let it be done as you say.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'So on that same day Laban [secretly] removed the male goats that
        were streaked and spotted and all the female goats that were speckled and
        spotted, every one with white on it, and all the dark ones among the sheep,
        and put them in the care of his sons. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "And he put [a distance of] three days\u2019 journey between himself
        and Jacob, and Jacob was then left in care of the rest of Laban\u2019s flock.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'Then Jacob took branches of fresh poplar and almond and plane trees,
        and peeled white stripes in them, exposing the white in the branches. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'Then he set the branches which he had peeled in front of the flocks
        in the watering troughs, where the flocks came to drink; and they mated and
        conceived when they came to drink. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'So the flocks mated and conceived by the branches, and the flocks
        gave birth to streaked, speckled, and spotted offspring. '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "Jacob separated the lambs, and [as he had done with the peeled branches]
        he made the flocks face toward the streaked and all the dark or black in
        the [new] flock of Laban; and he put his own herds apart by themselves and
        did not put them [where they could breed] with Laban\u2019s flock. "
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'Furthermore, whenever the stronger [animals] of the flocks were breeding,
        Jacob would place the branches in the sight of the flock in the watering
        troughs, so that they would mate and conceive among the branches; '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: "but when the flock was sickly, he did not put the branches there;
        so the sicker [animals] were Laban\u2019s and the stronger Jacob\u2019s. "
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: So Jacob became exceedingly prosperous, and had large flocks [of sheep
        and goats], and female and male servants, and camels and donkeys.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jacob Leaves Secretly for Canaan'
      title: Jacob Leaves Secretly for Canaan
      number: 1
      content: "  Jacob heard that Laban\u2019s sons were saying: \u201CJacob has
        taken away everything that was our father\u2019s, and from what belonged
        to our father he has acquired all this wealth and honor.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Jacob noticed [a change in] the attitude of Laban, and saw that it
        was not friendly toward him as before. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Then the Lord said to Jacob, \u201CReturn to the land of your fathers
        and to your people, and I will be with you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'So Jacob sent and called Rachel and Leah to his flock in the field, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "and he said to them, \u201CI see [a change in] your father\u2019s
        attitude, that he is not friendly toward me as [he was] before; but the God
        of my father [Isaac] has been with me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'You know that I have served your father with all my strength. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Yet your father has cheated me [as often as possible] and changed
        my wages ten times; but God did not allow him to hurt me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "If he said, \u2018The speckled shall be your wages,\u2019 then the
        entire flock gave birth to speckled [young]; and if he said, \u2018The streaked
        shall be your wages,\u2019 then the entire flock gave birth to streaked [young]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Thus God has taken away the flocks of your father and given them
        to me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And it happened at the time when the flock conceived that I looked
        up and saw in a dream that the rams which mated [with the female goats] were
        streaked, speckled, and spotted. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And the Angel of God said to me in the dream, \u2018Jacob.\u2019
        And I said, \u2018Here I am.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "He said, \u2018Look up and see, all the rams which are mating [with
        the flock] are streaked, speckled, and spotted; for I have seen all that
        Laban has been doing to you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "I am the God of Bethel, where you anointed the pillar, and where
        you made a vow to Me; now stand up, leave this land, and return to the land
        of your birth.\u2019\u2009\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Rachel and Leah answered him, \u201CIs there still any portion or
        inheritance for us in our father\u2019s house? "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Are we not counted by him as foreigners? For he sold us [to you in
        marriage], and has also entirely used up our purchase price. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Surely all the riches which God has taken from our father are ours
        and our children\u2019s. Now then, whatever God has told you to do, do it.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Then Jacob stood [and took action] and put his children and his wives
        on camels; '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'and he drove away all his livestock and [took along] all his property
        which he had acquired, the livestock he had obtained and accumulated in Paddan-aram,
        to go to his father Isaac in the land of Canaan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "When Laban had gone to shear his sheep, Rachel [went inside the house
        and] stole her father\u2019s household gods. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And Jacob deceived Laban the Aramean (Syrian) by not telling him
        that he intended to leave and he slipped away secretly. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: Laban Pursues Jacob'
      title: Laban Pursues Jacob
      number: 21
      content: 'So he fled with everything that he had, and got up and crossed the
        river [Euphrates], and set his face toward the hill country of Gilead [east
        of the Jordan River].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'On the third day [after his departure] Laban was told that Jacob
        had fled. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'So he took his relatives with him and pursued him for seven days,
        and they overtook him in the hill country of Gilead. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "God came to Laban the Aramean in a dream at night and said to him,
        \u201CBe careful that you do not speak to Jacob, either good or bad.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Then Laban overtook Jacob. Now Jacob had pitched his tent on the
        hill, and Laban with his relatives camped on the same hill of Gilead. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Then Laban said to Jacob, \u201CWhat do you mean by deceiving me
        and leaving without my knowledge, and carrying off my daughters as if [they
        were] captives of the sword? "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Why did you run away secretly and deceive me and not tell me, so
        that [otherwise] I might have sent you away with joy and with songs, with
        [music on the] tambourine and lyre? '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'And why did you not allow me to kiss my grandchildren and my daughters
        [goodbye]? Now you have done a foolish thing [in behaving like this]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "It is in my power to harm you, but the God of your father spoke to
        me last night, saying, \u2018Be careful not to speak to Jacob, either good
        or bad.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "Now [I suppose] you felt you must go because you were homesick for
        your father\u2019s house and family; but why did you steal my [household]
        gods?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "Jacob answered Laban, \u201C[I left secretly] because I was afraid,
        for I thought you would take your daughters away from me by force. "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "The one with whom you find your gods shall not live; in the presence
        of our relatives [search my possessions and] point out whatever you find
        that belongs to you and take it.\u201D For Jacob did not know that Rachel
        had stolen the idols.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "So Laban went into Jacob\u2019s tent and into Leah\u2019s tent and
        the tent of the two maids, but he did not find them. Then he came out of
        Leah\u2019s tent and entered Rachel\u2019s tent. "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "Now Rachel had taken the household idols and put them in the camel\u2019s
        saddlebag and sat on them. Laban searched through all her tent, but did not
        find them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "So Rachel said to her father, \u201CDo not be displeased, my lord,
        that I cannot rise before you, for the manner of women is on me and I am
        unwell.\u201D He searched [further] but did not find the household idols.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "Then Jacob became angry and argued with Laban. And he said to Laban,
        \u201CWhat is my fault? What is my sin that you pursued me like this? "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'Although you have searched through all my possessions, what have
        you found of your household goods? Put it here before my relatives and your
        relatives, so that they may decide [who has done right] between the two of
        us. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'These twenty years I have been with you; your ewes and your female
        goats have not lost their young, nor have I eaten the rams of your flocks. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'I did not bring you the torn carcasses [of the animals attacked by
        predators]; I [personally] took the loss. You required of me [to make good]
        everything that was stolen, whether it occurred by day or night. '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'This was my situation: by day the heat consumed me and by night the
        cold, and I could not sleep. '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'These twenty years I have been in your house; I served you fourteen
        years for your two daughters and six years for [my share of] your flocks,
        and you have changed my wages ten times. '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: The Covenant of Mizpah'
      title: The Covenant of Mizpah
      number: 42
      content: "If the God of my father, the God of Abraham, and [the Feared One]
        of Isaac, had not been with me, most certainly you would have sent me away
        now empty-handed. God has seen my affliction and humiliation and the [exhausting]
        labor of my hands, so He rendered judgment and rebuked you last night.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: "Laban answered Jacob, \u201CThese women [that you married] are my
        daughters, these children are my grandchildren, these flocks are [from] my
        flocks, and all that you see [here] is mine. But what can I do today to these
        my daughters or to their children to whom they have given birth? "
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: "So come now, let us make a covenant, you and I, and let it serve
        as a witness between you and me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: 'So Jacob took a stone and set it up as a [memorial] pillar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: "Jacob said to his relatives, \u201CGather stones.\u201D And they
        took stones and made a mound [of stones], and they ate [a ceremonial meal
        together] there on the mound [of stones]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: 'Laban called it Jegar-sahadutha (stone monument of testimony in Aramaic),
        but Jacob called it Galeed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: "Laban said, \u201CThis mound [of stones] is a witness [a reminder
        of the oath taken] today between you and me.\u201D Therefore he [also] called
        the name Galeed, "
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: "and Mizpah (watchtower), for Laban said, \u201CMay the Lord watch
        between you and me when we are absent from one another. "
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: "If you should mistreat (humiliate, oppress) my daughters, or if you
        should take other wives besides my daughters, although no one is with us
        [as a witness], see and remember, God is witness between you and me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: "Laban said to Jacob, \u201CLook at this mound [of stones] and look
        at this pillar which I have set up between you and me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '52: '
      title: 
      number: 52
      content: 'This mound is a witness, and this pillar is a witness, that I will
        not pass by this mound to harm you, and that you will not pass by this mound
        and this pillar to harm me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '53: '
      title: 
      number: 53
      content: "The God of Abraham [your father] and the God of Nahor [my father],
        and the god [the image of worship] of their father [Terah, an idolater],
        judge between us.\u201D But Jacob swore [only] by [the one true God] the
        Fear of his father Isaac. "
      comments: []
    - name: '54: '
      title: 
      number: 54
      content: 'Then Jacob offered a sacrifice [to the Lord] on the mountain, and
        called his relatives to the meal; and they ate food and spent the night on
        the mountain. '
      comments: []
    - name: '55: '
      title: 
      number: 55
      content: "Early in the morning Laban got up and kissed his grandchildren and
        his daughters [goodbye] and pronounced a blessing [asking God\u2019s favor]
        on them. Then Laban left and returned home."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Jacob\u2019s Fear of Esau"
      title: "Jacob\u2019s Fear of Esau"
      number: 1
      content: '  Then as Jacob went on his way, the angels of God met him [to reassure
        and protect him]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "When Jacob saw them, he said, \u201CThis is God\u2019s camp.\u201D
        So he named that place Mahanaim (double camps).  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Then Jacob sent messengers ahead of him to his brother Esau in the
        land of Seir, the country of Edom. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "He commanded them, saying, \u201CThis is what to say to my lord Esau:
        \u2018Your servant Jacob says this, \u201CI have been living temporarily
        with Laban, and have stayed there until now; "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "I have oxen, donkeys, flocks, male servants, and female servants;
        and I have sent [this message] to tell my lord, so that I may find grace
        and kindness in your sight.\u201D\u2009\u2019\u2009\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "The messengers returned to Jacob, saying, \u201CWe went to your brother
        Esau, and now he is coming to meet you, and there are four hundred men with
        him.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Jacob was greatly afraid and distressed; and he divided the people
        who were with him, and the flocks and herds and camels, into two camps; '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "and he said, \u201CIf Esau comes to the one camp and attacks it,
        then the other camp which is left will escape.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Jacob said, \u201CO God of my father Abraham and God of my father
        Isaac, the Lord, who said to me, \u2018Return to your country and to your
        people, and I will make you prosper,\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'I am unworthy of all the lovingkindness and compassion and of all
        the faithfulness which You have shown to Your servant. With only my staff
        [long ago] I crossed over this Jordan, and now I have become [blessed and
        increased into these] two groups [of people]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Save me, please, from the hand of my brother, from the hand of Esau;
        for I fear him, that he will come and attack me and the mothers with the
        children. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And You [Lord] said, \u2018I will certainly make you prosper and
        make your descendants as [numerous as] the sand of the sea, which is too
        great to be counted.\u2019\u2009\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'So Jacob spent the night there. Then he selected a present for his
        brother Esau from the livestock he had acquired: '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'two hundred female goats, twenty male goats, two hundred ewes, twenty
        rams, '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'thirty milking camels with their colts, forty cows, ten bulls, twenty
        female donkeys, and ten [donkey] colts. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "He put them into the care of his servants, every herd by itself,
        and said to his servants, \u201CGo on ahead of me, and put an interval [of
        space] between the individual herds.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Then he commanded the one in front, saying, \u201CWhen Esau my brother
        meets you and asks to whom you belong, and where you are going, and whose
        are the animals in front of you? "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "then you shall say, \u2018They are your servant Jacob\u2019s; they
        are a gift sent to my lord Esau. And he also is behind us.\u2019\u2009\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "And so Jacob commanded the second and the third as well, and all
        that followed the herds, saying, \u201CThis is what you shall say to Esau
        when you meet him; "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "and you shall say, \u2018Look, your servant Jacob is behind us.\u2019\u2009\u201D
        For he said [to himself], \u201CI will try to appease him with the gift that
        is going ahead of me. Then afterward I will see him; perhaps he will accept
        and forgive me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'So the gift [of the herds of livestock] went on ahead of him, and
        he himself spent that night back in the camp.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'But he got up that same night and took his two wives, his two female
        servants, and his eleven children, and waded over the ford of the Jabbok. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: Jacob Wrestles'
      title: Jacob Wrestles
      number: 23
      content: 'Then he took them and sent them across the brook. And he also sent
        across whatever he had.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'So Jacob was left alone, and a Man [came and] wrestled with him until
        daybreak. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "When the Man saw that He had not prevailed against Jacob, He touched
        his hip joint; and Jacob\u2019s hip was dislocated as he wrestled with Him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Then He said, \u201CLet Me go, for day is breaking.\u201D But Jacob
        said, \u201CI will not let You go unless You declare a blessing on me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "So He asked him, \u201CWhat is your name?\u201D And he said, \u201CJacob.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "And He said, \u201CYour name shall no longer be Jacob, but Israel;
        for you have struggled with God and with men and have prevailed.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Then Jacob asked Him, \u201CPlease tell me Your name.\u201D But He
        said, \u201CWhy is it that you ask My name?\u201D And He declared a blessing
        [of the covenant promises] on Jacob there. "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "So Jacob named the place Peniel (the face of God), saying, \u201CFor
        I have seen God face to face, yet my life has not been snatched away.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Now the sun rose on him as he passed Penuel (Peniel), and he was
        limping because of his hip. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "Therefore, to this day the Israelites do not eat the tendon of the
        hip which is on the socket of the thigh, because He touched the socket of
        Jacob\u2019s thigh by the tendon of the hip."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jacob Meets Esau'
      title: Jacob Meets Esau
      number: 1
      content: '  Then Jacob looked up, and saw Esau coming with four hundred men.
        So he divided the children among Leah and Rachel and the two maids. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'He put the maids and their children in front, Leah and her children
        after them, and Rachel and Joseph last of all. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Then Jacob crossed over [the stream] ahead of them and bowed himself
        to the ground seven times [bowing and moving forward each time], until he
        approached his brother.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'But Esau ran to meet him and embraced him, and hugged his neck and
        kissed him, and they wept [for joy]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Esau looked up and saw the women and the children, and said, \u201CWho
        are these with you?\u201D So Jacob replied, \u201CThey are the children whom
        God has graciously given your servant.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Then the maids approached with their children, and they bowed down. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Leah also approached with her children, and they bowed down. Afterward
        Joseph and Rachel approached, and they bowed down. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Esau asked, \u201CWhat do you mean by all this company which I have
        met?\u201D And he answered, \u201C[These are] to find favor in the sight
        of my lord.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "But Esau said, \u201CI have plenty, my brother; keep what you have
        for yourself.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Jacob replied, \u201CNo, please, if now I have found favor in your
        sight, then accept my gift [as a blessing] from my hand, for I see your face
        as if I had seen the face of God, and you have received me favorably. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Please accept my blessing (gift) which has been brought to you, for
        God has dealt graciously with me and I have everything [that I could possibly
        want].\u201D So Jacob kept urging him and Esau accepted it.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Then Esau said, \u201CLet us get started on our journey and I will
        go in front of you [to lead the way].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "But Jacob replied, \u201CYou know, my lord, that the children are
        frail and need gentle care, and the nursing flocks and herds [with young]
        are of concern to me; for if the men should drive them hard for a single
        day, all the flocks will die. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Please let my lord go on ahead of his servant, and I will move on
        slowly, governed by the pace of the livestock that are in front of me and
        according to the endurance of the children, until I come to my lord in Seir
        [in Edom].\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Then Esau said, \u201CPlease let me leave with you some of the people
        who are with me.\u201D But Jacob said, \u201CWhat need is there [for it]?
        Let me find favor in the sight of my lord.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'So Esau turned back [toward the south] that day on his way to Seir. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: Jacob Settles in Shechem'
      title: Jacob Settles in Shechem
      number: 17
      content: 'But Jacob journeyed [north] to Succoth, and built himself a house
        and made shelters for his livestock; so the name of the place is Succoth
        (huts, shelters).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'When Jacob came from Paddan-aram, he arrived safely and in peace
        at the city of Shechem, in the land of Canaan, and camped in front of the
        [walled] city. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Then he bought the piece of land on which he had pitched his tents
        from the sons of Hamor, Shechem\u2019s father, for a hundred pieces of money. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: There he erected an altar and called it El-Elohe-Israel.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: The Treachery of Jacob\u2019s Sons"
      title: "The Treachery of Jacob\u2019s Sons"
      number: 1
      content: '  Now Dinah the daughter of Leah, whom she had borne to Jacob, went
        out [unescorted] to visit the girls of the land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'When Shechem the son of Hamor the Hivite, prince (sheik) of the land,
        saw her, he kidnapped her and lay [intimately] with her by force [humbling
        and offending her]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "But his soul longed for and clung to Dinah daughter of Jacob, and
        he loved the girl and spoke comfortingly to her young heart\u2019s wishes. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "So Shechem said to his father Hamor, \u201CGet me this young woman
        as a wife.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Now Jacob heard that Shechem had defiled (violated) Dinah his daughter;
        but his sons were in the field with his livestock, so Jacob said nothing
        until they came in. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "But Shechem\u2019s father Hamor went to Jacob to talk with him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Now when Jacob\u2019s sons heard of it they came in from the field;
        they were deeply grieved, and they were very angry, for Shechem had done
        a disgraceful thing to Israel by lying with Jacob\u2019s daughter, for such
        a thing is not to be done.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "But Hamor conferred with them, saying, \u201CThe soul of my son Shechem
        [deeply] longs for your daughter [and sister]. Please give her to him as
        his wife. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And [beyond that] intermarry with us; give your daughters to us [as
        wives] and take our daughters for yourselves. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "In this way you shall live with us; the country will be open to you;
        live and do business in it and acquire property and possessions in it.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Shechem also said to Dinah\u2019s father and to her brothers, \u201CLet
        me find favor in your sight, and I will give you whatever you ask of me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Demand of me a very large bridal payment and gift [as compensation
        for giving up your daughter and sister], and I will give you whatever you
        tell me; only give me the girl to be my wife.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Jacob\u2019s sons answered Shechem and Hamor his father deceitfully,
        because Shechem had defiled and disgraced their sister Dinah. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "They said to them, \u201CWe cannot do this thing and give our sister
        [in marriage] to one who is not circumcised, because that would be a disgrace
        to us. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'But we will consent to you only on this condition: if you will become
        like us, in that every male among you consents to be circumcised, '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'then we will give our daughters to you [in marriage], and we will
        take your daughters for ourselves, and we will live with you and become one
        people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "But if you do not listen to us and refuse to be circumcised, then
        we will take our daughter [Dinah] and go.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Their words seemed reasonable to Hamor and his son Shechem, '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "and the young man did not hesitate to do the [required] thing, for
        he was delighted with Jacob\u2019s daughter. Now he was more respected and
        honored than all [others] in the household of his father. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Then Hamor and Shechem his son came to the gate of their [walled]
        city [where the leading men would meet] and spoke with the men of the city,
        saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "\u201CThese men are peaceful and friendly with us; so let them live
        in the land and do business in it, for the land is large enough [for us and]
        for them; let us take their daughters for wives and let us give them our
        daughters [in marriage]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'But only on this condition will the men consent to our request that
        they live among us and become one people: that every male among us become
        circumcised just as they are circumcised. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Will not their cattle and their possessions and all their animals
        be ours [if we do this]? Let us consent [to do as they ask], and they will
        live here with us.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'And every [Canaanite] man who went out of the city gate listened
        and considered what Hamor and Shechem said; and every male who was a resident
        of that city was circumcised.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Now on the third day [after the circumcision], when all the men were
        [terribly] sore and in pain, two of Jacob\u2019s sons, Simeon and Levi, Dinah\u2019s
        [full] brothers, took their swords, boldly entered the city [without anyone
        suspecting them of evil intent], and they killed every male. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "They killed Hamor and his son Shechem with the edge of the sword,
        and took Dinah out of Shechem\u2019s house [where she was staying], and left. "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Then Jacob\u2019s [other] sons came upon those who were killed and
        looted the town, because their sister had been defiled and disgraced. "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "They took the Canaanites\u2019 flocks and their herds and their donkeys,
        and whatever was in the city and in the field; "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'they looted all their wealth, and [took captive] all their children
        and their wives, even everything that was in the houses. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "Then Jacob said to Simeon and Levi, \u201CYou have ruined me, making
        me a stench to the inhabitants of the land, the Canaanites and the Perizzites!
        My men are few in number, and the men of the land will band together against
        me and attack me; I shall be destroyed, I and my household.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "But they said, \u201CShould he [be permitted to] treat our sister
        as a prostitute?\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jacob Moves to Bethel'
      title: Jacob Moves to Bethel
      number: 1
      content: "  Then God said to Jacob, \u201CGo up to Bethel and live there, and
        make an altar there to God, who appeared to you [in a distinct manifestation]
        when you fled [years ago] from Esau your brother.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Then Jacob said to his household and to all who were with him, \u201CGet
        rid of the [idols and images of] foreign gods that are among you, and ceremonially
        purify yourselves and change [into fresh] clothes; "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "then let us get up and go up to Bethel, and I will make an altar
        there to God, who answered me in the day of my distress and has been with
        me wherever I have gone.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'So they gave Jacob all the [idols and images of the] foreign gods
        they had and the rings which were in their ears [worn as charms against evil],
        and Jacob buried them under the oak tree near Shechem.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'As they journeyed, there was a great [supernatural] terror [sent
        from God] on the cities around them, and [for that reason] the Canaanites
        did not pursue the sons of Jacob. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'So Jacob came to Luz (that is, Bethel), which is in the land of Canaan,
        he and all the people who were with him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'There he built an altar [to worship the Lord], and called the place
        El-bethel (God of the House of God), because there God had revealed Himself
        to him when he escaped from his brother. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: Jacob Is Named Israel'
      title: Jacob Is Named Israel
      number: 8
      content: "Now Deborah, [who once was] Rebekah\u2019s nurse, died and was buried
        below Bethel under the oak; and the name of it was called Allon-bacuth (Oak
        of Weeping).  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Then God [in a visible manifestation] appeared to Jacob again when
        he came out of Paddan-aram, and declared a blessing on him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Again God said to him,\u201CYour name is Jacob;You shall no longer
        be called Jacob,But Israel shall be your name.\u201DSo he was called Israel. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And God said to him,\u201CI am God Almighty.Be fruitful and multiply;A
        nation and a company of nations shall come from you,And kings shall be born
        of your loins.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "The land which I gave Abraham and IsaacI will give to you,and to
        your descendants after you I will give the land.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Then God ascended from Jacob in the place where He had spoken with
        him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Jacob set up a pillar (memorial, monument) in the place where he
        had talked with God, a pillar of stone, and he poured a drink offering [of
        wine] on it; he also poured oil on it [to declare it sacred for God\u2019s
        purpose]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'So Jacob named the place where God had spoken with him, Bethel (the
        House of God).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Then they journeyed from Bethel; and when there was still some distance
        to go to Ephrath (Bethlehem), Rachel began to give birth and had difficulty
        and suffered severely. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "When she was in hard labor the midwife said to her, \u201CDo not
        be afraid; you now have another son.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And as her soul was departing, (for she died), she named him Ben-oni
        (son of my sorrow); but his father called him Benjamin (son of the right
        hand). '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'So Rachel died and was buried on the way to Ephrath (that is, Bethlehem). '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Jacob set a pillar (memorial, monument) on her grave; that is the
        pillar of Rachel\u2019s grave to this day. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Then Israel (Jacob) journeyed on and pitched his tent on the other
        side of the tower of Eder [the lookout point used by shepherds].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: The Sons of Israel'
      title: The Sons of Israel
      number: 22
      content: "While Israel was living in that land, Reuben [his eldest son] went
        and lay with Bilhah his father\u2019s concubine, and Israel heard about it. 
        Now Jacob had twelve sons\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "The sons of Leah: Reuben, Jacob\u2019s firstborn, then Simeon, Levi,
        Judah, Issachar, and Zebulun; "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'and the sons of Rachel: Joseph and Benjamin; '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "and the sons of Bilhah, Rachel\u2019s maid: Dan and Naphtali; "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "and the sons of Zilpah, Leah\u2019s maid: Gad and Asher. These are
        the sons of Jacob born to him in Paddan-aram.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Jacob came to Isaac his father at Mamre of Kiriath-arba (that is,
        Hebron), where Abraham and Isaac had lived temporarily.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Now the days of Isaac were a hundred and eighty years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Isaac\u2019s spirit departed and he died and was gathered to his
        people [who had preceded him in death], an old man full of days (satisfied,
        fulfilled); his sons Esau and Jacob buried him [in the cave of Machpelah
        with his parents Abraham and Sarah]."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Esau Moves'
      title: Esau Moves
      number: 1
      content: '  Now these are the records of the descendants of Esau, (that is,
        Edom).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Esau took his [three] wives from the daughters of Canaan: Adah the
        daughter of Elon the Hittite, and Oholibamah the daughter of Anah, the son
        of Zibeon the Hivite, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "and Basemath, Ishmael\u2019s daughter, sister of Nebaioth. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Adah bore Eliphaz to Esau, and Basemath bore Reuel, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'and Oholibamah bore Jeush, Jalam, and Korah. These are the sons of
        Esau born to him in Canaan.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Now Esau took his wives and his sons and his daughters and all the
        members of his household, and his livestock and all his cattle and all his
        possessions which he had acquired in the land of Canaan, and he went to a
        land away from his brother Jacob. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'For their [great flocks and herds and] possessions made it impossible
        for them to live together [in the same region]; the land in which they lived
        temporarily could not support them because of their livestock. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: Descendants of Esau'
      title: Descendants of Esau
      number: 8
      content: 'So Esau lived in the hill country of Seir; Esau is Edom.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'These are the records of the generations of Esau the father of the
        Edomites in the hill country of Seir. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "These are the names of Esau\u2019s sons: Eliphaz, the son of Adah,
        Esau\u2019s wife, and Reuel, the son of Basemath, Esau\u2019s wife. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And the sons of Eliphaz were Teman, Omar, Zepho, Gatam, and Kenaz. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And Timna was a concubine of Eliphaz, Esau\u2019s son; and she bore
        Amalek to Eliphaz. These are the sons of Adah, Esau\u2019s wife. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "These are the sons of Reuel: Nahath, Zerah, Shammah, and Mizzah.
        These are the sons of Basemath, Esau\u2019s wife. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "And these are the sons of Oholibamah, Esau\u2019s wife, the daughter
        of Anah, the son of Zibeon. She bore to Esau: Jeush, Jalam, and Korah.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'These are the tribal chiefs of the sons of Esau: The sons of Eliphaz,
        the firstborn of Esau: Chiefs Teman, Omar, Zepho, Kenaz, '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Korah, Gatam, and Amalek. These are the chiefs of Eliphaz in the
        land of Edom; they are the sons of Adah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "These are the sons of Reuel, Esau\u2019s son: Chiefs Nahath, Zerah,
        Shammah, Mizzah. These are the chiefs of Reuel in the land of Edom; they
        are the sons of Basemath, Esau\u2019s wife. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "These are the sons of Oholibamah, Esau\u2019s wife: Chiefs Jeush,
        Jalam, and Korah. These are the chiefs born of Oholibamah, daughter of Anah,
        Esau\u2019s wife. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'These are the sons of Esau, (that is, Edom), and these are their
        chiefs.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'These are the sons of Seir the Horite, the inhabitants of the land:
        Lotan, Shobal, Zibeon, Anah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Dishon, Ezer, and Dishan. These are the chiefs of the Horites, the
        sons of Seir in the land of Edom. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "The sons of Lotan are Hori and Hemam; and Lotan\u2019s sister is
        Timna. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'The sons of Shobal are these: Alvan, Manahath, Ebal, Shepho, and
        Onam. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'These are the sons of Zibeon: Aiah and Anah. This is the Anah who
        found the hot springs in the wilderness as he pastured the donkeys of Zibeon
        his father. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "The children of Anah are these: Dishon and Oholibamah [Esau\u2019s
        wife], the daughter of Anah. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'These are the sons of Dishon: Hemdan, Eshban, Ithran, and Cheran. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Ezer\u2019s sons are these: Bilhan, Zaavan, and Akan. "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'The sons of Dishan are these: Uz and Aran. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'The Horite chiefs are these: Chiefs Lotan, Shobal, Zibeon, Anah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Dishon, Ezer, Dishan. These are the Horite chiefs, according to their
        various clans in the land of Seir.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'And these are the kings who reigned in the land of Edom before any
        king reigned over the Israelites: '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'Bela the son of Beor reigned in Edom, and the name of his city was
        Dinhabah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'Now Bela died, and Jobab the son of Zerah of Bozrah reigned as his
        successor. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'Then Jobab died, and Husham of the land of the Temanites reigned
        as his successor. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'And Husham died, and Hadad the son of Bedad, who defeated Midian
        in the country of Moab, reigned as his successor. The name of his [walled]
        city was Avith. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'Hadad died, and Samlah of Masrekah succeeded him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'Then Samlah died, and Shaul of Rehoboth on the river [Euphrates]
        reigned as his successor. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'And Shaul died, and Baal-hanan son of Achbor reigned as his successor. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "Baal-hanan the son of Achbor died, and then Hadar reigned [as his
        successor]. His [walled] city was Pau; his wife\u2019s name was Mehetabel
        the daughter of Matred, the daughter of Mezahab.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'And these are the names of the tribal chiefs of Esau, according to
        their families and places of residence, by their names: Chiefs Timna, Alvah,
        Jetheth, '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'Oholibamah, Elah, Pinon, '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'Kenaz, Teman, Mibzar, '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: Magdiel, and Iram. These are the tribal chiefs of Edom (that is, of
        Esau the father of the Edomites), according to their dwelling places in the
        land of their possession.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Joseph\u2019s Dream"
      title: "Joseph\u2019s Dream"
      number: 1
      content: '  So Jacob (Israel) lived in the land where his father [Isaac] had
        been a stranger (sojourner, resident alien), in the land of Canaan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "These are the generations of Jacob.  Joseph, when he was seventeen
        years old, was shepherding the flock with his brothers [Dan, Naphtali, Gad,
        and Asher]; the boy was with the sons of Bilhah and Zilpah, his father\u2019s
        [secondary] wives; and Joseph brought back a bad report about them to their
        father. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Now Israel (Jacob) loved Joseph more than all his children, because
        he was the son of his old age; and he made him a [distinctive] multicolored
        tunic. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'His brothers saw that their father loved Joseph more than all of
        his brothers; so they hated him and could not [find it within themselves
        to] speak to him on friendly terms.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Now Joseph dreamed a dream, and he told it to his brothers, and they
        hated him even more. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "He said to them, \u201CPlease listen to [the details of] this dream
        which I have dreamed; "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "we [brothers] were binding sheaves [of grain stalks] in the field,
        and lo, my sheaf [suddenly] got up and stood upright and remained standing;
        and behold, your sheaves stood all around my sheaf and bowed down [in respect].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "His brothers said to him, \u201CAre you actually going to reign over
        us? Are you really going to rule and govern us as your subjects?\u201D So
        they hated him even more for [telling them about] his dreams and for his
        [arrogant] words.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "But Joseph dreamed still another dream, and told it to his brothers
        [as well]. He said, \u201CSee here, I have again dreamed a dream, and lo,
        [this time I saw] eleven stars and the sun and the moon bowed down [in respect]
        to me!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "He told it to his father as well as to his brothers; but his father
        rebuked him and said to him [in disbelief], \u201CWhat is [the meaning of]
        this dream that you have dreamed? Shall I and your mother and your brothers
        actually come to bow down to the ground [in respect] before you?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Joseph\u2019s brothers were envious and jealous of him, but his father
        kept the words [of Joseph] in mind [wondering about their meaning].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Then his brothers went to pasture their father\u2019s flock near
        Shechem. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Israel (Jacob) said to Joseph, \u201CAre not your brothers pasturing
        [the flock] at Shechem? Come, and I will send you to them.\u201D And he said,
        \u201CHere I am [ready to obey you].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Then Jacob said to him, \u201CPlease go and see whether everything
        is all right with your brothers and all right with the flock; then bring
        word [back] to me.\u201D So he sent him from the Hebron Valley, and he went
        to Shechem.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Now a certain man found Joseph, and saw that he was wandering around
        and had lost his way in the field; so the man asked him, \u201CWhat are you
        looking for?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "He said, \u201CI am looking for my brothers. Please tell me where
        they are pasturing our flocks.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: The Plot against Joseph'
      title: The Plot against Joseph
      number: 17
      content: "Then the man said, \u201C[They were here, but] they have moved on
        from this place. I heard them say, \u2018Let us go to Dothan.\u2019\u2009\u201D
        So Joseph went after his brothers and found them at Dothan.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And when they saw him from a distance, even before he came close
        to them, they plotted to kill him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "They said to one another, \u201CLook, here comes this dreamer. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Now then, come and let us kill him and throw him into one of the
        pits (cisterns, underground water storage); then we will say [to our father],
        \u2018A wild animal killed and devoured him\u2019; and we shall see what
        will become of his dreams!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Now Reuben [the eldest] heard this and rescued him from their hands
        and said, \u201CLet us not take his life.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Reuben said to them, \u201CDo not shed his blood, but [instead] throw
        him [alive] into the pit that is here in the wilderness, and do not lay a
        hand on him [to kill him]\u201D\u2014[he said this so] that he could rescue
        him from them and return him [safely] to his father. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Now when Joseph reached his brothers, they stripped him of his tunic,
        the [distinctive] multicolored tunic which he was wearing; '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'then they took him and threw him into the pit. Now the pit was empty;
        there was no water in it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Then they sat down to eat their meal. When they looked up, they saw
        a caravan of Ishmaelites coming from Gilead [east of the Jordan], with their
        camels bearing ladanum resin [for perfume] and balm and myrrh, going on their
        way to carry the cargo down to Egypt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Judah said to his brothers, \u201CWhat do we gain if we kill our
        brother and cover up his blood (murder)? "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Come, let us [instead] sell him to these Ishmaelites [and Midianites]
        and not lay our hands on him, because he is our brother and our flesh.\u201D
        So his brothers listened to him and agreed. "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Then as the Midianite [and Ishmaelite] traders were passing by, the
        brothers pulled Joseph up and lifted him out of the pit, and they sold him
        to the Ishmaelites for twenty shekels of silver. And so they took Joseph
        [as a captive] into Egypt.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Now Reuben [unaware of what had happened] returned to the pit, and
        [to his great alarm found that] Joseph was not in the pit; so he tore his
        clothes [in deep sorrow]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "He rejoined his brothers and said, \u201CThe boy is not there; as
        for me, where shall I go [to hide from my father]?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "Then they took Joseph\u2019s tunic, slaughtered a male goat and dipped
        the tunic in the blood; "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "and they brought the multicolored tunic to their father, saying,
        \u201CWe have found this; please examine it and decide whether or not it
        is your son\u2019s tunic.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "He recognized it and said, \u201CIt is my son\u2019s tunic. A wild
        animal has devoured him; Joseph is without doubt torn in pieces!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'So Jacob tore his clothes [in grief], put on sackcloth and mourned
        many days for his son. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "Then all his sons and daughters attempted to console him, but he
        refused to be comforted and said, \u201CI will go down to Sheol (the place
        of the dead) in mourning for my son.\u201D And his father wept for him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: Meanwhile, in Egypt the Midianites sold Joseph [as a slave] to Potiphar,
        an officer of Pharaoh and the captain of the [royal] guard.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Judah and Tamar'
      title: Judah and Tamar
      number: 1
      content: '  Now at that time, Judah left his brothers and went down to [stay
        with] a certain Adullamite named Hirah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'There Judah saw a daughter of Shua, a Canaanite, and he took her
        [as his wife] and lived with her. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'So she conceived and gave birth to a son and Judah named him Er. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Then she conceived again and gave birth to a son and named him Onan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Again she conceived and gave birth to still another son and named
        him Shelah. It was at Chezib that she gave birth to him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Now Judah took a wife for Er his firstborn; her name was Tamar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "But Er, Judah\u2019s firstborn, was evil in the sight of the Lord,
        and the Lord killed him [in judgment]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Then Judah told Onan, \u201CGo in to your brother\u2019s widow, and
        perform your duty as a brother-in-law [under the levirate marriage custom];
        [be her husband and] raise children for [the name of] your brother.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Onan knew that the child (heir) would not be his [but his dead brother\u2019s];
        so whenever he lay with his brother\u2019s widow, he spilled his seed on
        the ground [to prevent conception], so that he would not give a child to
        his brother. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'But what he did was displeasing in the sight of the Lord; therefore
        He killed him also [in judgment]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Then Judah said to Tamar, his daughter-in-law, \u201CRemain a widow
        at your father\u2019s house until Shelah my [youngest] son is grown\u201D;
        [but he was deceiving her] for he thought that [if Shelah should marry her]
        he too might die like his brothers did. So Tamar went and lived in her father\u2019s
        house.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "  But quite a while later, Judah\u2019s wife, the daughter of Shua,
        died; and when the time of mourning was ended, he went up to his sheepshearers
        at Timnah with his friend Hirah the Adullamite. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Tamar was told, \u201CListen, your father-in-law is going up to Timnah
        to shear his sheep.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "So she removed her widow\u2019s clothes and covered herself with
        a veil, and wrapped herself up [in disguise], and sat in the gateway of Enaim,
        which is on the road to Timnah; for she saw that Shelah had grown up, and
        she had not been given to him as a wife [as Judah had promised]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'When Judah saw her, he thought she was a [temple] prostitute, for
        she had covered her face [as such women did]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "He turned to her by the road, and said, \u201CPlease come, let me
        lie with you\u201D; for he did not know that she was his daughter-in-law.
        And she said, \u201CWhat will you give me, that you may lie with me?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "He answered, \u201CI will send you a young goat from the flock.\u201D
        And she said, \u201CWill you give me a pledge [as a deposit] until you send
        it?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "He said, \u201CWhat pledge shall I give you?\u201D She said, \u201CYour
        seal and your cord, and the staff that is in your hand.\u201D So he gave
        them to her and was intimate with her, and she conceived by him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Then she got up and left, and removed her veil and put on her widow\u2019s
        clothing.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'When Judah sent the young goat by his friend the Adullamite, to get
        his pledge [back] from the woman, he was unable to find her. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "He asked the men of that place, \u201CWhere is the temple prostitute
        who was by the roadside at Enaim?\u201D They said, \u201CThere was no prostitute
        here.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "So he returned to Judah, and said, \u201CI cannot find her; also
        the local men said, \u2018There was no prostitute around here.\u2019\u2009\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Then Judah said, \u201CLet her keep the things (pledge articles)
        for herself, otherwise we will be a laughingstock [searching everywhere for
        her]. After all, I sent this young goat, but you did not find her.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "About three months later Judah was told, \u201CTamar your daughter-in-law
        has played the [role of a] prostitute, and she is with child because of her
        immorality.\u201D So Judah said, \u201CBring her out and let her be burned
        [to death as punishment]!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "While she was being brought out, she [took the things Judah had given
        her and] sent [them along with a message] to her father-in-law, saying, \u201CI
        am with child by the man to whom these articles belong.\u201D And she added,
        \u201CPlease examine [them carefully] and see [clearly] to whom these things
        belong, the seal and the cord and staff.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Judah recognized the articles, and said, \u201CShe has been more
        righteous [in this matter] than I, because I did not give her to my son Shelah
        [as I had promised].\u201D And Judah did not have [intimate] relations with
        her again.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Now when the time came for her to give birth, there were twins in
        her womb. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "And when she was in labor, one [baby] put out his hand, and the midwife
        took his hand and tied a scarlet thread on it, saying, \u201CThis one was
        born first.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "But he pulled back his hand, and his brother was born first. And
        she said, \u201CWhat a breach you have made for yourself [to be the firstborn]!\u201D
        So he was named Perez (breach, break forth). "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: Afterward his brother who had the scarlet [thread] on his hand was
        born and was named Zerah (brightness).
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Joseph\u2019s Success in Egypt"
      title: "Joseph\u2019s Success in Egypt"
      number: 1
      content: '  Now Joseph had been taken down to Egypt; and Potiphar, an Egyptian
        officer of Pharaoh, the captain of the [royal] guard, bought him from the
        Ishmaelites, who had taken him down there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'The Lord was with Joseph, and he [even though a slave] became a successful
        and prosperous man; and he was in the house of his master, the Egyptian. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Now his master saw that the Lord was with him and that the Lord caused
        all that he did to prosper (succeed) in his hand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "So Joseph pleased Potiphar and found favor in his sight and he served
        him as his personal servant. He made Joseph overseer over his house, and
        he put all that he owned in Joseph\u2019s charge. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "It happened that from the time that he made Joseph overseer in his
        house and [put him in charge] over all that he owned, that the Lord blessed
        the Egyptian\u2019s house because of Joseph; so the Lord\u2019s blessing
        was on everything that Potiphar owned, in the house and in the field. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "So Potiphar left all that he owned in Joseph\u2019s charge; and with
        Joseph there he did not [need to] pay attention to anything except the food
        he ate.  Now Joseph was handsome and attractive in form and appearance. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Then after a time his master\u2019s wife looked at Joseph with desire,
        and she said, \u201CLie with me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "But he refused and said to his master\u2019s wife, \u201CLook, with
        me in the house, my master does not concern himself with anything; he has
        put everything that he owns in my charge. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "He is not greater in this house than I am, nor has he kept anything
        from me except you, because you are his wife. How then could I do this great
        evil and sin against God [and your husband]?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And so it was that she spoke to Joseph [persistently] day after day,
        but he did not listen to her [plea] to lie beside her or be with her. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Then it happened one day that Joseph went into the house to attend
        to his duties, and none of the men of the household was there in the house. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "She caught Joseph by his [outer] robe, saying, \u201CLie with me!\u201D
        But he left his robe in her hand and ran, and got outside [the house]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'When she saw that he had left his robe in her hand and had run outside, '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "she called to the men of her household and said to them, \u201CLook
        at this, your master has brought a Hebrew [into the household] to mock and
        insult us; he came to me to lie with me, and I screamed. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "When he heard me screaming, he left his robe with me and ran outside
        [the house].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "So she left Joseph\u2019s [outer] robe beside her until his master
        came home. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Then she told her husband the same story, saying, \u201CThe Hebrew
        servant, whom you brought among us, came to me to mock and insult me; "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: Joseph Imprisoned'
      title: Joseph Imprisoned
      number: 18
      content: "then as soon as I raised my voice and screamed, he left his robe
        with me and ran outside [the house].\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "And when Joseph\u2019s master heard the words of his wife, saying,
        \u201CThis is the way your servant treated me,\u201D his anger burned. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "So Joseph\u2019s master took him and put him in the prison, a place
        where the king\u2019s prisoners were confined; so he was there in the prison. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'But the Lord was with Joseph and extended lovingkindness to him,
        and gave him favor in the sight of the warden. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "The warden committed to Joseph\u2019s care (management) all the prisoners
        who were in the prison; so that whatever was done there, he was in charge
        of it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "The warden paid no attention to anything that was in Joseph\u2019s
        care because the Lord was with him; whatever Joseph did, the Lord made to
        prosper."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Joseph Interprets a Dream'
      title: Joseph Interprets a Dream
      number: 1
      content: "  Now some time later, the cupbearer (butler) and the baker for the
        king of Egypt offended their lord, Egypt\u2019s king. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Pharaoh (Sesostris II) was extremely angry with his two officials,
        the chief of the cupbearers and the chief of the bakers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'He put them in confinement in the house of the captain of the guard,
        in the same prison where Joseph was confined. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'The captain of the guard put Joseph in charge of them, and he served
        them; and they continued to be in custody for some time. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Then the cupbearer and the baker of the king of Egypt, who were confined
        in the prison, both dreamed a dream in the same night, each man with his
        [own significant] dream and each dream with its [personal] interpretation. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'When Joseph came to them in the morning and looked at them, [he saw
        that] they were sad and depressed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "So he asked Pharaoh\u2019s officials who were in confinement with
        him in his master\u2019s house, \u201CWhy do you look so down-hearted today?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And they said to him, \u201CWe have [each] dreamed [distinct] dreams
        and there is no one to interpret them.\u201D So Joseph said to them, \u201CDo
        not interpretations belong to God? Please tell me [your dreams].\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "So the chief cupbearer told his dream to Joseph, and said to him,
        \u201CIn my dream there was a grapevine in front of me; "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'and on the vine were three branches. Then as soon as it budded, its
        blossoms burst open, and its clusters produced ripe grapes [in rapid succession]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Now Pharaoh\u2019s cup was in my hand, and I took the grapes and
        squeezed them into Pharaoh\u2019s cup; then I placed the cup into Pharaoh\u2019s
        hand.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Then Joseph said to him, \u201CThis is the interpretation of it:
        the three branches represent three days; "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "within three more days Pharaoh will lift up your head (present you
        in public) and restore you to your position; and you will [again] put Pharaoh\u2019s
        cup into his hand just as [you did] when you were his cupbearer. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Only think of me when it goes well with you, and please show me kindness
        by mentioning me to Pharaoh and get me out of this house. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "For in fact I was taken (stolen) from the land of the Hebrews by
        [unlawful] force, and even here I have done nothing for which they should
        put me in the dungeon.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "When the chief baker saw that the interpretation [of the dream] was
        good, he said to Joseph, \u201CI also dreamed, and [in my dream] there were
        three cake baskets on my head; "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "and in the top basket there were some of all sorts of baked food
        for Pharaoh, but the birds [of prey] were eating [these foods] out of the
        basket on my head.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Joseph answered, \u201CThis is the interpretation of it: the three
        baskets represent three days; "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "within three more days Pharaoh will lift up your head and will hang
        you on a tree (gallows, pole), and [you will not so much as be given a burial,
        but] the birds will eat your flesh.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Now on the third day, [which was] the Pharaoh\u2019s birthday, he
        [released the two men from prison and] made a feast for all his servants;
        and he lifted up the head of the chief cupbearer and the head of the chief
        baker [that is, presented them in public] among his servants. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "He restored the chief cupbearer to his office, and the cupbearer
        [once again] put the cup into Pharaoh\u2019s hand; "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'but Pharaoh hanged the chief baker, just as Joseph had interpreted
        [the meaning of the dreams] to them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: Yet [even after all that] the chief cupbearer did not remember Joseph,
        but forgot [all about] him.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Pharaoh\u2019s Dream"
      title: "Pharaoh\u2019s Dream"
      number: 1
      content: '  Now it happened at the end of two full years that Pharaoh dreamed
        that he was standing by the Nile. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And lo, there came up out of the Nile seven [healthy] cows, sleek
        and handsome and fat; and they grazed in the reed grass [in a marshy pasture]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Then behold, seven other cows came up after them out of the Nile,
        ugly and gaunt and raw-boned, and stood by the fat cows on the bank of the
        Nile. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Then the ugly and gaunt and raw-boned cows ate up the seven sleek
        and fat cows. Then Pharaoh awoke. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Then he fell asleep and dreamed a second time; and behold, seven
        ears of grain came up on a single stalk, plump and good. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Then behold, seven ears [of grain], thin and dried up by the east
        wind, sprouted after them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Then the thin ears swallowed the seven plump and full ears. And Pharaoh
        awoke, and it was a dream. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'So when morning came his spirit was troubled and disturbed and he
        sent and called for all the magicians and all the wise men of Egypt. And
        Pharaoh told them his dreams, but no one could interpret them to him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Then the chief cupbearer spoke to Pharaoh, saying, \u201CI would
        mention my faults today. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: '[Two years ago] Pharaoh was angry with his servants, and he put me
        in confinement in the house of the captain of the guard, both me and the
        chief baker. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'We dreamed a dream on the same night, he and I; each of us dreamed
        according to [the significance of] the interpretation of his own dream. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Now there was with us [in the prison] a young man, a Hebrew, servant
        to the captain of the guard; and we told him, and he interpreted our dreams
        for us, to each man according to the significance of his own dream. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: Joseph Interprets'
      title: Joseph Interprets
      number: 13
      content: "And just as he interpreted [the dreams] for us, so it happened; I
        was restored to my office [as chief cupbearer], and the baker was hanged.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Then Pharaoh sent and called for Joseph, and they hurriedly brought
        him out of the dungeon; and when Joseph shaved himself and changed his clothes
        [making himself presentable], he came to Pharaoh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Pharaoh said to Joseph, \u201CI have dreamed a dream, and there is
        no one who can interpret it; and I have heard it said about you that you
        can understand a dream and interpret it.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Joseph answered Pharaoh, \u201CIt is not in me [to interpret the
        dream]; God [not I] will give Pharaoh a favorable answer [through me].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "So Pharaoh said to Joseph, \u201CIn my dream, I was standing on the
        bank of the Nile; "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'and seven fat, sleek and handsome cows came up out of the river,
        and they grazed in the reed grass [of a marshy pasture]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Lo, seven other cows came up after them, very ugly and gaunt [just
        skin and bones]; such emaciated animals as I have never seen in all the land
        of Egypt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And the lean and ugly cows ate up the first seven fat cows. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Yet when they had devoured them, it could not be detected that they
        had eaten them, because they were still as thin and emaciated as before.
        Then I awoke [but again I fell asleep and dreamed]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'I saw in my [second] dream, seven ears [of grain], plump and good,
        growing on a single stalk; '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'and lo, seven [other] ears, withered, thin, and scorched by the east
        wind, sprouted after them; '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "and the thin ears devoured the seven good ears. Now I told this to
        the magicians and soothsayers, but there was no one who could explain it
        [to me].\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Then Joseph said to Pharaoh, \u201CThe [two] dreams are one [and
        the same and have one interpretation]; God has shown Pharaoh what He is about
        to do. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'The seven good cows are seven years, and the seven good ears are
        seven years; the [two] dreams are one [and the same]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'The seven thin and ugly cows that came up after them are seven years;
        and also the seven thin ears, dried up and scorched by the east wind, they
        are seven years of famine and hunger. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'This is the message just as I have told Pharaoh: God has shown Pharaoh
        what He is about to do. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Listen very carefully: seven years of great abundance will come throughout
        all the land of Egypt; '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'but afterward seven years of famine and hunger will come, and [there
        will be such desperate need that] all the great abundance [of the previous
        years] will be forgotten in the land of Egypt [as if it never happened],
        and famine and destitution will ravage and destroy the land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'So the great abundance will become forgotten in the land because
        of that subsequent famine, for it will be very severe. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'That the dream was repeated twice to Pharaoh [and in two different
        ways] indicates that this matter is fully determined and established by God,
        and God will bring it to pass very quickly. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'So now let Pharaoh [prepare ahead and] look for a man discerning
        and clear-headed and wise, and set him [in charge] over the land of Egypt
        [as governor under Pharaoh]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'Let Pharaoh take action to appoint overseers and officials over the
        land, and set aside one-fifth [of the produce] of the [entire] land of Egypt
        in the seven years of abundance. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'Let them gather [as a tax] all [of the fifth of] the food of these
        good years that are coming, and store up grain under the direction and authority
        of Pharaoh, and let them guard the food [in fortified granaries] in the cities. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "That food shall be put [in storage] as a reserve for the land against
        the seven years of famine and hunger which will occur in the land of Egypt,
        so that the land (people) will not be ravaged during the famine.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: Joseph Is Made a Ruler of Egypt'
      title: Joseph Is Made a Ruler of Egypt
      number: 37
      content: 'Now the plan seemed good to Pharaoh and to all of his servants.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "So Pharaoh said to his servants, \u201CCan we find a man like this
        [a man equal to Joseph], in whom is the divine spirit [of God]?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "Then Pharaoh said to Joseph, \u201CSince [your] God has shown you
        all this, there is no one as discerning and clear-headed and wise as you
        are. "
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "You shall have charge over my house, and all my people shall be governed
        according to your word and pay respect [to you with reverence, submission,
        and obedience]; only in [matters of] the throne will I be greater than you
        [in Egypt].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: "Then Pharaoh said to Joseph, \u201CSee, I have set you [in charge]
        over all the land of Egypt.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: "Then Pharaoh took off his signet ring from his hand and put it on
        Joseph\u2019s hand, and dressed him in [official] vestments of fine linen
        and put a gold chain around his neck. "
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: "He had him ride in his second chariot; and runners proclaimed before
        him, \u201C[Attention,] bow the knee!\u201D And he set him over all the land
        of Egypt. "
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: "Moreover, Pharaoh said to Joseph, \u201CThough I am Pharaoh, yet
        without your permission shall no man raise his hand [to do anything] or set
        his foot [to go anywhere] in all the land of Egypt [all classes of people
        shall submit to your authority].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: 'Then Pharaoh named Joseph Zaphenath-paneah; and he gave him Asenath,
        the daughter of Potiphera, priest of On (Heliopolis in Egypt), as his wife.
        And Joseph went out over all the land of Egypt [to inspect and govern it].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: 'Now Joseph [had been in Egypt thirteen years and] was thirty years
        old when he stood before Pharaoh, king of Egypt. Joseph departed from the
        presence of Pharaoh and went through all the land of Egypt [performing his
        duties]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: 'In the seven abundant years the earth produced handfuls [for each
        seed planted]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: 'And Joseph gathered all the [surplus] food of the seven [good] years
        in the land of Egypt and stored [enormous quantities of] the food in the
        cities. He stored away in every city the food [collected] from its own surrounding
        fields. '
      comments: []
    - name: '49: The Sons of Joseph'
      title: The Sons of Joseph
      number: 49
      content: 'Thus Joseph gathered and stored up grain in great abundance like
        the sand of the sea, until he stopped counting it, for it could not be measured.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: 'Now two sons were born to Joseph before the years of famine came,
        whom Asenath, the daughter of Potiphera, priest of On, bore to him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: "Joseph named the firstborn Manasseh (causing to forget), for he said,
        \u201CGod has made me forget all my trouble and hardship and all [the sorrow
        of the loss of] my father\u2019s household.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '52: '
      title: 
      number: 52
      content: "He named the second [son] Ephraim (fruitfulness), for \u201CGod has
        caused me to be fruitful and very successful in the land of my suffering.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '53: '
      title: 
      number: 53
      content: 'When the seven years of plenty came to an end in the land of Egypt, '
      comments: []
    - name: '54: '
      title: 
      number: 54
      content: 'the seven years of famine began to come, just as Joseph had said
        [they would]; the famine was in all the [surrounding] lands, but in the land
        of Egypt there was bread (food). '
      comments: []
    - name: '55: '
      title: 
      number: 55
      content: "So when all the land of Egypt was famished, the people cried out
        to Pharaoh for food; and Pharaoh said to all the Egyptians, \u201CGo to Joseph;
        do whatever he says to you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '56: '
      title: 
      number: 56
      content: 'When the famine was spread over all the land, Joseph opened all the
        storehouses, and sold [surplus grain] to the Egyptians; and the famine grew
        [extremely] severe in the land of Egypt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '57: '
      title: 
      number: 57
      content: And [the people of] all countries came to Egypt to Joseph to buy grain,
        because the famine was severe over all the [known] earth.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Joseph\u2019s Brothers Sent to Egypt"
      title: "Joseph\u2019s Brothers Sent to Egypt"
      number: 1
      content: "  Now when Jacob (Israel) learned that there was grain in Egypt,
        he said to his sons, \u201CWhy are you staring at one another [in bewilderment
        and not taking action]?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "He said, \u201CI have heard that there is grain in Egypt; go down
        there and buy [some] grain for us, so that we may live and not die [of starvation].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "So ten of Joseph\u2019s brothers went down to buy grain in Egypt. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "But Jacob did not send Benjamin, Joseph\u2019s [younger] brother,
        with his brothers, for he said, \u201CI am afraid that some harm or injury
        may come to him.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'So the sons of Israel came [to Egypt] to buy grain along with the
        others who were coming, for famine was in the land of Canaan also.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Now Joseph was the ruler over the land, and he was the one who sold
        [grain] to all the people of the land; and Joseph\u2019s [half] brothers
        came and bowed down before him with their faces to the ground. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "When Joseph saw his brothers he recognized them, but [hiding his
        identity] he treated them as strangers and spoke harshly to them. He said
        to them, \u201CWhere have you come from?\u201D And they said, \u201CFrom
        the land of Canaan, to buy food.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Joseph recognized his brothers, but they did not recognize him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Joseph remembered the dreams he had dreamed about them, and said
        to them, \u201CYou are spies; you have come [with a malicious purpose] to
        observe the undefended parts of our land.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "But they said to him, \u201CNo, my lord, for your servants have [only]
        come to buy food. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "We are all the sons of one man; we are honest men, your servants
        are not spies.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Yet he said to them, \u201CNo, you have come to see the undefended
        parts of our land.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "But they said, \u201CYour servants are twelve brothers [in all],
        the sons of one man in the land of Canaan; please listen: the youngest is
        with our father today, and one is no longer alive.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Joseph said to them, \u201CIt is as I said to you, you are spies. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'In this way you shall be tested: by the life of Pharaoh, you shall
        not leave this place unless your youngest brother comes here! '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Send one of you [back home], and let him bring your brother [here],
        while [the rest of] you remain confined, so that your words may be tested,
        [to see] whether there is any truth in you [and your story]; or else, by
        the life of Pharaoh, certainly you are spies.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Then Joseph put them all in prison for three days.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Now Joseph said to them on the third day, \u201CDo this and [you
        may] live, for I fear God: "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'if you are honest men, let one of your brothers be confined in your
        [place here in] prison; but as for the rest of you, go, carry grain for the
        famine in your households, '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "but bring your youngest brother to me, so your words will be verified
        and you will not die.\u201D And they did so. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "And they said to one another, \u201CTruly we are guilty regarding
        our brother [Joseph], because we saw the distress and anguish of his soul
        when he pleaded with us [to let him go], yet we would not listen [to his
        cry]; so this distress and anguish has come on us.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Reuben answered them, \u201CDid I not tell you, \u2018Do not sin
        against the boy\u2019; and you would not listen? Now the accounting for his
        blood is required [of us for we are guilty of his death].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'They did not know that Joseph understood [their conversation], because
        he spoke to them through an interpreter. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'He turned away from his brothers and [left the room and] wept; then
        he returned and talked with them, and took Simeon from them and bound him
        in front of them [to be kept as a hostage in Egypt]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Then Joseph gave orders [privately] that their bags be filled with
        grain, and that every man\u2019s money [used to pay for the grain] be put
        back in his sack, and that provisions be given to them for the journey. And
        so this was done for them.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'They loaded their donkeys with grain and left from there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'And at the lodging place, as one of them opened his sack to feed
        his donkey, he saw his money in the opening of his sack. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: The Return to Canaan'
      title: The Return to Canaan
      number: 28
      content: "And he said to his brothers, \u201CMy money has been returned! Here
        it is in my sack!\u201D And their hearts sank, and they were afraid and turned
        trembling to one another, saying, \u201CWhat is this that God has done to
        us?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'When they came to Jacob their father in the land of Canaan, they
        told him everything that had happened to them, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "\u201CThe man who is the lord of the land spoke harshly to us, and
        took us for spies of the land. "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "But we told him, \u2018We are honest men; we are not spies. "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "We are twelve brothers, sons of our father; one is no longer alive,
        and the youngest is with our father today in the land of Canaan.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "And the man, the lord of the country, said to us, \u2018By this [test]
        I will know that you are honest men: leave one of your brothers here with
        me and take grain for your starving households and go. "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "Bring your youngest brother to me; then I will know that you are
        not spies, but that you are honest men. Then I will return your [imprisoned]
        brother [back] to you, and you may trade and do business in the land.\u2019\u2009\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "Now when they emptied their sacks, every man\u2019s bundle of money
        [paid to buy grain] was in his sack. When they and their father saw the bundles
        of money, they were afraid. "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "Jacob their father said to them, \u201CYou have bereaved me [by causing
        the loss] of my children. Joseph is no more, and Simeon is no more, and you
        would take Benjamin [from me]. All these things are [working] against me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "Then Reuben spoke to his father, \u201CYou may put my two sons to
        death if I do not bring Benjamin back to you; put him in my care, and I will
        return him to you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "But Jacob said, \u201CMy son shall not go down [to Egypt] with you;
        for his brother is dead, and he alone is left [of Rachel\u2019s children].
        If any harm or accident should happen to him on the journey you are taking,
        then you will bring my gray hair down to Sheol (the place of the dead) in
        sorrow.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Return to Egypt'
      title: The Return to Egypt
      number: 1
      content: '  Now the famine was very severe in the land [of Canaan]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And it happened that when the families of Jacob\u2019s sons had finished
        eating [all of] the grain which they had brought from Egypt, their father
        said to them, \u201CGo again, buy us a little food.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "But Judah said to him, \u201CThe man [representing Pharaoh] solemnly
        and sternly warned us, saying, \u2018You will not see my face [again] unless
        your brother is with you.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'If you will send our brother with us, we will go down [to Egypt]
        and buy you food. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "But if you will not send him, we will not go down there; for the
        man said to us, \u2018You will not see my face unless your brother is with
        you.\u2019\u2009\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And Israel (Jacob) said, \u201CWhy did you treat me so badly by telling
        the man that you had another brother?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And they said, \u201CThe man asked us straightforward questions about
        ourselves and our relatives. He said, \u2018Is your father still alive? Have
        you another brother?\u2019 And we answered him accordingly. How could we
        possibly know that he would say, \u2018Bring your brother down [here to Egypt]\u2019?\u2009\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Judah said to Israel his father, \u201CSend the young man with me
        and we will get up and go [buy food], so that we may live and not die [of
        starvation], we as well as you and our little ones. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'I will be security (a guarantee) for him; you may hold me [personally]
        responsible for him. If I do not bring him [back] to you and place him [safely]
        before you, then let me bear the blame before you forever. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "For if we had not delayed like this, surely by now we would have
        returned the second time.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Then their father Israel said to them, \u201CIf it must be so, then
        do this; take some of the choicest products of the land in your sacks, and
        carry it as a present [of tribute] to the man [representing Pharaoh], a little
        balm and a little honey, aromatic spices or gum, resin, pistachio nuts, and
        almonds. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Take double the [amount of] money with you, and take back the money
        that was returned in the opening of your sacks; perhaps it was an oversight. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Take your brother [Benjamin] also, and get up, and go to the man; '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "and may God Almighty grant you compassion and favor before the man,
        so that he will release to you your other brother [Simeon] and Benjamin.
        And as for me, if I am bereaved of my children [Joseph, Simeon, and Benjamin],
        I am bereaved.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: Joseph Sees Benjamin'
      title: Joseph Sees Benjamin
      number: 15
      content: 'Then the men took the present, and they took double the [amount of]
        money with them, and Benjamin; then they left and went down to Egypt and
        stood before Joseph.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "When Joseph saw Benjamin with them, he said to the steward of his
        house, \u201CBring the men into the house, and kill an animal and make [a
        meal] ready; for the men will dine with me at noon.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "So the man did as Joseph said, and brought the men to Joseph\u2019s
        house. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "The men were afraid, because they were brought to Joseph\u2019s house;
        and [expecting the worst] they said, \u201CIt is because of the money that
        was returned in our sacks the first time [we came] that we are being brought
        in, so that he may find a reason to accuse us and assail us, and take us
        as slaves, and seize our donkeys.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "So they approached the steward of Joseph\u2019s house, and talked
        with him at the entrance of the house, "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "and said, \u201COh, my lord, we indeed came down here the first time
        to buy food; "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "and when we arrived at the inn [after leaving here], we opened our
        sacks and there was each man\u2019s money [with which he had paid for grain],
        in full, returned in the mouth of his sack. So we have brought it back [this
        time]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "We have also brought down with us additional money to buy food; we
        do not know who put our money [back] in our sacks [last time].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "But the steward [encouraged them and] said, \u201CPeace be to you,
        do not be afraid; your God and the God of your father has [miraculously]
        given you treasure in your sacks. I [already] had your money [which you paid
        to us].\u201D Then he brought Simeon out to them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Then the steward brought the men into Joseph\u2019s house and gave
        them water, and they washed [the dust off] their feet; and he gave their
        donkeys feed. "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'So they prepared the present [of tribute] for Joseph before his arrival
        at noon; for they had heard that they were to eat a meal there.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'When Joseph came home, they brought into the house to him the present
        [of tribute] which they had with them and bowed to the ground before him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "He asked them about their well-being, and said, \u201CIs your old
        father well, of whom you spoke? Is he still alive?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "And they answered, \u201CYour servant our father is in good health;
        he is still alive.\u201D And they bowed down [their heads before Joseph]
        in respect. "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "And he looked up and saw his brother Benjamin, his mother\u2019s
        [only other] son, and said, \u201CIs this your youngest brother, of whom
        you spoke to me?\u201D And Joseph said, \u201CGod be gracious to you and
        show you favor, my son.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Then Joseph hurried out [of the room] because his heart was deeply
        touched over his brother, and he sought privacy to weep; so he entered his
        chamber and wept there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "Then he washed his face and came out, and, restraining himself, said,
        \u201CLet the meal be served.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'So the servants served Joseph by himself [in honor of his rank],
        and his brothers by themselves, and the Egyptians who ate with him by themselves,
        because [according to custom] the Egyptians could not eat food with the Hebrews,
        for that is loathsome to the Egyptians. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "Now Joseph\u2019s brothers were seated [by the steward] before him
        [in the order of their birth]\u2014the firstborn according to his birthright
        and the youngest according to his youth; and the men looked at one another
        in astonishment [because so much was known about them]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "Joseph selected and sent portions to them from his own table, but
        Benjamin\u2019s portion was five times as much as any of theirs. So they
        feasted and drank freely and celebrated with him."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Brothers Are Brought Back'
      title: The Brothers Are Brought Back
      number: 1
      content: "  And he commanded the steward of his house, saying, \u201CFill the
        men\u2019s sacks with food, as much as they can carry, and put every man\u2019s
        [grain] money in the mouth of the sack. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Put my [personal] cup, the silver cup, in the mouth of the sack of
        the youngest, with his grain money.\u201D And the steward did as Joseph had
        told him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'As soon as the morning was light, the men were sent away, they and
        their donkeys. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "When they had left the city, and were not yet far away, Joseph said
        to his steward, \u201CGet up, follow after the men; and when you overtake
        them, say to them, \u2018Why have you repaid evil [to us] for good [paid
        to you]? "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Is this not my lord\u2019s drinking cup and the one which he uses
        for divination? You have done [a great and unforgivable] wrong in doing this.\u2019\u2009\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'So the steward overtook them and he said these words to them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "They said to him, \u201CWhy does my lord speak these things? Far
        be it from your servants to do such a thing! "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Please remember, the money which we found in the mouths of our sacks
        we have brought back to you from the land of Canaan. Is it likely then that
        we would steal silver or gold from your master\u2019s house? "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "With whomever of your servants your master\u2019s cup is found, let
        him die, and the rest of us will be my lord\u2019s slaves.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And the steward said, \u201CNow let it be as you say; he with whom
        the cup is found will be my slave, but the rest of you shall be blameless.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Then every man quickly lowered his sack to the ground and each man
        opened his sack [confident the cup would not be found among them]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "The steward searched, beginning with the eldest and ending with the
        youngest, and the cup was found in Benjamin\u2019s sack. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Then they tore their clothes [in grief]; and after each man had loaded
        his donkey again, they returned to the city.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "When Judah and his brothers came to Joseph\u2019s house, he was still
        there; and they fell to the ground before him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Joseph spoke harshly to them, \u201CWhat is this thing that you have
        done? Do you not realize that such a man as I can indeed practice divination
        and foretell [everything you do without outside knowledge of it]?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "So Judah said, \u201CWhat can we say to my lord? What can we reply?
        Or how can we clear ourselves, since God has exposed the sin and guilt of
        your servants? Behold, we are my lord\u2019s slaves, the rest of us as well
        as he with whom the cup is found.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "But Joseph said, \u201CFar be it from me that I should do that; but
        the man in whose hand the cup has been found, he will be my servant; and
        as for [the rest of] you, get up and go in peace to your father.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Then Judah approached him, and said, \u201CO my lord, please let
        your servant say a word to you in private, and do not let your anger blaze
        against your servant, for you are equal to Pharaoh [so I speak as if directly
        to him]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "My lord asked his servants, saying, \u2018Have you a father or a
        brother?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "We said to my lord, \u2018We have an old father and a young [brother,
        Benjamin, the] child of his old age. Now his brother [Joseph] is dead, and
        he alone is left of [the two sons born of] his mother, and his father loves
        him.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Then you said to your servants, \u2018Bring him down to me that I
        may actually see him.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "But we said to my lord, \u2018The young man cannot leave his father,
        for if he should leave his father, his father would die.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "You said to your servants, \u2018Unless your youngest brother comes
        with you, you shall not see my face again.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'So when we went back to your servant my father, we told him what
        my lord had said. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Our father said, \u2018Go back [to Egypt], and buy us a little food.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "But we said, \u2018We cannot go down [to Egypt]. If our youngest
        brother is with us, then we will go down [there]; for we [were sternly told
        that we] cannot see the man\u2019s face unless our youngest brother is with
        us.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Your servant my father said to us, \u2018You know that my wife [Rachel]
        bore me [only] two sons. "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "And one [son] went out from me, and I said, \u201CSurely he is torn
        to pieces,\u201D and I have not seen him since. "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "If you take this one also from me, and harm or an accident happens
        to him, you will bring my gray hair down to Sheol in sorrow.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "Now, therefore, when I come to your servant my father, and the young
        man is not with us, since his life is bound up in the young man\u2019s life, "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'when he sees that the young man is not with us, he will die; and
        your servants will bring the gray hair of your servant our father down to
        Sheol in [great] sorrow. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "For your servant became security for the young man to my father,
        saying, \u2018If I do not bring him back to you, then let me bear the blame
        before my father forever.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'Now, therefore, please let your servant (Judah) remain here instead
        of the youth [to be] a slave to my lord, and let the young man go home with
        his brothers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "How can I go up to my father if the young man is not with me\u2014for
        fear that I would see the tragedy that would overtake my [elderly] father
        [if Benjamin does not return]?\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Joseph Shows Kindness to His Brothers'
      title: Joseph Shows Kindness to His Brothers
      number: 1
      content: "  Then Joseph could not control himself [any longer] in front of
        all those who attended him, and he called out, \u201CHave everyone leave
        me.\u201D So no man stood there when Joseph revealed himself to his brothers. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Joseph wept aloud, and the Egyptians [who had just left him] heard
        it, and the household of Pharaoh heard of it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Then Joseph said to his brothers, \u201CI am Joseph! Is my father
        still alive?\u201D But his brothers were speechless, for they were stunned
        and dismayed by [the fact that they were in] Joseph\u2019s presence.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And Joseph said to his brothers, \u201CPlease come closer to me.\u201D
        And they approached him. And he said, \u201CI am Joseph your brother, whom
        you sold into Egypt. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Now do not be distressed or angry with yourselves because you sold
        me here, for God sent me ahead of you to save life and preserve our family. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'For the famine has been in the land these two years, and there are
        still five more years in which there will be no plowing and harvesting. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'God sent me [to Egypt] ahead of you to preserve for you a remnant
        on the earth, and to keep you alive by a great escape. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'So now it was not you who sent me here, but God; and He has made
        me a father to Pharaoh and lord of all his household and ruler over all the
        land of Egypt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Hurry and go up to my father, and tell him, \u2018Your son Joseph
        says this to you: \u201CGod has made me lord of all Egypt; come down to me,
        do not delay. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "You shall live in the land of Goshen [the best pasture land of Egypt],
        and you shall be close to me\u2014you and your children and your grandchildren,
        your flocks and your herds and all you have. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "There I will provide for you and sustain you, so that you and your
        household and all that are yours may not become impoverished, for there are
        still five years of famine to come.\u201D\u2009\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Look! Your eyes see, and the eyes of my brother Benjamin see, that
        I am speaking to you [personally in your language and not through an interpreter]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Now you must tell my father of all my splendor and power in Egypt,
        and of everything that you have seen; and you must hurry and bring my father
        down here.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Then he embraced his brother Benjamin\u2019s neck and wept, and Benjamin
        wept on his neck. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'He kissed all his brothers and wept on them, and afterward his brothers
        talked with him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "When the news was heard in Pharaoh\u2019s house that Joseph\u2019s
        brothers had come, it pleased Pharaoh and his servants. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Then Pharaoh said to Joseph, \u201CTell your brothers, \u2018Do this:
        load your animals and return to the land of Canaan [without delay], "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "and get your father and your households and come to me. I will give
        you the best of the land of Egypt and you will eat the fat (the finest produce)
        of the land.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Now you [brothers of Joseph] are ordered [by Pharaoh], \u2018Do this:
        take wagons from the land of Egypt for your little ones and for your wives,
        and bring your father and come. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Do not be concerned with your goods, for the best of all the land
        of Egypt is yours.\u2019\u2009\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Then the sons of Israel did so; and Joseph gave them wagons according
        to the command of Pharaoh, and gave them provisions for the journey. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'To each of them Joseph gave changes of clothing, but to Benjamin
        he gave three hundred pieces of silver and five changes of clothing. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'To his father he sent the following: ten male donkeys loaded with
        the good things of Egypt, and ten female donkeys loaded with grain and bread
        and provision for his father [to supply all who were with him] on the journey.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "So he sent his brothers away, and as they departed, he said to them,
        \u201CSee that you do not quarrel on the journey [about how to explain this
        to our father].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'So they went up from Egypt, and came to the land of Canaan to Jacob
        their father, '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "and they said to him, \u201CJoseph is still alive, and indeed he
        is ruler over all the land of Egypt.\u201D But Jacob was stunned and his
        heart almost stopped beating, because he did not believe them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'When they told him everything that Joseph had said to them, and when
        he saw the wagons which Joseph had sent to carry him, the spirit of their
        father Jacob revived. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "And Israel (Jacob) said, \u201CIt is enough! Joseph my son is still
        alive. I will go and see him before I die.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jacob Moves to Egypt'
      title: Jacob Moves to Egypt
      number: 1
      content: '  So Israel set out with all that he had, and came to Beersheba [where
        both his father and grandfather had worshiped God], and offered sacrifices
        to the God of his father Isaac. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And God spoke to Israel in visions of the night and said, \u201CJacob,
        Jacob!\u201D And he said, \u201CHere I am.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And He said, \u201CI am God, the God of your father; do not be afraid
        to go down to Egypt, for I will make you (your descendants) a great nation
        there. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "I will go down with you to Egypt, and I will also surely bring you
        (your people) up again; and Joseph will put his hand on your eyes [to close
        them at the time of your death].\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'So Jacob set out from Beersheba; and the sons of Israel carried their
        father Jacob and their children and their wives in the wagons that Pharaoh
        had sent to carry him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And they took their livestock and the possessions which they had
        acquired in the land of Canaan and came to Egypt, Jacob and all his descendants
        with him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: Those Who Came to Egypt'
      title: Those Who Came to Egypt
      number: 7
      content: 'His sons and his grandsons, his daughters and his granddaughters,
        and all his descendants he brought with him to Egypt.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Now these are the names of the sons of Israel, Jacob and his sons,
        who went to Egypt: Reuben, Jacob\u2019s firstborn. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'The sons of Reuben: Hanoch, Pallu, Hezron, and Carmi. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'The sons of Simeon: Jemuel, Jamin, Ohad, Jachin, Zohar, and Shaul
        the son of a Canaanite woman. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'The sons of Levi: Gershon, Kohath, and Merari. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "The sons of Judah: Er, Onan, Shelah, Perez, and Zerah\u2014but Er
        and Onan died in the land of Canaan. And the sons of Perez were Hezron and
        Hamul. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'The sons of Issachar: Tola, Puvah, Job, and Shimron. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'The sons of Zebulun: Sered, Elon, and Jahleel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'These are the sons of Leah, whom she bore to Jacob in Paddan-aram,
        with his daughter Dinah; all of his sons and daughters numbered thirty-three. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'The sons of Gad: Ziphion, Haggi, Shuni, Ezbon, Eri, Arodi, and Areli. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'The sons of Asher: Imnah, Ishvah, Ishvi, Beriah, and Serah their
        sister. And the sons of Beriah: Heber and Malchiel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'These are the sons of Zilpah, [the maid] whom Laban gave to Leah
        his daughter [when she married Jacob]; and she bore to Jacob these sixteen
        persons [two sons and fourteen grandchildren]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "The sons of Rachel, Jacob\u2019s wife: Joseph and Benjamin. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Now to Joseph in the land of Egypt were born Manasseh and Ephraim,
        whom Asenath, the daughter of Potiphera, priest of On (Heliopolis in Egypt),
        bore to him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And the sons of Benjamin: Bela, Becher, Ashbel, Gera, Naaman, Ehi,
        Rosh, Muppim, Huppim, and Ard. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'These are the sons of Rachel, who were born to Jacob; [there were]
        fourteen persons in all [two sons and twelve grandchildren]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'The son of Dan: Hushim. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'The sons of Naphtali: Jahzeel, Guni, Jezer, and Shillem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'These are the sons of Bilhah, [the maid] whom Laban gave to Rachel
        his daughter [when she married Jacob]. And she bore these to Jacob; [there
        were] seven persons in all [two sons and five grandchildren]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "All the persons who came with Jacob into Egypt\u2014who were his
        direct descendants, not counting the wives of [Jacob or] Jacob\u2019s sons,
        were sixty-six persons in all, "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'and the sons of Joseph, who were born to him in Egypt, were two.
        All the persons of the house of Jacob [including Jacob, and Joseph and his
        sons], who came into Egypt, were seventy.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Now Jacob (Israel) sent Judah ahead of him to Joseph, to direct him
        to Goshen; and they came into the land of Goshen. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Then Joseph prepared his chariot and went up to meet Israel his father
        in Goshen; as soon as he presented himself before him (authenticating his
        identity), he fell on his [father\u2019s] neck and wept on his neck a [very]
        long time. "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "And Israel said to Joseph, \u201CNow let me die [in peace], since
        I have seen your face [and know] that you are still alive.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "Joseph said to his brothers and to his father\u2019s household, \u201CI
        will go up and tell Pharaoh, and say to him, \u2018My brothers and my father\u2019s
        household, who were in the land of Canaan, have come to me; "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "and the men are shepherds, for they have been keepers of livestock;
        and they have brought their flocks and their herds and all that they have.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "And it shall be that when Pharaoh calls you and says, \u2018What
        is your occupation?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "you shall say, \u2018Your servants have been keepers of livestock
        from our youth until now, both we and our fathers [before us],\u2019 in order
        that you may live [separately and securely] in the land of Goshen; for every
        shepherd is repulsive to the Egyptians.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Jacob\u2019s Family Settles in Goshen"
      title: "Jacob\u2019s Family Settles in Goshen"
      number: 1
      content: "  Then Joseph came and told Pharaoh, \u201CMy father and my brothers,
        with their flocks and their herds and all that they own, have come from the
        land of Canaan, and they are in the land of Goshen.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'He took five men from among his brothers and presented them to Pharaoh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And Pharaoh said to his brothers [as Joseph expected], \u201CWhat
        is your occupation?\u201D And they said to Pharaoh, \u201CYour servants are
        shepherds, both we and our fathers [before us].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Moreover, they said to Pharaoh, \u201CWe have come to live temporarily
        (sojourn) in the land [of Egypt], for there is no pasture for the flocks
        of your servants [in our land], for the famine is very severe in Canaan.
        So now, please let your servants live in the land of Goshen.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then Pharaoh spoke to Joseph, saying, \u201CYour father and your
        brothers have come to you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "The land of Egypt is before you; settle your father and your brothers
        in the best of the land. Let them live in the land of Goshen; and if you
        know of any men of ability among them, put them in charge of my livestock.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Then Joseph brought Jacob (Israel) his father and presented him before
        Pharaoh; and Jacob blessed Pharaoh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And Pharaoh asked Jacob, \u201CHow old are you?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Jacob said to Pharaoh, \u201CThe years of my pilgrimage are a hundred
        and thirty. Few and unpleasant have been the years of my life, and they have
        not reached the years that my fathers lived during the days of their pilgrimage.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And Jacob blessed Pharaoh, and departed from his presence. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'So Joseph settled his father and brothers and gave them a possession
        in Egypt, in the best of the land, in the land of Rameses (Goshen), as Pharaoh
        commanded. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Joseph provided and supplied his father and his brothers and all
        his father\u2019s household with food, according to [the needs of] their
        children.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Now [in the course of time] there was no food in all the land, for
        the famine was distressingly severe, so that the land of Egypt and all the
        land of Canaan languished [in destitution and starvation] because of the
        famine. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Joseph gathered all the money that was found in the land of Egypt
        and in the land of Canaan [in payment] for the grain which they bought, and
        Joseph brought the money into Pharaoh\u2019s house. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And when the money was exhausted in the land of Egypt and in the
        land of Canaan, all the Egyptians came to Joseph and said, \u201CGive us
        food! Why should we die before your very eyes? For our money is gone.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Joseph said, \u201CGive up your livestock, and I will give you food
        in exchange for your livestock, since the money is gone.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'So they brought their livestock to Joseph, and he gave them food
        in exchange for the horses and the flocks and the herds and the donkeys;
        and he supplied them with food in exchange for all their livestock that year. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "When that year was ended, they came to him the next year and said
        to him, \u201CWe will not hide from my lord [the fact] that our money is
        spent; my lord also has our herds of livestock; there is nothing left in
        the sight of my lord but our bodies and our lands. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: Result of the Famine'
      title: Result of the Famine
      number: 19
      content: "Why should we die before your eyes, both we and our land? Buy us
        and our land in exchange for food, and we and our land will be servants to
        Pharaoh. And give us seed [to plant], that we may live and not die, and that
        the land may not be desolate.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "So Joseph bought all the land of Egypt for Pharaoh; for every Egyptian
        sold his field because the famine was severe upon them. So the land became
        Pharaoh\u2019s. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "And as for the people, he relocated them [temporarily] to cities
        from one end of Egypt\u2019s border to the other. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Only the land of the priests he did not buy, for the priests had
        an allotment from Pharaoh, and they lived on the amount which Pharaoh gave
        them, so they did not sell their land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Then Joseph said to the people, \u201CLook, today I have bought you
        and your land for Pharaoh; now, here is seed for you, and you shall plant
        the land. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "At harvest time [when you reap the increase] you shall give one-fifth
        of it to Pharaoh, and four-fifths will be your own to use for seed for the
        field and as food for you and those of your households and for your little
        ones.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "And they said, \u201CYou have saved our lives! Let us find favor
        in the sight of my lord, and we will be Pharaoh\u2019s servants.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "And Joseph made it a law over the land of Egypt\u2014valid to this
        day\u2014that Pharaoh should have the fifth part [of the crops]; only the
        land of the priests did not become Pharaoh\u2019s.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Now [the people of] Israel lived in the country of Egypt, in [the
        land of] Goshen, and they gained possessions and acquired property there
        and were fruitful and multiplied greatly. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "And Jacob lived in the land of Egypt seventeen years; so the length
        of Jacob\u2019s life was a hundred and forty-seven years.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "And when the time drew near for Israel to die, he called his son
        Joseph and said to him, \u201CIf now I have found favor in your sight, please
        put your hand under my thigh and [promise to] deal loyally and faithfully
        with me. Please do not bury me in Egypt, "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "but when I lie down with my fathers [in death], you will carry me
        out of Egypt and bury me in their burial place [at Hebron in the cave of
        Machpelah].\u201D And Joseph said, \u201CI will do as you have directed.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "Then he said, \u201CSwear to me [that you will do it].\u201D So he
        swore to him. Then Israel (Jacob) bowed in worship at the head of the bed."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Israel\u2019s Last Days"
      title: "Israel\u2019s Last Days"
      number: 1
      content: "  Now some time after these things happened, Joseph was told, \u201CYour
        father is sick.\u201D So he took his two sons Manasseh and Ephraim with him
        [to go to Goshen]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And when Jacob (Israel) was told, \u201CLook now, your son Joseph
        has come to you,\u201D Israel strengthened himself and sat up on the bed. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Then Jacob said to Joseph, \u201CGod Almighty appeared to me at Luz
        (Bethel) in the land of Canaan and blessed me, "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "and said to me, \u2018Behold, I will make you fruitful and numerous,
        and I will make you a great company of people, and will give this land to
        your descendants after you as an everlasting possession.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Now your two sons [Ephraim and Manasseh], who were born to you in
        the land of Egypt before I came to you in Egypt, are mine; Ephraim and Manasseh
        shall be mine [that is, adopted as my heirs and sons as surely], as Reuben
        and Simeon are my sons. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'But other sons who were born to you after them shall be your own;
        they shall be called by the names of their [two] brothers in their inheritance. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Now as for me, when I came from Paddan [in Mesopotamia], Rachel died
        beside me in the land of Canaan on the journey, when there was still some
        distance to go to Ephrath; and I buried her there on the way to Ephrath (that
        is, Bethlehem).\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "When Israel [who was almost blind] saw Joseph\u2019s sons, he said,
        \u201CWho are these?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Joseph said to his father, \u201CThey are my sons, whom God has given
        me here [in Egypt].\u201D So he said, \u201CPlease bring them to me, so that
        I may bless them.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Now Israel\u2019s eyes were so dim from age that he could not see
        [clearly]. Then Joseph brought them close to him, and he kissed and embraced
        them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Israel said to Joseph, \u201CI never expected to see your face, but
        see, God has shown me your children as well.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Then Joseph took the boys [from his father\u2019s embrace], and he
        bowed [before him] with his face to the ground. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Then Joseph took them both, Ephraim with his right hand toward Israel\u2019s
        left, and Manasseh with his left hand toward Israel\u2019s right, and brought
        them close to him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "But Israel reached out his right hand and laid it on the head of
        Ephraim, who was the younger, and his left hand on Manasseh\u2019s head,
        crossing his hands [intentionally], even though Manasseh was the firstborn. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Then Jacob (Israel) blessed Joseph, and said,\u201CThe God before
        whom my fathers Abraham and Isaac walked [in faithful obedience],The God
        who has been my Shepherd [leading and caring for me] all my life to this
        day,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "The Angel [that is, the Lord Himself] who has redeemed me [continually]
        from all evil,Bless the boys;And may my name live on in them [may they be
        worthy of having their names linked with mine],And the names of my fathers
        Abraham and Isaac;And may they grow into a [great] multitude in the midst
        of the earth.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "When Joseph saw that his father laid his right hand on Ephraim\u2019s
        head, it displeased him [because he was not the firstborn]; and he grasped
        his father\u2019s hand to move it from Ephraim\u2019s head to Manasseh\u2019s
        head. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Joseph said to his father, \u201CNot so, my father, for this is the
        firstborn; place your right hand on Manasseh\u2019s head.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "But his father refused and said, \u201CI know, my son, I know; Manasseh
        also will become a people and he will be great; but his younger brother shall
        be greater than he, and his descendants shall become a multitude of nations.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Then Jacob blessed them that day, saying,\u201CBy you Israel will
        pronounce a blessing, saying,\u2018May God make you like Ephraim and Manasseh.\u2019\u2009\u201DAnd
        he put Ephraim before Manasseh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Then Israel said to Joseph, \u201CBehold, I am about to die, but
        God will be with you, and bring you back to [Canaan] the land of your fathers. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Moreover, I have given you [the birthright,] one portion [Shechem,
        one mountain ridge] more than any of your brothers, which I took [reclaiming
        it] from the hand of the Amorites with my sword and with my bow.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Israel\u2019s Prophecy concerning His Sons"
      title: "Israel\u2019s Prophecy concerning His Sons"
      number: 1
      content: "  Then Jacob called for his sons and said, \u201CAssemble yourselves
        [around me] that I may tell you what will happen to you and your descendants
        in the days to come.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Gather together and hear, O sons of Jacob;And listen to Israel (Jacob)
        your father.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u201CReuben, you are my firstborn;My might, the beginning of my
        strength and vigor,Preeminent in dignity and preeminent in power [that should
        have been your birthright].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "But unstable and reckless and boiling over like water [in sinful
        lust], you shall not excel or have the preeminence [of the firstborn],Because
        you went up to your father\u2019s bed [with Bilhah];You defiled it\u2014he
        went up to my couch.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CSimeon and Levi are brothers [equally headstrong, deceitful,
        vindictive, and cruel];Their swords are weapons of violence and revenge.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'O my soul, do not come into their secret council;Let not my glory
        (honor) be united with their assembly [for I knew nothing of their plot];Because
        in their anger they killed men [an honored man, Shechem, and the Shechemites],And
        in their self-will they lamed oxen.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Cursed be their anger, for it was fierce;And their wrath, for it
        was cruel.I will divide and disperse them in Jacob,And scatter them in [the
        midst of the land of] Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CJudah, you are the one whom your brothers shall praise;Your
        hand will be on the neck of your enemies;Your father\u2019s sons shall bow
        down to you.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Judah, a lion\u2019s cub;With the prey, my son, you have gone high
        up [the mountain].He stooped down, he crouched like a lion,And like a lion\u2014who
        dares rouse him?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "The scepter [of royalty] shall not depart from Judah,Nor the ruler\u2019s
        staff from between his feet,Until Shiloh [the Messiah, the Peaceful One]
        comes,And to Him shall be the obedience of the peoples.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Tying his foal to the [strong] vineAnd his donkey\u2019s colt to
        the choice vine,He washes his clothing in wine [because the grapevine produces
        abundantly],And his robes in the blood of grapes.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'His eyes are darker and sparkle more than wine,And his teeth whiter
        than milk.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CZebulun shall dwell at the seashore;And he shall be a haven
        (landing place) for ships,And his flank shall be toward Sidon.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CIssachar is [like] a strong-boned donkey,Crouching down between
        the sheepfolds.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'When he saw that the resting place was goodAnd that the land was
        pleasant,He bowed his shoulder to bear [burdens],And became a servant at
        forced labor.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CDan shall judge his people,As one of the tribes of Israel.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Dan shall be a [venomous] serpent in the way,A fanged snake in the
        path,That bites the horse\u2019s heels,So that his rider falls backward.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'I wait for Your salvation, O Lord.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "\u201CAs for Gad\u2014a raiding troop shall raid him,But he shall
        raid at their heels and assault them [victoriously].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "\u201CAsher\u2019s food [supply] shall be rich and bountiful,And
        he shall yield and deliver royal delights.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "\u201CNaphtali is a doe let loose, [a swift warrior,]Which yields
        branched antlers (eloquent words).  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "\u201CJoseph is a fruitful bough (a main branch of the vine),A fruitful
        bough by a spring (a well, a fountain);Its branches run over the wall [influencing
        others].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'The [skilled] archers have bitterly attacked and provoked him;They
        have shot [at him] and harassed him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'But his bow remained firm and steady [in the Strength that does not
        fail],For his arms were made strong and agileBy the hands of the Mighty One
        of Jacob,(By the name of the Shepherd, the Stone of Israel),  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'By the God of your father who will help you,And by the Almighty who
        blesses youWith blessings of the heavens above,Blessings lying in the deep
        that couches beneath,Blessings of the [nursing] breasts and of the [fertile]
        womb.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'The blessings of your fatherAre greater than the blessings of my
        ancestors [Abraham and Isaac]Up to the utmost bound of the everlasting hills;They
        shall be on the head of Joseph,Even on the crown of the head of him who was
        the distinguished one and the one who is prince among (separate from) his
        brothers.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "\u201CBenjamin is a ravenous wolf;In the morning he devours the prey,And
        at night he divides the spoil.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'All these are the [beginnings of the] twelve tribes of Israel, and
        this is what their father said to them as he blessed them, blessing each
        one according to the blessing appropriate to him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "He charged them and said to them, \u201CI am to be gathered to my
        people; bury me with my fathers in the cave that is in the field of Ephron
        the Hittite, "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'in the cave in the field at Machpelah, east of Mamre, in the land
        of Canaan, that Abraham bought, along with the field from Ephron the Hittite,
        to possess as a burial site. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "There they buried Abraham and Sarah his wife, there they buried Isaac
        and Rebekah his wife, and there I buried Leah\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "the field and the cave that is in it was purchased from the sons
        of Heth.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: When Jacob (Israel) had finished commanding his sons, he drew his
        feet into the bed and breathed his last, and was gathered to his people [who
        had preceded him in death].
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Burial Preparations and Mourning for Jacob'
      title: Burial Preparations and Mourning for Jacob
      number: 1
      content: "  Then Joseph fell upon his father\u2019s face, and wept over him
        and kissed him [tenderly]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Then Joseph ordered his servants the physicians to embalm (mummify)
        his father. So the physicians embalmed Israel (Jacob). '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Now forty days were required for this, for that is the customary
        number of days [of preparation] required for embalming. And the Egyptians
        wept and grieved for him [in public mourning as they would for royalty] for
        seventy days.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "When the days of weeping and public mourning for him were past, Joseph
        spoke to [the nobles of] the house of Pharaoh, saying, \u201CIf now I have
        found favor in your sight, please speak to Pharaoh, saying, "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u2018My father made me swear [an oath], saying, \u201CHear me, I
        am about to die; bury me in my tomb which I prepared for myself in the land
        of Canaan.\u201D So now let me go up [to Canaan], please, and bury my father;
        then I will return.\u2019\u2009\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And Pharaoh said, \u201CGo up and bury your father, as he made you
        swear.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "So Joseph went up [to Canaan] to bury his father, and with him went
        all the officials of Pharaoh, [the nobles of his court and] the elders of
        his household and all [the nobles and] the elders of the land of Egypt\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "and all the household of Joseph and his brothers and his father\u2019s
        household. They left only their little ones and their flocks and herds in
        the land of Goshen. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Both chariots and horsemen also went up [to Canaan] with Joseph;
        and it was a very great company. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'When they came to the threshing floor of Atad, which is beyond the
        Jordan, they mourned there with a great lamentation (expressions of mourning
        for the deceased) and [extreme demonstrations of] sorrow [according to Egyptian
        custom]; and Joseph observed a seven-day mourning for his father. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: Burial at Machpelah'
      title: Burial at Machpelah
      number: 11
      content: "When the inhabitants of the land, the Canaanites, saw the mourning
        at the threshing floor of Atad, they said, \u201CThis is a grievous mourning
        for the Egyptians.\u201D Therefore the place was named Abel-mizraim (mourning
        of Egypt); it is west of the Jordan.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "So Jacob\u2019s sons did for him as he had commanded them; "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'for his sons carried him to the land of Canaan and buried him in
        the cave of the field of Machpelah, east of Mamre, which Abraham bought along
        with the field as a burial site from Ephron the Hittite. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'After he had buried his father, Joseph returned to Egypt, he and
        his brothers, and all who had gone up with him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "When Joseph\u2019s brothers saw that their father was dead, they
        said, \u201CWhat if Joseph carries a grudge against us and pays us back in
        full for all the wrong which we did to him?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "So they sent word to Joseph, saying, \u201CYour father commanded
        us before he died, saying, "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u2018You are to say to Joseph, \u201CI beg you, please forgive the
        transgression of your brothers and their sin, for they did you wrong.\u201D\u2009\u2019
        Now, please forgive the transgression of the servants of the God of your
        father.\u201D And Joseph wept when they spoke to him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Then his brothers went and fell down before him [in confession];
        then they said, \u201CBehold, we are your servants (slaves).\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "But Joseph said to them, \u201CDo not be afraid, for am I in the
        place of God? [Vengeance is His, not mine.] "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'As for you, you meant evil against me, but God meant it for good
        in order to bring about this present outcome, that many people would be kept
        alive [as they are this day]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: Death of Joseph'
      title: Death of Joseph
      number: 21
      content: "So now, do not be afraid; I will provide for you and support you
        and your little ones.\u201D So he comforted them [giving them encouragement
        and hope] and spoke [with kindness] to their hearts.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Now Joseph lived in Egypt, he and his father\u2019s household, and
        Joseph lived a hundred and ten years. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Joseph saw the third generation of Ephraim\u2019s children; also
        the children of Machir, the son of Manasseh, were born and raised on Joseph\u2019s
        knees. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Joseph said to his brothers, \u201CI am about to die, but God will
        surely take care of you and bring you up out of this land to the land which
        He promised to Abraham, to Isaac, and to Jacob [to give you].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Then Joseph made the sons of Israel (Jacob) swear [an oath], saying,
        \u201CGod will surely visit you and take care of you [returning you to Canaan],
        and [when that happens] you shall carry my bones up from here.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: So Joseph died, being a hundred and ten years old; and they embalmed
        him and he was put in a coffin in Egypt.
      comments: []
